(51, NULL, 'Mongolian National Arrested for Alleged Espionage Activities in Zambales', 46, 'MANILA, Philippines — In a shocking turn of events, a Mongolian national has been apprehended in Zambales, Philippines, in connection with alleged espionage activities. The Bureau of Immigration (BI) confirmed the arrest, raising concerns over foreign individuals engaging in intelligence-gathering operations within the country.\r\n\r\nOn October 20, 2023, the BI reported the capture of a 33-year-old Mongolian man identified only by his surname, Baatar. The arrest took place in the coastal town of San Antonio, Zambales, during an operation led by the BI\'s intelligence division. Authorities acted on a tip-off regarding Baatar’s suspicious activities, which allegedly involved gathering sensitive information potentially harmful to national security.\r\n\r\nAccording to BI Commissioner Norman Tansingco, the operation was a collaborative effort with the Philippine National Police (PNP) and the military, highlighting the growing vigilance of local authorities against espionage. Tansingco emphasized that the Philippines will not tolerate any foreign nationals engaging in activities that threaten the sovereignty and safety of the nation.\r\n\r\nWhile details surrounding the specific nature of Baatar\'s espionage activities remain scarce, reports suggest that he was surveilling military installations and other strategic locations in the vicinity. This alarming revelation has prompted discussions about national security and the potential risks posed by foreign nationals who may be involved in intelligence work for their home countries.\r\n\r\nThe BI has not disclosed whether Baatar had any accomplices or if he was part of a larger network operating within the country. However, the incident has raised questions about how foreign nationals are monitored and regulated in the Philippines, especially given the country’s strategic geopolitical position in Southeast Asia.\r\n\r\nThe arrest of Baatar is a crucial reminder of the need for heightened awareness regarding foreign activities within the Philippines. National security experts have voiced their concerns about the increasing number of foreign nationals involved in espionage and surveillance operations, particularly in regions close to military bases and critical infrastructure.\r\n\r\nAs the Philippines continues to strengthen its international partnerships and alliances, especially in the face of rising tensions in the Asia-Pacific region, the government must remain vigilant in safeguarding its national interests. This includes implementing stricter regulations on foreign workers and tourists, particularly those from countries known for engaging in espionage.\r\n\r\nIn response to this incident, the Philippine government is likely to review its policies on immigration and the monitoring of foreign nationals. Increased cooperation with international intelligence agencies may also be considered to combat the threat of espionage more effectively.\r\n\r\nThe BI has indicated that Baatar will face charges related to his espionage activities, and the investigation is ongoing to determine the full extent of his operations. Authorities are urging the public to report any suspicious behavior by foreign nationals, highlighting the critical role that community vigilance plays in national security.\r\n\r\nThe arrest of the Mongolian national in Zambales serves as a stark reminder of the ever-present threats to national security posed by espionage. As the Philippines navigates complex international relationships, it is imperative for the government to bolster its defenses against foreign intelligence activities. Public awareness and cooperation will be essential in ensuring the safety and sovereignty of the nation in this increasingly interconnected world.', 1, 10, '2026-02-16 03:06:10', '2026-02-16 03:13:53', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699289a286a076.36308613.gif', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(52, NULL, 'Basilan Ferry Disaster: Death Toll Climbs to 57 as More Bodies Recovered', 46, 'MANILA, Philippines  – The MV Lady Mary Joy 3 ferry disaster off Basilan has claimed 57 lives after three additional bodies were recovered, according to the Philippine Coast Guard. The vessel caught fire on the night of March 29, 2023, while traveling from Zamboanga City to Jolo, Sulu, forcing passengers to jump into the sea as flames rapidly engulfed the ship. Many died from smoke inhalation or were trapped inside the burning ferry.\r\n\r\nRescue operations began immediately but were hampered by darkness, strong currents, and later, the extreme depth (around 450 meters) where the vessel sank. Recovery efforts have been complex and emotionally taxing, with divers working to retrieve remains and provide closure to grieving families. Identification of victims requires forensic testing, prolonging the anguish of relatives.\r\n\r\nInvestigations led by the Maritime Industry Authority are examining possible causes, including mechanical failure, electrical faults, or safety lapses. The tragedy has renewed concerns about maritime safety in the Philippines, a country with a history of ferry disasters, including the 1987 sinking of the MV Doña Paz.\r\n\r\nThe incident underscores the urgent need for stricter safety enforcement, improved vessel standards, and systemic reforms to prevent similar maritime catastrophes in the future.', 1, 10, '2026-02-16 03:14:06', '2026-02-16 03:14:33', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69928b7ec70405.57669868.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(53, NULL, 'DOST-FNRI Sounds Alarm on Nutrition and Lifestyle Challenges', 53, 'A recent national nutrition survey conducted by the Department of Science and Technology–Food and Nutrition Research Institute (DOST-FNRI) has unveiled critical health challenges facing Filipinos. The 2023 study highlights significant nutritional deficiencies and unhealthy lifestyle patterns across various population groups. According to the findings, energy and nutrient intake remain consistently below recommended levels, while concerning trends in physical activity and risk behaviors emerge. Specifically, the survey revealed that one in ten adults struggles with high cholesterol, two in ten have elevated triglyceride levels, and a staggering three out of four adolescents are physically inactive.\r\n\r\nThe comprehensive report also exposed additional health risks, with six out of ten adults engaging in binge drinking and two out of ten adults continuing to smoke. In response, the DOST-FNRI is revisiting the Nutritional Guidelines for Filipinos (NGF), adopting a food systems approach that focuses on commonly consumed local foods and recommends adaptable dietary patterns across different income levels. The national nutrition council has already translated these guidelines into the more culturally accessible \"10 Kumainments,\" encouraging Filipinos to eat varied foods in appropriate quantities, maintain physical activity, and limit salt, sugar, and alcohol consumption. By aligning nutrition guidance with realistic food environments, the institute aims to support policies and partnerships that can make healthier diets more accessible, affordable, and sustainable for all Filipinos.', 1, 5, '2026-02-16 05:11:04', '2026-02-16 06:54:40', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992a6e8c50c14.68172712.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(54, NULL, 'Video Codec Licensing Dispute Blocks ASUS and Acer in German Market', 54, 'In a significant legal development within the tech industry, Nokia has successfully enforced its video codec patent rights against ASUS and Acer in Germany, resulting in a temporary halt of their PC and laptop sales. The dispute centers on HEVC (High-Efficiency Video Coding), a ubiquitous codec essential for modern computing devices. German courts found both companies guilty of patent infringement, mandating that they cease importing and selling new stock until they secure the necessary licensing from Nokia. While this ruling does not completely remove these brands from the German market—existing inventory can still be sold by third-party retailers—it represents a notable intervention in tech manufacturing and intellectual property regulations.\r\n\r\nThe incident highlights the complex landscape of technological licensing and international patent enforcement. Unlike previous brand bans driven by geopolitical tensions, this case stems from a specific intellectual property dispute. Other technology manufacturers have navigated similar challenges, with Hisense recently resolving a comparable situation by purchasing the required license. ASUS and Acer now face a straightforward resolution: either negotiate a licensing agreement with Nokia or risk continued sales restrictions. The outcome will likely depend on the companies\' willingness to comply with patent requirements and their assessment of the German market\'s economic significance.', 1, 5, '2026-02-16 05:18:21', '2026-02-16 06:54:36', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992a89d73e936.78293965.png', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(55, NULL, 'Northeast Monsoon Continues to Dampen Luzon', 51, 'MANILA – The Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (PAGASA) reported Wednesday that the shear line will continue to affect the Visayas, while the northeast monsoon, locally known as \"amihan,\" will persist over Luzon in the next 24 hours. In its 5 a.m. bulletin, the state weather bureau said cloudy skies with scattered rains and isolated thunderstorms are expected over the Visayas, as well as Albay, Sorsogon, Masbate, Surigao del Norte, and Dinagat Islands. Residents in these areas were advised to remain alert, as moderate to heavy rains could trigger flash floods or landslides.  Meanwhile, cloudy skies with light rains are forecast over Cagayan Valley, the Cordillera Administrative Region, the rest of the Bicol Region, Aurora, and Quezon due to the northeast monsoon. Metro Manila and the rest of Luzon will see partly cloudy to cloudy conditions with isolated light rains. The rest of Mindanao will experience partly cloudy to cloudy skies with isolated rain showers or thunderstorms caused by localized thunderstorms, which may also bring possible flash floods or landslides during severe weather. PAGASA added that moderate to strong northeast winds will affect the eastern sections of Southern Luzon, the Visayas, and Mindanao, resulting in moderate to rough seas, while other parts of the country will have light to moderate winds and slight to moderate coastal waters.\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Shelwin Buenaventura\r\nSource: MBC Chat\r\nPublished: February 16, 2026', 1, 8, '2026-02-16 05:23:39', '2026-02-16 06:54:33', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/chat_media/2026/02/thumb_6992a9db9365a.jpg', NULL, 'mbc_chat', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(56, NULL, 'DepEd Unveils Plans for Trimester-Based Academic Year', 52, 'The Department of Education (DepEd) is advocating for reforms to the school calendar, including a proposal to transition to a trimester system. This initiative is part of a holistic approach aimed at ensuring a better distribution of time across academic, co-curricular, and extracurricular activities.\r\n\r\nEducation Secretary Sonny Angara stated that the proposal aims to extend and enhance teaching periods, reduce teachers\' workload, and improve the quality of education through a more organized school year. \"We are pushing for this to create longer, uninterrupted learning periods, better pacing of lessons, and lower administrative burdens for our teachers. This way, we safeguard the quality of education,\" Angara said, referencing findings from the Second Congressional Commission on Education (EDCOM 2).\r\n\r\nUnder the proposed trimester system, the academic year will be divided into three terms, each allowing for extended teaching and enrichment activities. The goal is to facilitate continuous lesson discussions without frequent interruptions. For the 2026-2027 school year, the 201 school days will be divided into three terms, each featuring longer and uninterrupted teaching days to enhance lesson pacing. Scheduled breaks will be included between terms to provide teachers with time for lesson planning, output assessment, and other professional tasks that contribute to more effective teaching.\r\n\r\nAccording to the proposed calendar framework, classes will begin in early June, with the first trimester running from June to September, the second from September to December, and the third from January to late March to complete the 201 school days. Each term will feature instructional blocks of 54-61 days focused on quality, continuous teaching and learning, minimizing disruptions from non-academic activities. An enrichment block is also planned for remediation, grade computation, preparation and checking of school forms, and wellness breaks, among other tasks. Additionally, the first term will include an opening block for school year kick-off activities.\r\n\r\nThe reform also promotes \"low-disruption alternatives,\" where scheduled celebrations and observances will be integrated into lessons rather than conducted as separate programs that disrupt classes. \r\n\r\nDepEd data indicate that the current school calendar leads to reduced teaching time due to the need for schools to accommodate numerous mandatory observances, reporting requirements, and administrative tasks. Consequently, the flow of lessons is interrupted, increasing teachers\' workload, who often prioritize compliance over continuous instruction. For instance, national and cultural celebrations may be incorporated into reading materials, writing exercises, science discussions, and project-based learning. This integration allows students to learn about significant topics while maintaining regular class activities. Shorter reflection activities, thematic discussions, or curriculum-linked projects could replace full-day events that suspend academic instruction.\r\n\r\nDepEd is expected to release formal policy guidelines regarding the trimester calendar following consultations with teachers, school leaders, and other education stakeholders.', 1, 5, '2026-02-16 05:30:39', '2026-02-16 06:54:21', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992ab7f9440b1.30269835.png', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(57, NULL, 'Bidders Submit Proposals for Major Luang Prabang Airport Upgrade', 99, 'A pivotal moment for Laos\' economic development and burgeoning tourism sector has arrived, as multiple bidders have submitted comprehensive proposals for the extensive upgrade of Luang Prabang International Airport. This initiative marks a crucial step in the Lao government\'s overarching strategy to significantly enhance the nation\'s aviation infrastructure and position the UNESCO World Heritage city as a modern, accessible gateway for a projected surge in international visitors.\r\n\r\nThe modernization project is central to the government\'s broader commitment to overhaul key airports across the country. For Luang Prabang, a cornerstone of Lao tourism that attracts a substantial portion of international arrivals, the expansion is deemed vital. The current annual passenger capacity of one million is targeted to increase dramatically, aiming for between two and three million passengers post-upgrade. This expansion is not merely about capacity but about transforming the airport into a state-of-the-art facility capable of meeting global standards for efficiency, safety, and passenger experience.\r\n\r\nAccording to reports from the Vientiane Times, four distinct entities, comprising both local and international companies, have formally submitted their proposals for the ambitious undertaking. Their submissions outline plans to address various critical components of the airport\'s infrastructure. Key elements of the comprehensive upgrade plan are expected to include the significant expansion of the existing terminal building to accommodate higher passenger volumes and provide enhanced amenities. Furthermore, the project entails the reinforcement and potential extension of the runway, crucial for handling a wider range of aircraft types and ensuring operational resilience.\r\n\r\nBeyond these primary components, the upgrade is anticipated to encompass the construction of a new, modern air traffic control tower equipped with advanced navigation aids to bolster safety and operational precision. Plans also likely include the development of new cargo facilities to support increased trade and logistics, as well as the acquisition of modern ground support equipment to streamline operations. The overall objective is to create an airport infrastructure that can seamlessly manage increased traffic while providing a comfortable and efficient experience for travelers.\r\n\r\nThe successful implementation of this upgrade is expected to yield substantial benefits for Laos. Economically, it promises to stimulate tourism revenue, create numerous job opportunities within the aviation and hospitality sectors, and foster regional connectivity. Improved air links will make Luang Prabang more accessible to a broader international audience, further solidifying its status as a premier cultural and historical destination in Southeast Asia. This strategic investment underscores the Lao government\'s vision to leverage its natural and cultural assets for sustainable economic growth and integration into the regional economy.\r\n\r\nThe evaluation of the submitted proposals will now proceed, with authorities tasked with selecting the most suitable partner to bring this transformative vision to fruition. The chosen bidder will be instrumental in shaping the future of air travel to Luang Prabang, thereby playing a significant role in the nation\'s journey towards enhanced prosperity and global connectivity.', 1, 10, '2026-02-16 05:36:24', '2026-02-16 06:54:18', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992ad071017e5.16706684.webp', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(58, NULL, 'Love\'s Playlist: Spotify\'s Musical Matchmaking', 57, 'Spotify has launched an innovative Valentine\'s Day feature called \"Match Made in Spotify,\" allowing users to explore romantic compatibility through musical preferences. The interactive in-app experience, available from February 10, enables users to enter a crush or partner\'s favorite song and receive a unique compatibility assessment based on their shared listening data.\r\n\r\nThe playful feature works by having users input their partner\'s preferred track and then shake their phone to generate results. Spotify creates a personalized compatibility score and curates a special playlist reflecting the pair\'s musical tastes, which can be shared with friends or on social media. This creative approach transforms music into a tool for expressing and understanding relationship dynamics during the romantic season.', 1, 5, '2026-02-16 05:37:31', '2026-02-16 06:54:16', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992ad1b204e10.90525422.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(59, NULL, 'Jollibee Set to Launch Compose Coffee in the Philippines by 2026', 49, 'Manila, Philippines – Jollibee Foods Corporation, the Filipino fast-food giant known for its signature chickenjoy and spaghetti, has announced plans to expand its beverage offerings with the introduction of Compose Coffee. Targeted for launch in 2026, this new venture aims to tap into the growing coffee market in the Philippines.\r\n\r\nJollibee’s decision to enter the coffee segment comes as the popularity of coffee consumption continues to rise among Filipinos, especially among the younger demographic. According to industry reports, the Philippine coffee market has seen a significant shift towards specialty coffee shops and premium coffee products in recent years. This trend highlights a growing consumer preference for quality over quantity, which Jollibee hopes to address through Compose Coffee.\r\n\r\nThe company has revealed that Compose Coffee will feature a diverse menu of coffee beverages, including classic espresso drinks, cold brews, and unique signature blends designed to cater to local tastes. Jollibee\'s commitment to quality is evident in its announcement that the coffee will be sourced from various regions known for their rich coffee-growing heritage, aiming to deliver a product that resonates with both local and international coffee connoisseurs.\r\n\r\n“Compose Coffee is our answer to the evolving tastes of our customers,” said Jollibee CEO Ernesto Tanmantiong during a press briefing. “We have always been focused on delivering joy through our food offerings, and we believe that coffee is an essential part of that experience. With Compose Coffee, we aim to create not just a beverage, but a community space where people can come together to enjoy quality coffee.”\r\n\r\nIn line with its launch strategy, Jollibee plans to develop a network of Compose Coffee stores across the Philippines. The company is also exploring potential partnerships with local coffee farmers to ensure that its coffee is not only high quality but also sustainably sourced. This initiative aligns with Jollibee\'s broader commitment to corporate social responsibility and supporting local agriculture.\r\n\r\nThe announcement of Compose Coffee has already generated buzz on social media, with many fans expressing excitement over the prospect of a new coffee brand backed by the iconic fast-food chain. Jollibee’s extensive experience in the food and beverage industry, combined with its strong brand loyalty, positions Compose Coffee as a formidable contender in the competitive coffee market.\r\n\r\nAs part of its preparations for the launch, Jollibee is investing in research and development to refine its coffee offerings. The company intends to conduct market studies and taste tests to ensure that Compose Coffee meets the high expectations of Filipino consumers. Jollibee’s approach emphasizes innovation while maintaining affordability, a combination that has historically resonated well with its customer base.\r\n\r\nThe launch of Compose Coffee is not just about beverages; it reflects Jollibee’s strategy to diversify its product portfolio and adapt to changing consumer preferences. With coffee culture thriving in urban centers across the Philippines, Jollibee aims to capture a share of this lucrative market segment while reinforcing its position as a food industry leader.\r\n\r\nAs the launch date approaches, Jollibee is expected to unveil more details about Compose Coffee, including specific store locations and menu offerings. The company’s foray into the coffee business is seen as a significant step in its ongoing efforts to innovate and expand, ensuring that it remains at the forefront of the Philippine food and beverage industry.\r\n\r\nWith the anticipated launch of Compose Coffee, Jollibee is poised to stir excitement among coffee lovers and further enhance its reputation as a beloved brand in the Philippines.', 1, 10, '2026-02-16 05:42:26', '2026-02-16 06:54:11', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992ae4d07eb23.39932755.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(60, NULL, 'AI Impact Summit 2026 Kicks Off in Delhi, Prime Minister Modi Inaugurates Global Dialogue on Responsible AI Future', 54, 'The Bharat Mandapam, India\'s premier exhibition and convention centre, today became the epicentre of global discourse on artificial intelligence as the much-anticipated AI Impact Summit 2026 commenced its inaugural sessions at 10:00 AM. The high-profile event, poised to shape the future trajectory of AI development and deployment, was formally inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, underscoring India\'s strategic commitment to harnessing AI for inclusive growth and global well-being.\r\n\r\nThe Summit, a flagship initiative by the Indian government in collaboration with leading technology organizations and international bodies, has drawn an unparalleled congregation of policymakers, industry titans, academic researchers, civil society representatives, and AI innovators from across the globe. Over the next several days, participants are expected to delve into the multifaceted implications of artificial intelligence, ranging from ethical considerations and governance frameworks to economic transformation, social impact, and the imperative for responsible innovation.\r\n\r\nIn his keynote address, Prime Minister Modi articulated a compelling vision for India\'s role in the global AI landscape, emphasizing the nation\'s dual commitment to technological advancement and ethical stewardship. \"AI is not merely a tool; it is a profound force that will redefine human civilization,\" Prime Minister Modi stated, addressing a packed hall of delegates. \"India, with its vast talent pool, democratic values, and an unwavering belief in \'Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam\' – the world is one family – is uniquely positioned to lead the charge in building an AI future that is equitable, accessible, and beneficial for all.\"\r\n\r\nThe Prime Minister highlighted the necessity of a human-centric approach to AI development, stressing that technology must serve humanity, not supersede it. He called for international collaboration to establish robust ethical guidelines, data privacy standards, and transparent AI systems that prevent bias and ensure accountability. \"The speed of AI\'s evolution demands agile governance. We must collectively foster an ecosystem where innovation thrives, yet is anchored by strong ethical guardrails and a commitment to public good,\" he added, receiving widespread applause.\r\n\r\nThe AI Impact Summit 2026 arrives at a critical juncture, as nations grapple with the transformative potential and inherent challenges posed by increasingly sophisticated AI systems. Discussions throughout the summit are structured around several key pillars:\r\n* Ethical AI and Governance:** Exploring frameworks for responsible AI development, bias mitigation, fairness, transparency, and accountability.\r\n* Economic Transformation and Future of Work:** Analyzing AI\'s impact on industries, job creation, skill development, and economic growth models.\r\n* Social Impact and Inclusivity:** Addressing AI\'s role in healthcare, education, agriculture, public services, and ensuring equitable access to its benefits.\r\n* AI Innovation and Research:** Showcasing cutting-edge advancements, fostering research collaboration, and identifying priority areas for future development.\r\n* Cybersecurity and AI Safety:** Deliberating on the security implications of AI and strategies for building resilient and safe AI systems.\r\n\r\nIndia\'s proactive stance on AI has been evident through various initiatives, including the National Strategy for Artificial Intelligence, launched with the vision of \'AI for All.\' The Prime Minister reiterated India\'s commitment to leveraging AI to solve pressing societal challenges, particularly in sectors like healthcare, where AI can enhance diagnostics and drug discovery, and agriculture, where it can optimize crop yields and mitigate climate risks. He also pointed to India\'s burgeoning startup ecosystem, which is increasingly contributing to AI innovation, and the government\'s efforts to foster digital literacy and AI skills among its youth.\r\n\r\nSeveral high-profile speakers are slated to address the summit in the coming days, including prominent AI researchers, CEOs of global tech giants, heads of international organizations, and ministers from various countries. The agenda includes a series of plenary sessions, interactive workshops, and expert panel discussions designed to facilitate robust dialogue and actionable outcomes. A dedicated exhibition zone, running concurrently with the summit, showcases groundbreaking AI applications and innovations from startups, research institutions, and established companies, offering attendees a glimpse into the future of AI technology.\r\n\r\n\"This summit is more than just a gathering; it is a crucible for ideas, a platform for partnerships, and a call to action,\" remarked Dr. Anjali Sharma, CEO of TechBridge India and a key organizer of the event. \"We aim to foster a global consensus on how AI can be developed and deployed responsibly, ensuring that its benefits are widely shared and its risks thoughtfully managed. India\'s leadership in convening such a diverse and influential group is a testament to its growing stature in the global technology arena.\"\r\n\r\nThe discussions are expected to culminate in a Delhi Declaration on Responsible AI, potentially outlining a shared international framework for AI governance, ethical principles, and collaborative research initiatives. Such an outcome would significantly advance global efforts to navigate the complexities of AI, building on the groundwork laid by previous international forums and national strategies.\r\n\r\nAs the world stands at the precipice of an AI-driven revolution, the AI Impact Summit 2026 at Bharat Mandapam serves as a critical forum for charting a collective path forward. With Prime Minister Modi’s inauguration setting a clear tone for responsible and inclusive AI development, the coming days are poised to lay down foundational principles for a future where artificial intelligence truly serves as a force for global good. The eyes of the technological world are firmly fixed on New Delhi, anticipating the insights and directions that will emerge from this pivotal gathering.', 1, 11, '2026-02-16 05:52:32', '2026-02-16 06:54:07', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/chat_media/2026/02/thumb_6992b0a0d2ced.jpg', NULL, 'mbc_chat', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(62, NULL, 'Annular Solar Eclipse 2026: Anticipation Builds for \'Ring of Fire\' Across Southern Hemisphere', 100, 'Anticipation is mounting among astronomers and skygazers worldwide for the annular solar eclipse slated for February 17, 2026. This celestial event, often dubbed the \"Ring of Fire,\" will offer a breathtaking spectacle as the Moon passes directly in front of the Sun, but appears too small to completely cover it, leaving a luminous ring of sunlight visible around the lunar silhouette. While a narrow corridor will experience the full annular phase, a much broader expanse of the globe will witness a partial solar eclipse.\r\n\r\nThe path of annularity, where the iconic \"Ring of Fire\" will be visible, is set to traverse some of the Earth\'s most remote and southernmost regions. The primary beneficiary of this full spectacle will be Antarctica, offering a unique opportunity for scientific expeditions and intrepid travelers. Following its sweep across the icy continent, the eclipse path will extend northeastward, briefly touching the southern tip of South America.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, parts of southern Chile and Argentina, particularly within the rugged landscapes of Patagonia, are positioned to experience the annular phase. Viewers in these regions, with appropriate safety precautions, will witness the Moon perfectly centered against the Sun, revealing the dazzling annulus. Additionally, the Falkland Islands, located in the South Atlantic, also fall within this narrow band, presenting a rare chance for residents and visitors to observe the full \'Ring of Fire\'.\r\n\r\nFor a significantly wider audience, a partial solar eclipse will be observable. This includes much of South America, extending from its southern reaches northward into vast areas of the continent. Parts of Africa, particularly its southwestern coastal regions, will also be treated to a partial obscuration of the sun. The Antarctic continent, beyond the path of annularity, will likewise experience varying degrees of partial eclipse.\r\n\r\nIt is crucial for anyone planning to observe the eclipse, whether annular or partial, to prioritize eye safety. Directly viewing the Sun, even when partially obscured, can cause permanent eye damage. Specialized solar viewing glasses or filters, certified to international safety standards (ISO 12312-2), are essential. Alternatively, indirect viewing methods such as pinhole projectors can provide a safe way to witness the event. Regular sunglasses are insufficient and unsafe for solar viewing.\r\n\r\nUnlike a total solar eclipse, where the Moon completely blocks the Sun\'s disk and allows for a brief period of naked-eye viewing of the corona, an annular eclipse never fully obscures the Sun. Therefore, solar filters must be used throughout the entire duration of an annular eclipse to prevent eye injury.\r\n\r\nThe 2026 annular solar eclipse presents a significant astronomical event, drawing attention to the intricate mechanics of our solar system. For those within the path of annularity, careful planning will be paramount to witness this rare and captivating celestial phenomenon.', 1, 11, '2026-02-16 06:37:08', '2026-02-17 08:09:13', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6992bb1413a906.22264532.webp', NULL, 'manual', 'Annular nga Eklipse kan Araw 2026: Nagdadakul an Ekspektasyon para sa \'Singsing kan Apoy\' sa Timog nga Hemisperyo', 'Nagdadakul an anticipasyon sa mga astronomo asin mga nagmamasid sa langit sa bilog na mundo para sa annular solar eclipse na naka-iskedyul sa Pebrero 17, 2026. Ini na celestial event, na kadalasang tinatawag na \"Ring of Fire,\" maghahatag nin nakakagandang tan-awon habang ang Buwan nag-aagi direkta sa atubangan kan Araw, pero nag-aapod na mas maliit para sa kumpletong pagtakop, nag-iiwan nin maliwanag na singsing kan sinag kan adlaw na nakikita sa palibot kan silweta kan Buwan. Samantalang an makitid na daan makakaranas kan kumpletong annular phase, an mas malawak na bahagi kan mundo makakakita nin partial solar eclipse.\n\nAn landas kan annularity, kun sain makikita an tanyag na \"Ring of Fire,\" naka-iskedyul na mag-agi sa mga pinaka-remote asin pinaka-timog na rehiyon kan Daigdig. An pangunahing makikinabang sa ini na kumpletong tan-awon amo an Antarctica, na nag-aalok nin natatanging oportunidad para sa mga siyentipikong ekspedisyon asin mga matapang na biyahero. Pagkatapos kan pag-agi nito sa nagyeyelo na kontinente, an landas kan eclipse magpapadayon sa hilagang-silangan, saglit na tatamaan an timog na dulo kan Timog Amerika.\n\nPartikular, an mga parte kan timog na Chile asin Argentina, lalo na sa magubot na tanawin kan Patagonia, nakaposisyon para makaranas kan annular phase. An mga manunood sa mga rehiyon ini, sa tamang mga hakbang sa seguridad, makakakita kan Buwan na perpektong nakasentro sa atubangan kan Araw, nagpapakita kan nakakasilaw na annulus. Dugang pa, an Falkland Islands, na nasa Timog Atlantiko, nahuhulog man sa ini na makitid na banda, nag-aalok nin bihirang pagkakataon para sa mga residente asin bisita na masaksihan an kumpletong \'Ring of Fire\'.\n\nPara sa mas malawak na audience, an partial solar eclipse makikita. Ini naglalakip kan kadaklan kan Timog Amerika, nag-aabot halik sa mga timog na bahagi papuntang hilaga sa malawak na lugar kan kontinente. An mga parte kan Africa, partikular an mga timog-kanlurang baybayin, makakaranas man nin partial na pagtakip kan araw. An kontinente kan Antarctica, lampas sa landas kan annularity, makakaranas man nin iba-ibang antas kan partial eclipse.\n\nMahalaga para sa sinuman na nagbabalak na masaksihan an eclipse, maging annular man o partial, na unahon an kaligtasan kan mata. An direktang pagtan-aw sa Araw, maski pa man ini ay bahagyang natatakpan, puede magdulot nin permanenteng pinsala sa mata. An mga espesyal na salamin para sa solar viewing o mga filter, na sertipikado sa internasyonal na pamantayan sa seguridad (ISO 12312-2), ay mahalaga. Sa alternatibo, an mga hindi direktang paraan kan pagtan-aw, tulad kan pinhole projectors, puede maghatag nin ligtas na paraan para masaksihan an event. An mga regular na salamin sa araw ay hindi sapat asin delikado para sa solar viewing.\n\nHindi tulad kan total solar eclipse, kun sain an Buwan kumpletong nagtatakip sa disk kan Araw asin nag-aalok nin saglit na panahon kan pagtan-aw sa corona gamit an mata, an annular eclipse hindi man kumpletong nagtatakip sa Araw. Kaya, an mga solar filters kinahanglan gamiton sa kabug-usan kan panahon kan annular eclipse para maiwasan an pinsala sa mata.\n\nAn 2026 annular solar eclipse nag-aalok nin dakulang astronomical event, nagdadala nin atensyon sa masalimuot na mekanika kan satuyang solar system. Para sa mga nasa landas kan annularity, an maingat na pagpaplano magiging mahalaga para masaksihan ini na bihirang asin nakakabighaning celestial phenomenon.', 'Bicolano', '2026-02-17 16:09:13', 1),
(63, NULL, 'Testing Title', 96, 'Testing Description,Testing Description,Testing Description,Testing Description\n\n---\nAuthor: Cloyd\nSource: MBC Chat\nPublished: February 16, 2026\n', 1, 1, '2026-02-16 07:47:40', '2026-02-17 07:55:29', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/chat_media/2026/02/thumb_6992cb9c46b73.jpg', NULL, 'mbc_chat', 'Pagsulay nga Ulohan', '', 'Cebuano (Bisaya)', '2026-02-17 15:55:29', 1),
(65, NULL, 'Marcoleta agrees to debate Carpio on West Philippine Sea', 98, 'MANILA, Philippines — Sen. Rodante Marcoleta has accepted retired Supreme Court senior associate justice Antonio Carpio’s challenge to debate on the South China Sea issue. Speaking to GMA News yesterday, Marcoleta said he is amenable to the offer of the Philippine Bar Association to host a debate with the legal luminary if only to settle criticisms that he was defending China’s interests in questioning the West Philippine Sea (WPS). In accepting Marcoleta’s dare, Carpio said the debate would serve as an opportunity to “correct” Marcoleta’s claims that he said “misinform the people.” Marcoleta said he wants a no-holds barred debate, as opposed to the bar association’s plan to “limit” the discussions. “I am willing no matter the date, but about the limitations being mentioned, it wasn’t clear if they will be removed,” he stressed. “So that the entire Filipino people will triumph, because how do you limit the vast subject matter of the West Philippine Sea? This is not only an extensive topic. This is complex and its consequences are far-reaching. So, there should be no limitations, especially that the limitations allegedly came from me when I did not say those things,” Marcoleta said. But according to the bar association president Rachelle Aileen Santos, the limitations are only intended to focus the discussion and make it a “formal debate,” so it would not be a “free-wheeling” one that is the “source of all the confusion.” Marcoleta denied that he was muddling the issue by making sweeping interpellations at the Senate. He also denied that he was jeopardizing the country’s arbitral-backed claims within its exclusive economic zone (EEZ) when he took to the plenary and interpellated the adopted Senate resolution condemning the Chinese embassy in Manila’s social media rants against senators critical of Beijing. He also denied saying in a Commission on Appointments hearing that the Kalayaan Island Group was not part of the Philippines – a bold statement that was heavily criticized by residents there as well as experts who said there are several legal bases, including the new Philippine Maritime Zones law. He called criticisms against him fallacies that only put words in his mouth. Philstar.com is one of the most vibrant, opinionated, discerning communities of readers on cyberspace. With your meaningful insights, help shape the stories that can shape the country. Sign up now!\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Philstar\r\nSource: Philstar\r\nPublished: February 18, 2026', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 01:38:31', '2026-02-18 02:24:16', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6995184ae6dcc1.85392998.png', NULL, 'external_import', 'Si Marcoleta nagkasabot na makipagdebate kay Carpio sa West Philippine Sea.', 'MANILA, Pilipinas — Inawat ni Sen. Rodante Marcoleta an hamon ni retiradong senior associate justice Antonio Carpio na magdebate sa isyu kan South China Sea. Sa pag-istorya sa GMA News kahapon, sinabi ni Marcoleta na siya ay bukas sa alok kan Philippine Bar Association na mag-host nin debate sa nasabing legal na eksperto para ma-settle an mga kritisismo na siya ay nagtatanggol sa interes kan China sa pag-question sa West Philippine Sea (WPS). Sa pagtanggap sa hamon ni Marcoleta, sinabi ni Carpio na an debate magiging oportunidad para \"ituwid\" an mga pahayag ni Marcoleta na aniya \"nagbibigay ng maling impormasyon sa mga tao.\" Sinabi ni Marcoleta na gusto niya an debate na walang limitasyon, sa kabaligtaran kan plano kan bar association na \"limitahan\" an mga diskusyon. “Handa ako anuman an petsa, pero tungkol sa mga limitasyon na binanggit, hindi klaro kung ito ay aalisin,” diin niya. “Para magtagumpay an buong bayan Pilipino, dahil paano mo ililimit an malawak na paksa kan West Philippine Sea? Diri lang ini basta-basta na paksa. Komplikado ini at an mga epekto nito ay malawak. Kaya, dapat walang limitasyon, lalo na’t an mga limitasyon ay sinasabing galing sa akin nang hindi ko naman sinabi ang mga bagay na iyon,” dagdag ni Marcoleta. Pero ayon kay Rachelle Aileen Santos, presidente kan bar association, an mga limitasyon ay para lang magpokus an diskusyon at gawing \"pormal na debate,\" kaya hindi ito magiging \"malaya\" na debate na \"pinagmumulan ng lahat ng kalituhan.\" Tinanggihan ni Marcoleta na siya ay naguguluhan sa isyu sa pamamagitan kan malawak na interpellations sa Senado. Tinanggihan din niya na siya ay naglalagay sa panganib kan mga arbitral-backed claims kan bansa sa loob kan exclusive economic zone (EEZ) nang siya ay nag-interpellate sa plenary sa inaprubahang resolusyon kan Senado na kumukondena sa mga social media rants kan Chinese embassy sa Manila laban sa mga senador na kritikal sa Beijing. Tinanggihan din niya na sinabi sa isang pagdinig kan Commission on Appointments na an Kalayaan Island Group ay hindi parte kan Pilipinas – isang matapang na pahayag na labis na kinondena kan mga residente doon pati na rin kan mga eksperto na nagsabi na may mga legal na batayan, kasama na an bagong batas sa Philippine Maritime Zones. Tinawag niya an mga kritisismo laban sa kanya na mga maling akala na naglalagay lang ng mga salita sa kanyang bibig. Ang Philstar.com ay isa sa mga pinaka-aktibo, may opinyon, at mapanlikhang komunidad ng mga mambabasa sa cyberspace. Sa iyong makabuluhang pananaw, tulungan ang paghubog kan mga kwento na makakapagpabago sa bansa. Mag-sign up na!', 'Bicolano', '2026-02-18 10:24:16', 1),
(66, NULL, 'Alex Eala, pinataob ang World No. 8 na si Jasmine Paolini sa Dubai Tennis Championships', 98, 'Nalampasan ni Alexandra “Alex” Eala ang matinding pagsubok sa No.6 seed ng torneo na si Jasmine Paolini ng Italy, 6-1, 7-6(5), sa Round of 32 ng Dubai Tennis Championships nitong Miyerkoles ng madaling-araw upang umabante sa susunod na yugto ng torneo. SINO SIYA?: Jasmine Paolini ng Italya, ang sunod na pagsubok kay Alex Eala sa Dubai Tennis Championships Matapos dominahin ang unang set, mas tumindi ang hamon mula sa Italian sa ikalawang set. Maagang nakakuha si Eala ng 3-1 abante sa ikalawang set bago nakabawi si Paolini ng dalawang sunod na laro at maitabla ang iskor. Mabilis namang nabawi ni Eala sa kaniyang lakas at nakuha ang sumunod na dalawang laro upang maging abot-kamay na ang tagumpay. Sa ikasiyam na laro, habang si Eala ang nagsi-serve para sana sa panalo, nagawa pang patagalin ni Paolini ang laban nang makakuha siya ng tatlong match point, at nanatiling buhay sa laban. Naipantay ni Paolini ang set sa 5-all bago nakalamang, 6-5, sa gitna ng set na puno ng mga error. Ngunit hindi nawalan ng pag-asa ang kasalukuyang World No. 47 na si Eala at nailigtas ang dalawang set point upang maitulak ang laban sa tiebreak. Maagang nakalamang si Paolini, 3-2, sa tiebreak ngunit sumagot ang Filipina ace sa pamamagitan ng tatlong sunod na puntos upang makuha na ang kontrol. Nailigtas pa ni Paolini ang isa pang match point, ngunit makalipas ang isang oras at 40 minuto, tuluyan nang inangkin ni Eala ang pinaghirapang tagumpay. Sunod na makakalaban ni Eala si Sorana Cîrstea ng Romania.\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: GMA News\r\nSource: GMA News\r\nPublished: February 18, 2026', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 01:39:55', '2026-02-18 02:16:20', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699519251e0824.36435163.png', NULL, 'external_import', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(67, NULL, 'Pangilinan bill also seeks abolition of travel tax', 46, 'MANILA, Philippines — Another bill seeking to abolish the mandatory travel tax for Filipinos flying overseas has been filed in the Senate.\r\n\r\nFiled by Sen. Francis “Kiko” Pangilinan, Senate Bill No. 1843, also known as “An Act Abolishing the Travel Tax,” aims to reduce the expenses for Filipinos going on trips abroad, particularly those with limited means.\r\n\r\nThe current mandatory travel tax is P1,620 for those flying economy, and P2,700 for those in first-class.\r\n\r\nAccording to Pangilinan, the travel tax is an “economic burden” for Filipinos who have the right to visit other countries, regardless of status, as stated under the 1987 Constitution.\r\n\r\n“By lowering the cost of international travel, we expect to stimulate passenger volume, increase spending on transport, accommodation, food and services, and generate positive spillovers across the economy,” Pangilinan said.\r\n\r\n“Increased travel activity also strengthens people-to-people exchanges and supports the Philippines’ positioning as a competitive and accessible destination,” he added.\r\n\r\nShould the bill be passed into law, the programs supported by travel taxes will instead be funded by the Department of Tourism for Tourism Infrastructure and Enterprise Zone Authority, the Commission on Higher Education for the Higher Education Development Fund, and the National Commission for Culture and Arts for the National Endowment Fund for Culture and the Arts.\r\n\r\n\r\nGovernment agencies and private entities will also be prohibited from collecting travel taxes, and passengers who already paid travel taxes for departures scheduled on and after the passage of the bill will get a refund.\r\n\r\nSimilar bills were filed in the past by Senators Juan Miguel Zubiri, Joel Villanueva and Erwin Tulfo, while a counterpart measure was lodged recently in the House of Representatives by Ilocos Norte Rep. Sandro Marcos, the President’s son.', 1, 13, '2026-02-18 01:41:33', '2026-02-18 02:16:16', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699518cd49d630.00677825.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(68, NULL, 'Allegations in Epstein files may amount to \'crimes against humanity,\' UN experts say', 98, 'Millions of files related to the late sex offender Jeffrey Epstein suggest the existence of a \"global criminal enterprise\" that carried out acts meeting the legal threshold of crimes against humanity, according to a panel of independent experts appointed by the United Nations Human Rights Council. The experts said crimes outlined in documents released by the US Justice Department were committed against a backdrop of supremacist beliefs, racism, corruption and extreme misogyny. The crimes, they said, showed a commodification and dehumanization of women and girls. \"So grave is the scale, nature, systematic character, and transnational reach of these atrocities against women and girls, that a number of them may reasonably meet the legal threshold of crimes against humanity,\" the experts said in a statement. The experts said the allegations contained in the files require an independent, thorough and impartial investigation, and said inquiries should also be launched into how it was possible for such crimes to be committed for so long. The US Justice Department did not immediately respond to a request for comment. A law, approved by Congress with broad bipartisan support in November, requires all Epstein-related files to be made public. The UN experts raised concerns about \"serious compliance failures and botched redactions\" that exposed sensitive victim information. More than 1,200 victims were identified in the documents that have been released so far. \"The reluctance to fully disclose information or broaden investigations, has left many survivors feeling retraumatized and subjected to what they describe as \'institutional gaslighting,\'\" the experts said. The Justice Department\'s release of documents has revealed Epstein\'s ties to many prominent people in politics, finance, academia and business - both before and after he pleaded guilty in 2008 to prostitution charges, including soliciting an underage girl. He was found hanged in his jail cell in 2019 after being arrested again on federal charges of sex trafficking of minors. His death was ruled a suicide. —Reuters\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: GMA News\r\nSource: GMA News\r\nPublished: February 18, 2026', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 01:43:36', '2026-02-18 02:16:13', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6995195d3c7fe9.42769702.jpg', NULL, 'external_import', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0);
