(85, 83, 'Kalayaan, Palawan officials cited as West PH Sea heroes after China ban', 46, 'Akbayan Party-list and Atin Ito coalition on Tuesday recognized as West Philippine Sea (WPS) heroes the 16 local officials of Kalayaan municipality in Palawan banned by China.\r\n\r\nThe groups gave the WPS Heroes Award to the local officials, collectively known as Kalayaan 16, on Chinese New Year, saying it was very deserving given how they have put up a brave stand against repeated Chinese aggression in the West Philippine Sea and within the country’s exclusive economic zone which are nearby their hometown.\r\n\r\n\"Kalayaan 16 are modern day heroes. They prove that there are no “casual commentators” when it comes to our sovereignty. Ordinary Filipinos are at the frontlines of our defense of the West Philippine Sea. China’s harassment only makes us stronger,” said Akbayan Party president Rafaela David, who has led civilian aid missions to the West Philippine Sea.\r\n\r\nChina banned Kalayaan local officials from entering China, Hong Kong and Macau after the town declared Chinese Ambassador Jing Quan persona non grata and banned the diplomat from setting foot in the Kalayaan islands.\r\n\r\n“China’s retaliatory ban has, in truth, backfired. China’s very act of banning the Kalayaan 16 is an effective recognition of the authority of the Municipality of Kalayaan as an official government unit of the Philippines,” David said.\r\n\r\nKalayaan Vice Mayor Maurice Phillip Alexis Albayda, Sangguniang Bayan Member Francis Polizon, and other personnel of the municipal government, accepted the distinction in behalf of the local government officials.\r\n\r\n\"Ngayong panahon pinakamasarap maging Pilipino. Karangalang maituturing ang mamatay para sa bayan. Kadakilaan ang mabuhay para rito!,” Albayda said after receiving the award.\r\n\r\n(This is the best time to be a Filipino. It is an honor to live and die for our country.)\r\n\r\nIn the same press conference, House Deputy Minority Leader Chel Diokno reiterated his call for the passage of the West Philippine Sea Education Bill under House Bill 1625 “to combat misinformation and \'Tsinador\' narratives in honor of the brave heroes defending the WPS.”\r\n\r\n\"The Kalayaan 16 are heroes because they represent our nation’s collective struggle to defend our territory and sovereignty in the WPS. Like them, we must all stand firm against intimidation and harassment by foreign powers. That is why we must pass our WPS Education Bill. When our people know the truth about the West Philippine Sea, it becomes harder to deceive and silence us,” Diokno said.\r\n\r\nAkbayan party-list Rep. Perci Cendaña and Dadah Ismula, for their part, pledged to ensure that the bravery of Kalayaan residents is matched by government investment:\r\n\r\n“Our support for our Kalayaan Island residents goes beyond mere rhetoric. Akbayan will push for greater budgetary support for the civilian community—from basic services to infrastructure. Hindi natin sila pwedeng iwan sa ere lalo na ngayong mas tumitindi ang pang-bubully ng China sa mga opisyal at mga residente ng Kalayaan,” Cendaña said.\r\n\r\n(We can’t leave them hanging, especially amid intensified Chinese bullying.)\r\n\r\n“Tutulungan natin ang komunidad ng Kalayaan na gawing sentro ng turismo at kabuhayan ang kanilang isla bilang pagtindig sa ating karapatan. By making portions of Kalayaan as destinations for ecotourism, we are not afraid to take care and develop what is rightfully ours,” Ismulah added.\r\n\r\n(We would aid the Kalayaan community in making their hometown the center of tourism and livelihood in pushing for our rights.)\r\n\r\nIn a separate statement, ACT Teachers Party-list Rep. Antonio Tinio, Gabriela Party-list Rep. Sarah Jane Elago, and Kabataan Party-list Rep. Atty. Renee Louise Co called out the Chinese government by citing that threats or warnings of economic sanctions or consequences against the Philippines are not consistent with calls for peaceful resolution.\r\n\r\n“Such threats undermine diplomatic efforts and breed resentment among the Filipino people, who have long valued friendship and cooperation with the Chinese people. The Chinese government should dial down its rhetoric and cease its aggressive actions in the West Philippine Sea, including harassment of Filipino fisherfolk, blocking of Philippine vessels conducting legitimate resupply and patrol missions, and militarization of disputed features. These actions violate international law, including UNCLOS and the 2016 arbitral ruling that affirmed Philippine sovereign rights,” they said.\r\n\r\n“Peaceful coexistence can only be achieved if China respects Philippine sovereignty and maritime rights, and if disputes are resolved through dialogue and adherence to international law—not through coercion or intimidation,” they added. —AOL, GMA Integrated News', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 02:45:30', '2026-02-18 02:53:25', 3, 1, 'developing', 2, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699527ca638d7.png', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(87, 8, 'Fuel Prices Surge for Sixth Straight Week, Adding PHP1.20 per Liter for Gasoline', 49, 'Fuel consumers in the Philippines will face another week of price increases, with major oil companies announcing significant pump price hikes starting Tuesday morning. Gasoline will rise by PHP1.20 per liter, while diesel and kerosene will increase by PHP0.60 per liter, continuing a six-week trend of escalating fuel costs.\r\n\r\nThe latest price surge follows last week\'s increases, which saw gasoline rise by PHP0.60 per liter, diesel by PHP1.00 per liter, and kerosene by PHP0.60 per liter. Motorists and consumers are likely to feel the continued economic pressure from these persistent price increments.\r\n\r\nThe persistent rise in fuel prices could have broader implications for transportation costs, consumer goods pricing, and overall economic spending in the Philippines.', 1, 4, '2026-02-18 02:56:19', '2026-02-18 02:56:34', 3, 1, 'developing', 2, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69952a539ce03.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(88, NULL, 'Sara Duterte, tatakbong presidente sa 2028', 48, 'Inanunsyo ni Bise Presidente Sara Duterte nitong Miyerkoles na tatakbo siyang presidente sa 2028 national elections. \"Ako si Sara Duterte tatakbo bilang pangulo ng Pilipinas,” sabi ni Duterte sa isang punong balitaan. Bago ang punong balitaan, iniutos ni Duterte ang pagtanggal ng logo ng Office of the Vice President sa podium. Hindi siya sumagot sa anumang tanong mula sa mga reporter pagkatapos ng kaniyang talumpati. Sinabi niya na inaako niya ang buong responsibilidad para sa kaniyang mga desisyon sa politika at kinilala ang pagkadismaya ng publiko sa mga isyung pambansa. “Mga kababayan, humihingi ako ng paumanhin sa inyong lahat. Patawad kung tinulungan kong mahalal si BBM bilang Pangulo ng ating bansa,” sabi niya. Sinabi ng Pangalawang Pangulo na bigo si Pangulong Ferdinand \"Bongbong\" Marcos Jr. na tuparin ang mga pangako sa kampanya at sinumpaang tungkulin. Sinabi rin ni Duterte na nagbitiw siya sa kaniyang posisyon sa Gabinete matapos magdesisyong hindi niya masusuportahan ang pambansang badyet para sa 2025 na inilarawan niyang \"tainted with corruption.\" Sinabi niyang inaasahan na niyang hahantong sa impeachment ang kaniyang pagbibitiw bilang kalihim ng Department of Education. “Dahil hindi ko kinayang maging bahagi ng 2025 national budget na tadtad ng katiwalian, pinili kong umalis sa Gabinete,” sabi niya. Sinabi ni Duterte na sa mga unang buwan pa lamang ng administrasyon, sinimulan na niyang kuwestiyonin ang inilarawan niyang kawalan ng integridad sa pamamahala. Sa limang-pahinang talumpati, inilista ni Duterte ang tinatawag niyang mga kabiguan ng administrasyon: patuloy na pagbaha, pagtaas ng presyo ng mga pangunahing bilihin, kawalan ng seguridad sa pagkain, mahinang sistema ng pangangalagang pangkalusugan, pagguho ng imprastraktura, at ang patuloy na krimen, ilegal na droga, at terorismo. Binatikos din niya ang inilarawan niya bilang kawalan ng malinaw at malayang foreign policy, at sinabi niyang nanganganib ang bansa na maipit sa pagitan ng mga pandaigdigang superpower. “Patuloy ang pagtaas ng presyo ng mga pangunahing bilihin habang nananatiling kapos ang kita ng bawat pamilya,” sabi niya. Iginiit pa ni Duterte na layunin ng mga imbestigasyon na may motibong politika at paulit-ulit na mga akusasyon na sirain ang kaniyang reputasyon, kabilang ang inilarawan niya bilang \"scripted\" na congressional inquiries. “Matagal na akong inaatake gamit ang buong makinarya ng kapangyarihan,” sabi niya. Bagama\'t sinabi niyang hindi siya natatakot para sa sarili, nagpahayag naman ng pagmamalasakit si Duterte para sa kinabukasan ng bansa, lalo na para sa mga nakababatang henerasyon. “May takot ako para sa ating mga anak. May takot ako para sa mga susunod na henerasyon,” sabi niya. Sinabi ni Duterte na ang kaniyang kandidatura ay isang pag-aalok ng serbisyo imbes na pagkuha ng simpatiya. “I cannot kneel before each and every Filipino to beg for forgiveness. Instead, I offer my life, my strength, and my future in the service of our nation,” sabi niya. —VBL GMA Integrated News\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: GMA News\r\nSource: GMA News\r\nPublished: February 18, 2026', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 05:10:16', '2026-02-18 05:48:25', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699549d9bfc0e9.96445824.jpg', NULL, 'external_import', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(89, NULL, 'Vlogger: I posted fake Marcos medical records ‘to keep up with trend’', 98, 'Vlogger: I posted fake Marcos medical records ‘to keep up with trend’\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Inquirer\r\nSource: Inquirer\r\nPublished: February 18, 2026', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 05:12:44', '2026-02-18 05:47:55', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69954a65032053.68576045.jpg', NULL, 'external_import', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(90, 89, 'Marcos medical records: NBI files cyberlibel case vs Sonza', 98, 'MANILA, Philippines — For allegedly spreading false medical information about President Marcos, the National Bureau of Investigation (NBI) has filed complaints for cyberlibel against former broadcaster Jay Sonza and online personality Jeffrey Celiz.\r\n\r\nThe NBI said screenshots of online posts and surveillance of YouTube videos showed the use of unverified medical reports to question the President’s capacity to govern.\r\n\r\nThe NBI recommended to the Department of Justice the filing of complaints for cyberlibel and violation of Article 154 of the Revised Penal Code against Sonza ad Celiz.\r\n\r\nSocial media personality Jack Argota has been summoned to appear at the NBI tomorrow over the alleged circulation of Marcos’ fake medical records.\r\n\r\nNBI spokesman Palmer Mallari said Argota was initially scheduled to face the Cybercrime Division on Feb. 13, but requested for a reset through email.\r\n\r\nAside from Argota, Sonza and other personalities are under investigation for allegedly spreading a fabricated medical certificate of the President.\r\n\r\nA medical certificate regarding Marcos’ health condition circulated online, which Malacañang condemned as “fabricated and malicious.”\r\n\r\nIn January, the St. Luke’s Medical Center denied the accuracy of the results of an abnormal CT scan supposedly done on Marcos, who has been diagnosed with diverticulitis.', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 05:19:01', '2026-02-18 05:48:21', 3, 1, 'developing', 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69954bc5ba17d.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(91, NULL, 'Retail prices of rice lower in early February, says PSA', 59, 'MANILA, Philippines — The average retail price of rice decreased in early February, even as farm-gate prices for palay or unmilled rice steadily increased.\r\n\r\nAccording to the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA), the retail price of regular milled rice averaged P45.54 per kilogram in the Feb. 1-5 period. This was down 4.7 percent from P47.77 per kg in the same period a year ago.\r\n\r\nHowever, the average retail price was 4.1 percent higher than the P43.76 per kg recorded in the Jan. 15-17 period.\r\n\r\nAmong the regions, the highest retail price of P50.67 per kg was recorded in the Bangsamoro Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao. The lowest at P40.29 per kg was seen in Mimaropa (Mindoro, Marinduque, Romblon and Palawan).\r\n\r\nThe statistics agency reported lower prices despite a steady rise in palay prices. \r\n\r\nThis followed the temporary rice import ban from September to December last year.\r\n\r\nAgriculture Secretary Francisco Tiu Laurel Jr. said the import suspension lifted palay prices. These have been decreasing due to excessive rice importation in previous years.\r\n\r\n“Excess importation undermines the profitability of rice farming by depressing palay prices at harvest time and discouraging production,” Tiu Laurel said in a statement last week.', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 05:23:49', '2026-02-18 05:48:11', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69954ce57868d5.55770148.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(94, NULL, 'Couple, helper charged with murder of cop, son', 47, 'MANILA, Philippines — The Quezon City police have filed murder charges against a car agent, her husband, and their helper for allegedly killing Police Senior Master Sgt. Diane Marie Mollenido and her son, 8-year-old John Ysmael, over a car deal scam.\r\n\r\n“The suspects, identified as Christian [Panganiban], Pia Katrina [Panganiban], and Gil [Dy Jr.], have been formally charged with two counts of murder, with no bail recommended, after the investigating prosecutor [found] prima facie evidence with a reasonable certainty of conviction against them,” the Quezon City Police District (QCPD) said in a statement on Tuesday.\r\n\r\n“In addition, Maribel [Panganiban], who was initially named as a suspect, has been cleared of all charges and will now be treated as an ordinary witness,” the QCPD added.\r\n\r\nMaribel is the sister of Christian Panganiban, a dismissed policeman. She and Dy were earlier suspected of having helped the couple clean up the crime scene.', 1, 12, '2026-02-18 05:51:53', '2026-02-18 06:57:47', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_6995537985aba4.12400254.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(96, NULL, 'Bam Aquino: EJK cases should be tried in PH courts', 48, 'Senator Bam Aquino on Tuesday said cases against individuals implicated in alleged extrajudicial killings during the Duterte administration’s drug war should be tried in Philippine courts rather than before an international tribunal.\r\n\r\nAquino made the statement after the International Criminal Court Office of the Prosecutor identified Senators Bong Go and Ronald “Bato” dela Rosa as among the alleged co-perpetrators in the crimes against humanity case against former president Rodrigo Duterte.\r\n\r\nSpeaking in an interview on Unang Balita, Aquino said the Philippines must confront the killings that occurred and pursue justice locally, noting that the victims and their families are in the country.\r\n\r\n“The trials for these cases should ideally be held here in the Philippines because this is where the victims are,” Aquino said, adding that seeking justice where the alleged crimes happened would be more meaningful.\r\n\r\nPalace to Rodrigo Duterte\'s \'co-perpetrators\': Don’t hide if you’re innocent\r\nFormer Justice chief Aguirre denies involvement in Duterte’s drug war\r\nICC: No confirmation yet on Dela Rosa warrant\r\nDespite this, Aquino said he respects the ongoing process at the ICC, which is based in The Hague.\r\n\r\nHe added that senators are expected to discuss the matter involving Go and dela Rosa in a caucus, but emphasized the need to wait for the court’s formal actions before drawing conclusions.\r\n\r\nThe confirmation of charges in Duterte’s case is scheduled to begin on February 23, with subsequent hearings set for February 24, 26, and 27.', 1, 13, '2026-02-18 06:28:36', '2026-02-18 06:57:43', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69955c141fabe8.71249341.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(97, 69, 'Cantada lifts Lady Bulldogs past Lady Falcons', 56, 'MANILA, Philippines — In a battle of young volleyball rising stars, Sam Cantada reigned supreme for the National University Lady Bulldogs.\r\n\r\nCantada carried the load for the three-peat-seeking Lady Bulldogs side as they swept the Shaina Nitura-led Adamson Lady Falcons, 25-23, 25-19, 28-26, in their UAAP Season 88 women’s volleyball clash Wednesday at the UST Quadricentennial Pavilion in Manila.\r\n\r\nThe 18-year-old former Juniors Most Valuable Player finished with 16 points on 13 attacks, two aces and a block. She also had nine excellent receptions against her former high school teammate Nitura. Arah Panique chipped in 13 markers on nine attacks and four blocks.\r\n\r\n“Yes po [natagtag ko na ang pressure.] Mas kumpiyansa na rin po ako lalo na sa crucial game po, mas nalalaban ko po siya. Nawawala po yung bigat sa dibdib ko,” Cantada told reporters after the match.\r\n\r\nThe two teams were kept in a tight third set, with neither gaining significant advantage.\r\n\r\nA Frances Mordi attack tied things up at 23-all.\r\n\r\nA Princess Dote block on Cantada pushed the Lady Falcons ahead, 24-23, before a checkball by the young NU star tied things up anew.\r\n\r\nNitura then gave Adamson the set point, 25-24, but it was quickly taken back by a service error by Dote.\r\n\r\nPanique and Nitura traded late attacks, before the Adamson star’s save went out, giving NU a 27-26 lead.\r\n\r\nAlexa Mata then iced the match with a service ace to help the Lady Bulldogs stamp their second win in an hour and 31 minutes. \r\n\r\nThe reigning UAAP MVP Nitura produced 18 points for Adamson, all from attacks. Frances Mordi backstopped with 17. \r\n\r\nFacing off against her former juniors team, Cantada said that she made sure to just focus on what’s in front of her.\r\n\r\n“Game is game na po. Like past na yun, tapos na po yun, and alam ko po ngayon okay na rin sila doon and okay na rin ako dito.” \r\n\r\nNU is now holding a 2-0 win-loss record in the season. \r\n\r\nAdamson dropped to 1-1.\r\n\r\nThe Lady Bulldogs will try to keep it going as they take on the Far Eastern University Lady Tamaraws, while the Lady Falcons will seek to return to its winning ways against University of the East Lady Warriors. Both games are on Saturday at the Mall of Asia Arena.', 1, 13, '2026-02-18 06:34:38', '2026-02-18 06:57:39', 3, 1, 'developing', 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69955d7e2b8392.21981673.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(98, NULL, 'New Fossil Shows Dinosaurs Were More Unique Than We Thought', 95, 'For over 200 years, scientists have studied plant-eating dinosaurs known as Iguanodontians, a group famous for their beaked mouths and strong back legs. Now, a team led by France’s CNRS has uncovered something completely unexpected in China: a new species called Haolong dongi. What makes this fossil so extraordinary isn’t just the nearly complete skeleton—it’s the skin. Thanks to rare preservation and advanced imaging tools, researchers were able to examine skin cells that are about 125 million years old, an almost unheard-of level of detail in dinosaur fossils.  Even more surprising, this dinosaur’s body was covered in hollow spikes made from skin, not bone—something never before seen in any dinosaur. Scientists believe these unusual spines may have helped protect it from predators, much like a porcupine’s quills, but they might also have played a role in controlling body temperature or sensing the environment. The discovery, published in Nature Ecology & Evolution, suggests dinosaurs were even more diverse and inventive in their body designs than we once imagined.\n\n---\nAuthor: Shelwin Buenaventura\nSource: MBC Chat\nPublished: February 18, 2026\n', 1, 8, '2026-02-18 07:29:31', '2026-02-19 03:43:41', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/chat_media/2026/02/thumb_69956a5bf01d4.jpg', NULL, 'mbc_chat', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(101, NULL, 'TNT Welcomes Towering Talent: Bol Bol\'s PBA Debut', 56, 'Towering basketball sensation Bol Bol has arrived in the Philippines to join TNT Tropang 5G for their championship pursuit in the PBA 50th Season Commissioner\'s Cup. The 7-foot-3 NBA veteran, who previously played for the Denver Nuggets, Orlando Magic, and Phoenix Suns, was greeted at Ninoy Aquino International Airport by team manager Jojo Lastimosa. As the son of legendary NBA player Manute Bol, who was known for being 7-foot-6, the 26-year-old American-South Sudanese athlete is expected to be one of the most high-profile imports in PBA history, bringing significant anticipation and excitement to the league.', 1, 5, '2026-02-19 01:07:02', '2026-02-19 03:43:36', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69966236962b12.61652336.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(102, NULL, 'AsteroidOS 2.0: A New Era for Open Smartwatches', 54, 'AsteroidOS has officially unveiled its 2.0 release, marking a significant milestone for those invested in open-source smartwatch technology. This new version seeks to provide a robust and appealing platform for users while simultaneously offering developers a valuable opportunity to innovate and engage with the community. Built on a Linux foundation, AsteroidOS stands as a free alternative to proprietary operating systems like Google’s Wear OS and Apple’s watchOS, promoting user autonomy and privacy through its community-driven approach.\r\n\r\nThe latest update introduces a suite of enhancements designed to elevate the user experience. Notable features include an always-on display, tilt-to-wake functionality, and palm-to-sleep capabilities. Additionally, users will find new apps, such as a heart rate monitor, a compass, and a step counter, alongside a fun game called Diamonds. The complete redesign of the QuickSettings menu, now dubbed the QuickPanel, allows for greater customization and improved usability. Other significant improvements include a Nightstand mode for bedside use, enhanced app designs, and system performance upgrades that ensure smoother animations and longer battery life. AsteroidOS 2.0 also broadens its compatibility, supporting 15 new smartwatch models, thus expanding accessibility for users worldwide.', 1, 5, '2026-02-19 01:46:11', '2026-02-19 03:43:32', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69966b63e502c1.36810032.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(103, NULL, 'Metrobank Soars: Record P49.7-B Profit Marks a Landmark Year', 49, 'MANILA, Philippines – Metropolitan Bank & Trust Co. (Metrobank) has achieved a historic financial milestone, announcing a net profit of P49.7 billion for the fiscal year ending 2025. This record profit not only reflects the bank\'s operational excellence but also underscores its resilience amidst a dynamic economic landscape, confirming its stature as a leading player in the Philippine banking sector.\r\n\r\nThe impressive profit figure marks a significant leap from previous earnings, showcasing a robust growth trajectory that has been fueled by a strategic focus on enhancing net interest income and diversifying revenue streams. The bank\'s management credited this achievement to a mix of effective asset quality management, disciplined lending practices, and an expanded range of non-interest income sources.\r\n\r\nIn an official statement, Metrobank highlighted that net interest income continued to be a primary driver of profitability, benefiting from an increase in loan demand and a favorable interest rate environment. The bank reported strong performance across various lending segments, including corporate and consumer loans, which contributed significantly to the overall growth.\r\n\r\nMoreover, Metrobank\'s efforts to diversify its income sources have paid off, with non-interest revenues—comprising fees from transactions, investment banking activities, and wealth management services—seeing substantial growth. This diversification strategy has not only bolstered the bank’s earnings but also provided a buffer against market volatility.\r\n\r\n\"The outstanding results are a testament to our commitment to maintaining a strong balance sheet, ensuring asset quality, and providing exceptional service to our clients,\" said Metrobank President Fabian S. Dee during a press briefing. \"We remain focused on our strategic initiatives that prioritize sustainable growth and innovation in our service offerings.\"\r\n\r\nThe bank\'s prudent approach to risk management has also been a crucial factor in achieving this record profit. By maintaining a high level of asset quality, Metrobank has effectively minimized non-performing loans, further enhancing its financial stability. This proactive stance has allowed the bank to navigate potential challenges in the economic environment, including fluctuations in interest rates and external market pressures.\r\n\r\nInvestors and stakeholders have reacted positively to the announcement, with Metrobank’s stock price reflecting increased confidence in the bank’s future performance. Analysts believe the bank\'s solid financial results will likely attract more investments, further cementing its position in the competitive banking landscape.\r\n\r\nLooking ahead, Metrobank aims to continue its growth momentum by leveraging digital transformation initiatives and expanding its reach within underserved segments of the market. The bank has committed to investing in technology and infrastructure to enhance customer experience and streamline operations.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, Metrobank\'s record P49.7 billion profit in 2025 highlights its financial resilience and strategic acumen. As the bank continues to adapt to changing market conditions, its strong performance serves as a beacon of stability and growth in the Philippine banking industry. With a firm foundation and an eye towards innovation, Metrobank is poised for continued success in the years to come.', 1, 10, '2026-02-19 01:52:50', '2026-02-19 03:43:28', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69966cf2b2e843.12174412.webp', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(104, NULL, 'Finding the Right AI: Choosing the Safest Option for You', 54, 'In the rapidly evolving landscape of artificial intelligence, concerns about safety, ethics, and privacy have become paramount. With a plethora of AI tools available, users often find themselves asking: what’s the ‘safest’ AI to use? While there isn’t a one-size-fits-all answer, understanding the characteristics of safer AI options can guide individuals and businesses in making informed choices.\r\n\r\nSafety in AI encompasses various dimensions, including data privacy, algorithmic bias, transparency, and user control. Users should consider these factors when evaluating AI tools for their specific needs. Here, we explore some of the key features that contribute to an AI\'s safety credentials.\r\n\r\nOne of the primary indicators of a safe AI system is transparency. Users should look for AI tools that openly communicate how they operate, what data they use, and the decision-making processes involved. Companies like OpenAI and Google research emphasize transparency, sharing their methodologies and findings with the public. A transparent AI system allows users to understand potential biases and limitations, fostering trust and accountability.\r\n\r\nIn an age where data breaches are commonplace, prioritizing AI systems that prioritize user privacy is essential. Safe AI platforms implement strict data protection measures, such as encryption and anonymization. Tools that allow users to retain control over their data, giving them the option to opt in or out, are generally safer choices. For instance, many reputable AI services provide clear privacy policies outlining how user data is collected, used, and stored.\r\n\r\nAlgorithmic bias is a significant concern in AI, as biased data can lead to unfair and discriminatory outcomes. Safer AI systems actively work to identify and mitigate biases in their algorithms. Companies that conduct regular audits and updates to their AI models demonstrate a commitment to fairness. Look for platforms that offer explanations for their AI-driven decisions, as this can help users understand and challenge potential biases.\r\n\r\nThe safest AI tools empower users with control over how the technology operates. This includes providing options for customization, allowing users to tailor the AI to their specific needs and preferences. AI systems that allow users to adjust settings, such as the level of interaction or the scope of data used, promote a safer and more personalized experience.\r\n\r\nBefore adopting an AI tool, consulting expert reviews and user feedback can provide valuable insights into its safety. Engaging with communities that focus on AI ethics, such as AI ethics forums or tech-related subreddits, can help users discover which tools are deemed safe by experts and peers alike. Platforms that foster positive user experiences and have a track record of addressing concerns are often more reliable.\r\n\r\nAs artificial intelligence becomes increasingly integrated into our daily lives, selecting the safest AI tools is crucial for protecting both personal and organizational interests. By prioritizing transparency, data privacy, bias mitigation, user control, and community feedback, users can navigate the AI landscape with confidence. Remember that while no AI can be entirely free of risks, informed choices can significantly enhance safety and reliability in your AI interactions. Stay engaged, stay informed, and choose wisely as you explore the myriad of AI options available today.', 1, 10, '2026-02-19 01:59:17', '2026-02-19 03:43:25', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_69966e75140332.34237233.jpg', NULL, 'manual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
(105, NULL, 'SAICT Official Dismissed Following Controversial Edsa Busway Incident', 47, 'In a move that underscores the importance of accountability in public service, a senior official from the Department of Information and Communications Technology\'s (DICT) Support for the Advancement of Information and Communications Technology (SAICT) program has been dismissed following an incident that occurred on the Edsa Busway. The decision, announced recently, has sparked a wave of discussions regarding the governance and operational protocols of public transportation systems.\r\n\r\nThe Edsa Busway, a vital transportation route in Metro Manila, has become a focal point for commuters seeking efficient and reliable transit options. However, the incident involving the SAICT official has raised serious concerns about the management and oversight of this critical infrastructure. Reports indicate that the official was involved in actions that compromised the safety and efficiency of the busway operations, leading to significant disruptions for thousands of daily commuters.\r\n\r\nEyewitness accounts detail a chaotic scene where the official\'s interference not only delayed bus operations but also created a potential safety hazard for both passengers and drivers. Such actions are particularly alarming in a city where traffic congestion is already a pressing issue. Commuters expressed frustration over the incident, highlighting the need for stricter adherence to protocols by officials tasked with overseeing public transport.\r\n\r\nThe dismissal of the SAICT official serves as a reminder of the ramifications of mismanagement in public service roles. As the government aims to modernize transportation systems and improve the quality of life for its citizens, incidents like these illustrate the necessity for accountability at every level. It is essential that officials uphold the standards expected of them, particularly in transportation sectors where the stakes are high.\r\n\r\nIn response to the incident, the DICT has reiterated its commitment to ensuring that all personnel adhere to established guidelines and protocols. The department is currently reviewing its training procedures to better equip officials with the necessary skills and knowledge to manage public transportation systems effectively. This includes enhancing awareness of the impact their actions can have on the daily lives of commuters.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the incident has prompted calls from various sectors for a more transparent and accountable governance framework within the transportation system. Advocacy groups have emphasized the importance of citizen engagement in monitoring public officials, urging the public to voice concerns and report any misconduct. Such community involvement can help create a culture of accountability and responsibility among government personnel.\r\n\r\nAs the Edsa Busway continues to serve as a lifeline for many commuters in Metro Manila, the focus must remain on ensuring its smooth operation. The recent dismissal of the SAICT official should act as a catalyst for broader discussions about the management of public transport in the Philippines. The hope is that this incident will lead to improvements in oversight, training, and ultimately, the commuter experience.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, the Edsa Busway incident has not only led to the dismissal of a public official but has also highlighted the critical importance of accountability in public service. As Metro Manila continues to grapple with transportation challenges, it is crucial for officials to prioritize the safety, efficiency, and reliability of the systems they oversee. The path forward must involve collective efforts from both the government and the community to ensure a better, more efficient public transportation future for all.', 1, 10, '2026-02-19 02:08:47', '2026-02-23 05:43:55', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699670af7afb28.26841740.jpg', NULL, 'manual', 'Opisyal kan SAICT Tinanggal Kasunod kan Kontrobersyal na Insidente sa Edsa Busway', 'Sa sarong hakbang na nagpapahiling kan kahalagahan kan accountability sa serbisyo publiko, sarong senior na opisyal hale sa Department of Information and Communications Technology\'s (DICT) Support for the Advancement of Information and Communications Technology (SAICT) program an tinanggal kasunod kan insidente na nangyari sa Edsa Busway. An desisyon, na inanunsyo kamakailan, nagdara nin dakulang diskusyon manungod sa pamamahala asin mga operational protocols kan mga sistema nin pampublikong transportasyon.\r\n\r\nAn Edsa Busway, sarong mahalagang ruta nin transportasyon sa Metro Manila, nagin sentro para sa mga komyuter na naghahanap nin epektibo asin mapagkakatiwalaang transit options. Alagad, an insidente na kinasangkutan kan opisyal kan SAICT nagtaas nin seryosong mga alalahanin manungod sa pamamahala asin oversight kan ini na kritikal na imprastruktura. An mga report nagpapahiling na an opisyal nagin parte sa mga aksyon na nagkompromiso sa seguridad asin epektibidad kan operasyon kan busway, na nagdara nin dakulang abala para sa libo-libong komyuter kada aldaw.\r\n\r\nAn mga saksi nagdetalye nin kaotikan na eksena kun sain an pakikialam kan opisyal dai sana nagpauruli sa operasyon kan mga bus kundi nagdara pa nin potensyal na peligro sa seguridad para sa mga pasahero asin mga driver. An mga aksyon na ini partikular na nakakaalarma sa sarong ciudad kun sain an trapiko sarong dakulang isyu na. An mga komyuter nagpaheling nin pagkadismaya sa insidente, na nagpapahiling kan pangangaipo para sa mas istriktong pagsunod sa mga protocol kan mga opisyal na may responsibilidad sa pamamahala kan pampublikong transportasyon.\r\n\r\nAn pagtanggal kan opisyal kan SAICT nagseserbing paheling kan mga epekto kan mismanagement sa mga papel sa serbisyo publiko. Habang an gobyerno naglalayong i-modernize an mga sistema nin transportasyon asin pagbutihin an kalidad nin buhay para sa mga sibilyan, an mga insidente na arog kaini nagpapahiling kan pangangaipo para sa accountability sa kada level. Mahalagang an mga opisyal magtaas kan mga standard na inaasahan sainda, partikular na sa mga sektor nin transportasyon kun sain dakula an mga nakataya.\r\n\r\nBilang pagtugon sa insidente, an DICT nag-ulit kan saindang commitment na siguraduhon na an gabos na personnel mag-adher sa mga established guidelines asin protocols. An departamento kasalukuyang nire-review an saindang mga training procedures para mas ma-equip an mga opisyal nin mga kailangang skills asin kaaraman para sa epektibong pamamahala kan mga sistema nin pampublikong transportasyon. Ini naglalakip nin pagpapataas nin awareness manungod sa epekto kan saindang mga aksyon sa aldaw-aldaw na buhay kan mga komyuter.\r\n\r\nHulita, an insidente nagdara nin mga panawagan hale sa iba-ibang sektor para sa mas transparent asin accountable na governance framework sa laog kan sistema nin transportasyon. An mga advocacy groups nag-emphasize kan kahalagahan kan citizen engagement sa pag-monitor kan mga opisyal publiko, na nag-aaghat sa publiko na ipahayag an mga alalahanin asin i-report an ano man na misconduct. An arog na community involvement makakatabang sa pagbuo nin kultura nin accountability asin responsibilidad sa mga personnel kan gobyerno.\r\n\r\nHabang an Edsa Busway padagos na nagseserbing lifeline para sa dakul na komyuter sa Metro Manila, an focus dapat magpundo sa pagsigurado kan smooth operation kaini. An kamakailan na pagtanggal kan opisyal kan SAICT dapat magin katalista para sa mas halangkaw na diskusyon manungod sa pamamahala kan pampublikong transportasyon sa Pilipinas. An paglaom na an insidente na ini magdara nin pagbuti sa oversight, training, asin sa katapusan, an experience kan mga komyuter.\r\n\r\nSa konklusyon, an insidente sa Edsa Busway dai sana nagdara sa pagtanggal nin sarong opisyal publiko kundi nagpaheling man kan kritikal na kahalagahan kan accountability sa serbisyo publiko. Habang an Metro Manila padagos na nag-aagom sa mga hamon sa transportasyon, mahalaga para sa mga opisyal na i-prioritize an seguridad, epektibidad, asin reliability kan mga sistema na saindang pinapamahalaan. An dalan pasiring sa mas marhay dapat maglakip nin kolektibong mga pagsisikap hale sa gobyerno asin komunidad para masigurado an mas marhay, mas epektibong pampublikong transportasyon sa masunod na panahon para sa gabos.', 'Bicolano', '2026-02-23 13:43:55', 1),
(106, NULL, 'Alex Eala ousts Cirstea, sets up quarterfinal duel vs Coco Gauff', NULL, 'MANILA, Philippines–Alex Eala took down higher-ranked Sorana Cirstea of Romania, 7-5, 6-4, early Thursday (Manila time) to book her spot in the quarterfinals of the Dubai Tennis Championships.\r\n\r\nEala put on another impressive showing in the nightcap at Center Court, racing to a 5-1 lead in the second set before sealing her second quarterfinal appearance of the Middle East swing in front of another big Filipino crowd.\r\n\r\n“Every round is such a battle and so filled with tension. So I’m really happy with how I performed,” Eala said in the post-match interview.\r\n\r\n“I think the key to today was staying calm and trusting my shots. I think I was very solid in particular moments where I needed to be. So that reflected in my performance and in the score.”\r\n\r\nThe Filipino tennis ace avenged a three-set loss to Cirstea at the 2024 Mutua Madrid Open.\r\n\r\nThis time, Eala kept Cirstea from finding her rhythm, especially in the first set when the World No. 32 took a 5-4 lead.\r\n\r\nEala responded by rattling off three straight games and carried the momentum into the second set with four consecutive games for a 4-0 lead.\r\n\r\nCirstea, who is retiring from tennis after the 2026 season, pulled within 5-4, but Eala held at love in the 10th game to end the match.\r\n\r\nEala, who 24 hours earlier eliminated No. 8 Jasmine Paolini, will face two-time Grand Slam champion Coco Gauff in the quarterfinals later on Thursday.\r\n\r\n“I think I’m in a good path. I think if I continue like this, the next match will be great,” Eala said. “Coco [Gauff] is such an amazing person. We tend to forget that she’s just a year older than me. But she’s a great role model for so many.”\r\n\r\nGauff outlasted Elise Mertens, 2-6, 7-6(9), 6-3, shortly before Eala’s round-of-16 match, securing her entry into the next round.', 1, 12, '2026-02-19 03:41:21', '2026-02-19 09:24:25', 3, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'uploads/thumb_699686617794d6.10482183.png', NULL, 'manual', 'Alex Eala pepalual Cirstea, makipagtagumpe king quarterfinal laban kang Coco Gauff', 'MANILA, Philippines–Alex Eala pepalual ing mas matas a ranggong Sorana Cirstea ning Romania, 7-5, 6-4, king abak ning Huwebes (oras ning Manila) ban makasulud king quarterfinals ning Dubai Tennis Championships.\r\n\r\nEala meging makabighani king kayang pamaglaro king Center Court, a pigumpisan ing 5-1 a pamanguna king kadwang set bayu na isara ing kayang kadwang quarterfinal a pamagpakit king Middle East swing king harap ning maragul a Filipino a talapanalbe.\r\n\r\n“Balang round metung yang laban ampong punung-punu ya king tensiyon. Kaybat masaya ku king pamangakit ku king sarili ku,” sabi nang Eala king post-match a interbyu.\r\n\r\n“Ing susi king pamagtagumpe ngeni ya ing pamagpakalma ampong pamagtiwala king shots ku. Akakit ku king metung kung masalese king partikular a oras nung nu ka kailangan. Iya ing meging refleksyon king pamaglaro ku ampong king score.”\r\n\r\nIng Filipino tennis ace meging matagumpe laban kang Cirstea king metung a three-set a pamagkaluguran king 2024 Mutua Madrid Open.\r\n\r\nNgeni, Eala pepigilan na ing pamagkamal ning ritmo nang Cirstea, lalu na king mumunang set nung nu ing World No. 32 miguna king 5-4.\r\n\r\nEala meging matagumpe king pamagbalik ning tatlung sunud-sunud a games ampong meging momentum king kadwang set king apat a sunud-sunud a games para king 4-0 a pamanguna.\r\n\r\nCirstea, a magretiro king tennis kaibat ning 2026 a season, meging malapit king 5-4, dapot Eala meging matagumpe king pamaghold king love king 10th game ban tapusin ing laban.\r\n\r\nEala, a 24 oras bayu na pepalual ing No. 8 Jasmine Paolini, makipagtagumpe kang Coco Gauff, metung a two-time Grand Slam champion, king quarterfinals king Huwebes.\r\n\r\n“Akakit ku king masanting ing dalan ku. Akakit ku nung ituloy ku ini, masanting ing sunud kung laban,” sabi nang Eala. “Coco [Gauff] metung yang makabighani a tao. Madalas tamung kalimutan na metung yang banua lang mas matwa kesa kanaku. Dapot metung yang dakilang modelo para king dakal.”\r\n\r\nGauff meging matagumpe laban kang Elise Mertens, 2-6, 7-6(9), 6-3, bayu ning laban nang Eala king round-of-16, ban makasulud king sunud a round.', 'Kapampangan', '2026-02-19 17:24:25', 1),
