(76, 8, NULL, 'Gasoline prices primed to jump by up to P1.60/liter at the pump', 'MANILA, Philippines — Fuel price hikes are expected to persist next week amid geopolitical tensions and robust demand. Diesel is poised for an eighth week of an uptrend. \r\n\r\nIn an advisory Friday, Jetti Petroleum president Leo Bellas said the local prices of diesel products may increase again by 50 centavos to 70 centavos per liter. \r\n\r\nGasoline prices are seen to jump higher by P1.40 to P1.60 a liter. If implemented on Feb. 17, it would mark the sixth consecutive week of price hikes for gasoline. \r\n\r\n“Oil prices have remained elevated and volatile this week as the threat of US-Iran conflict remains. Iran-related Western sanctions and tariff threats on countries buying Iranian goods have added to the price volatility,” Bellas said. \r\n\r\nBy: Lisbet K. Esmael - Reporter / @lisbetesmaelPhilippine Daily Inquirer / 08:46 AM February 13, 2026', 49, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698eb192527825.66120391.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 05:30:23', '2026-02-18 05:55:10', '2026-02-13 13:30:23', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, '2026-02-19 11:54:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(77, 9, NULL, 'God of War Franchise Expands with Trilogy Remake and Prequel Spinoff', 'Santa Monica Studio has announced two major additions to the God of War franchise, commemorating the series\' 20th anniversary. The studio will release a comprehensive remake of the original Greek mythology trilogy and a new 2D action platformer titled \"God of War: Sons of Sparta.\"\r\n\r\nThe remake of the original trilogy, featuring the iconic protagonist Kratos, is currently in early development stages. Simultaneously, \"Sons of Sparta\" offers fans a deep dive into Kratos\' youth, chronicling his brutal training at the Agoge alongside his brother Deimos. The side-scrolling game features hand-drawn pixel animation and introduces players to Kratos\' formative years through kinetic combat mechanics. Original voice actor TC Carson returns to narrate the game, bringing authenticity to Kratos\' origin story. The game explores themes of duty and brotherhood, allowing players to experience Kratos mastering combat skills with a spear and shield while discovering divine artifacts. Both projects represent significant expansions of the beloved action-adventure franchise, promising to engage long-time fans and potentially attract new players to Kratos\' epic saga.', 92, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eb1e7b56903.68560753.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 05:32:43', '2026-02-13 05:32:43', '2026-02-13 13:32:43', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(78, 17, NULL, 'Strategic Rice Importation Group Formed to Protect Farmers and Consumers', 'Agriculture Secretary Francisco P. Tiu Laurel Jr. has announced the establishment of a technical working group (TWG) focused on rice importation, aiming to implement a more analytical and strategic framework for managing supply, pricing, and farmer protection as the country prepares for the upcoming rice cycle. This initiative comes as the Department of Agriculture (DA) accelerates efforts to finalize import policies for May while laying the foundation for a more structured import system later in the year.\r\n\r\nIn a recent meeting with industry stakeholders, Tiu Laurel emphasized the urgency of the situation and the need for swift action. He instructed the TWG, which includes representatives from key agricultural organizations, to convene weekly and provide policy recommendations within a short timeframe. The TWG will prioritize evidence-based decision-making, moving away from ad hoc approvals to a more systematic approach based on regional shortages and stock levels. This new strategy aims to ensure that imported rice reaches the market in a timely manner to stabilize prices while safeguarding local farmers’ interests. The DA also plans to implement stricter reporting requirements for rice stock data, warning that non-compliance could result in the loss of import eligibility. Ultimately, the TWG seeks to transition rice policy from reactive measures to a proactive system that supports both market stability and local production.', 59, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eb92ac16d33.73864163.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:00:07', '2026-02-13 06:00:07', '2026-02-13 14:00:07', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79, 20, NULL, 'Saber Interactive and Lionsgate Unveil Highly Anticipated John Wick', 'Saber Interactive and Lionsgate are developing a highly anticipated John Wick video game that promises to deliver an authentic experience of the iconic action franchise. The AAA single-player game, designed for mature audiences, will be available on PlayStation 5, Xbox Series X, and PC, with Keanu Reeves and franchise director Chad Stahelski directly involved in the project. The untitled game will feature an original narrative set in the John Wick timeline, exploring the character\'s backstory years before his infamous \"Impossible Task\" and introducing both familiar and new characters within the High Table universe.\r\n\r\nThe game aims to capture the distinctive \"gun-fu\" fighting style that has become synonymous with the film series, leveraging Saber Interactive\'s expertise in creating immersive gaming experiences. Jenefer Brown, President of Global Products & Experiences at Lionsgate, expressed excitement about allowing fans to step into John Wick\'s world, while Saber Interactive\'s CEO Matthew Karch described the project as an honor, recognizing the character\'s significance in action film history. Although specific release dates remain undisclosed, the collaboration between the game developers and film creators suggests a commitment to delivering a truly authentic John Wick gaming experience.', 92, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ebdaca91290.59667464.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:01:06', '2026-02-13 06:01:06', '2026-02-13 14:01:06', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(80, 19, NULL, 'DTI Expands Partner Supply Chain and Logistics Network to Support MSME Exports', 'The Department of Trade and Industry (DTI) has taken a significant step to support micro, small, and medium enterprises (MSMEs) in the Philippines. The agency has expanded its roster of partner supply chain and logistics firms under a program aimed at helping MSMEs manage shipping costs. The DTI\'s Supply Chain and Logistics Center (SCLC) is a network designed to lower logistics expenses for MSMEs by offering discounted rates through accredited partners.\r\n\r\nTrade Secretary Cristina Roque emphasized the growing importance of logistics support, especially as Philippine exports reached a record high of $84.41 billion last year. The new partners that have joined the SCLC include domestic and international shipping lines, as well as express delivery firms such as J&T Express Philippines Inc., Shopee Xpress Philippines Inc., JRS Express, GO21 Inc., Toyota Motor Philippines, and Victory Liner Inc. This expansion of the partner network is expected to provide MSMEs with more options and better pricing when it comes to shipping their products to the global market.', 49, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ebc8f546450.39742698.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:01:56', '2026-02-13 06:01:56', '2026-02-13 14:01:56', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(81, 18, 78, 'DA Ramps Up P20 Rice Program in Metro Manila, Targets Vulnerable Sectors Amid Harvest Season', 'The Department of Agriculture (DA) is significantly accelerating the expansion of its \"Benteng Bigas, Meron Na!\" program across the National Capital Region, marking a crucial step in the Marcos administration\'s drive to make affordable rice widely accessible, particularly to vulnerable populations. This flagship initiative offers quality rice at P20 per kilo, aiming to mitigate the financial strain of persistent food inflation on Filipino families. The expanded rollout will prioritize various disadvantaged groups, including senior citizens, solo parents, persons with disabilities, and minimum wage earners, with its strategic timing in March coinciding with the peak harvest season to leverage increased local palay production.\r\n\r\nThis extensive program serves a dual objective: it seeks to alleviate congestion in National Food Authority warehouses to accommodate fresh stocks while simultaneously addressing temporary supply shortfalls. To ensure seamless implementation, the DA, in collaboration with the Metropolitan Manila Development Authority (MMDA), recently convened a Technical Working Group with local government units (LGUs). Agriculture Secretary Francisco P. Tiu Laurel Jr. has outlined an ambitious goal of establishing at least five P20 rice outlets in every Metro Manila LGU, underscoring the government\'s commitment to bolstering food security and easing the economic burden on citizens. The DA’s Agribusiness and Marketing Assistance Service is overseeing the project, with MMDA pledging vital logistical support and monitoring LGU compliance to achieve widespread reach.', 59, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eba2e676933.36100042.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, '', 1, '2026-02-13 06:02:20', '2026-02-13 06:02:20', '2026-02-13 14:02:20', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(82, 16, NULL, 'Missing Student\'s Burned Body Found in Quezon, Authorities Confirm Identity', 'The police in Quezon, Nueva Vizcaya have confirmed that the burned female body found is highly likely that of the missing student reported in the area. According to PMaj. Santy Ventura, the chief of the Quezon Municipal Police Station, the victim\'s own father identified the body through her socks, shoes, and pants. However, to ensure the identity, the body is also undergoing DNA testing.\r\n\r\nThe student, a second-year Tourism Management student at a university in Bayombong, was last seen alive on Tuesday, February 10, when she was supposed to attend her class. However, her classmate and professor confirmed that she did not make it to school that day. The body was found on Thursday morning, February 12, by a married couple walking their pet dog. The police suspect that the body was dumped in the area and was likely burned in another location before being brought there. The investigation is ongoing, and the police are gathering evidence and witnesses to help speed up the process.', 47, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eb67003b0b4.12781436.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:02:23', '2026-02-13 06:02:23', '2026-02-13 14:02:23', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(83, 15, NULL, 'Barangay Councilman Suspected in Shooting of Woman in Lipa City, Batangas', 'A woman was shot at close range in Barangay Pag-Olingin West, Lipa City, Batangas. After being shot once, she managed to walk away, but the gunman followed and shot her again. The suspect, who was allegedly a barangay councilman, calmly left the scene on an e-bike parked nearby. Another CCTV footage shows the gunman arriving on a motorcycle before the shooting.\r\n\r\nPolice spoke to the drivers of the motorcycle and e-bike used by the suspect. They believe it may be a case of mistaken identity since the victim was not from the area and the suspect didn\'t know her personally.\r\n\r\nThe police found a .45 caliber gun at the crime scene. The investigation is still ongoing. The authorities are in talks with the victim\'s family to get more information and are conducting follow-up operations to locate the suspect.', 50, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eb578003110.19227677.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:02:26', '2026-02-13 06:02:26', '2026-02-13 14:02:26', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(84, 14, NULL, 'Filipino Student Secures Top Honor at U.S. Science Olympiad', 'CALAPAN CITY, Oriental Mindoro — A student from Calapan City brought pride to the Philippines after winning top honors at an international science competition in the United States, besting participants from 16 countries.\r\n\r\nWarren Wade Casuga, a native of Calapan City and a student at Holy Infant Academy, was named absolute winner (first place overall) in the Natural Science category at the Copernicus Olympiad held in Houston from January 21 to 25, 2026.\r\n\r\nHe also received a gold award, with the awarding ceremony conducted on January 26.\r\n\r\nThe Copernicus Olympiad is regarded as one of the most challenging and prestigious science competitions in the United States, drawing young science standouts from across the globe.\r\n\r\nCasuga outperformed competitors from the United States, Brazil, Vietnam, China, Taiwan, Azerbaijan, Bolivia, Indonesia, Jordan, Kazakhstan, Pakistan, Mexico, Mongolia, Peru, Romania, and Turkey.\r\n\r\nHis victory highlights the academic excellence and global competitiveness of Filipino students, particularly in the field of science. It also adds to the growing list of international achievements by young Filipinos.\r\n\r\nEducators and supporters said Casuga’s success reflects years of discipline, dedication, and strong academic preparation — serving as an inspiration to students nationwide who aspire to excel on the global stage.', 52, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698eb4b77e1733.68153163.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:02:29', '2026-02-13 06:02:29', '2026-02-13 14:02:29', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(85, 13, NULL, 'Maris Racal intrigues after ‘plot twist’ post with Cup of Joe’s Gian Bernardino', 'MANILA, Philippines – Filipino actress and singer Maris Racal has ignited widespread speculation across social media platforms following a recent Instagram post featuring Cup of Joe vocalist Gian Bernardino. The intriguing image, captioned simply \"plot twist,\" has left fans and netizens debating whether the unexpected pairing signals a new romantic development or an upcoming professional collaboration.\r\n\r\nThe buzz began days before Valentine’s Day, when Racal, known for her vibrant presence on social media, shared a photograph on her official Instagram page. The image depicted her holding a bouquet of flowers, while Bernardino sat beside her, leaning casually on her shoulder. Accompanying the \"plot twist\" caption was a white heart emoji, adding another layer of mystery to the post.\r\n\r\nThe Instagram update quickly became a trending topic, garnering significant attention from Racal\'s extensive following. As of this report, the post has accumulated over 534,000 likes, reflecting the high level of public interest in the nature of her relationship with the Cup of Joe frontman.\r\n\r\nFurther fueling the online conversation, Racal and Bernardino also appeared together in a TikTok video. The pair participated in the popular \"Big Guy\" trend, with Racal adding the caption \"love month\" to the clip. This particular TikTok post has achieved even greater reach, amassing more than 1.6 million views and approximately 140,000 likes, further intensifying discussions among fans about a potential romance.\r\n\r\nDespite the fervent speculation, both Maris Racal and Gian Bernardino have maintained silence on the matter. Neither artist has issued any official statement or comment to confirm or deny the burgeoning theories, leaving the public to continue dissecting their social media interactions for clues.\r\n\r\nMaris Racal\'s personal life has previously been a subject of public interest. She was notably in a relationship with fellow acclaimed singer Rico Blanco. Their eventual separation drew considerable media attention, particularly after Racal was linked to a cheating scandal involving her former love team partner, Anthony Jennings. This history adds another dimension to the current speculation surrounding her and Bernardino.\r\n\r\nGian Bernardino, on the other hand, is widely recognized as the lead vocalist of the popular P-pop band Cup of Joe. The band has cultivated a significant following with their distinctive sound and memorable tracks. Among their most recognized songs are \"Multo,\" \"Misteryoso,\" \"Estranghero,\" and \"Pahina,\" which have cemented their presence in the Philippine music scene.\r\n\r\nAs the \"love month\" continues and social media remains abuzz, the public eagerly awaits any clarification from Maris Racal or Gian Bernardino regarding their \"plot twist.\" Whether it heralds a new celebrity couple or an exciting musical project, the unexpected pairing has undoubtedly captured the attention of fans and the entertainment industry alike.', 55, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698eb401104b71.11187213.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:03:08', '2026-02-13 06:03:08', '2026-02-13 14:03:08', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(86, 12, NULL, 'Medieval Mystery Unveiled: Ritual Tunnel Found in Ancient German Tomb', 'In a remarkable discovery that bridges millennia, archaeologists in Germany have unearthed a mysterious subterranean tunnel system, or \"erdstall,\" dating to the Middle Ages, unexpectedly constructed within a Stone Age burial site. This intricate find, located near the village of Dornberg in Saxony-Anhalt, offers compelling new evidence suggesting that medieval communities may have utilized ancient, revered landscapes for clandestine ritual practices or as secret hiding places. The revelation comes from the German State Office for Heritage Management and Archaeology (LDA) of Saxony-Anhalt, following a routine survey conducted in late 2023 ahead of a planned construction project. The excavation initially focused on prehistoric layers, revealing a rich tapestry of human activity spanning thousands of years. Among the preliminary finds were a distinct trapezoidal ditch from the fourth millennium B.C., a testament to early Neolithic settlements, followed by several individual Neolithic burials dating to the third millennium B.C., indicating a long-standing use of the area as a sacred resting place. Further deepening the historical layers, archaeologists also uncovered a Bronze Age burial mound from the second millennium B.C., underscoring the site\'s enduring significance across various ancient cultures. It was amidst these layers of deeply embedded history that researchers encountered an anomaly: a long, oval pit, measuring approximately 6.5 feet (2 meters) in length and 2.5 feet (0.75 meters) in width, which intersected one of the Neolithic burial ditches at a precise right angle. Initially, the team considered the possibility that this pit represented another ancient grave, seamlessly integrated into the existing necropolis. However, as excavations progressed, the true nature of the feature became clear. The pit was not a standalone grave but rather the carefully concealed entrance to a much larger, complex subterranean network—an \"erdstall,\" a term translating from German as \"earth tunnel\" or \"shaft.\" This unexpected intrusion of medieval engineering into a prehistoric sacred space has prompted archaeologists to reconsider the dynamic interplay between different historical periods and how later societies perceived and interacted with the remnants of their distant ancestors, particularly those associated with burial and ritual. The Dornberg discovery instantly elevated the site from a significant prehistoric finding to a unique crossroads of archaeological inquiry, where the mysteries of the Stone Age now intertwine with the enigmatic practices of the Middle Ages, offering a rare glimpse into the continuity of human reverence, fear, and adaptation within ancient landscapes. The meticulous work of the LDA researchers in uncovering and interpreting these stratified layers of history is crucial to understanding how successive generations shaped, respected, and sometimes repurposed the hallowed grounds left by those who came before them.\r\n\r\nThe phenomenon of \"erdstalls\" itself represents one of the enduring enigmas of European archaeology, particularly prevalent across Bavaria and other regions of Central Europe where the geology provides firm yet workable soil suitable for such subterranean constructions. Hundreds of these mysterious earth tunnels have been documented, characterized by their often narrow, winding passages, small chamber-like extensions, and frequently challenging access. While their construction is broadly attributed to the Middle Ages, typically between the 8th and 13th centuries, their precise purpose has remained a subject of intense academic debate for decades. Unlike fortifications or dwellings, erdstalls rarely show signs of long-term habitation, leading archaeologists to speculate on a range of alternative functions. Theories have posited their use as temporary refuges during times of conflict or banditry, storage facilities for perishable goods, escape routes from surface structures, or even as early attempts at mining. However, the most compelling and frequently discussed theories revolve around spiritual or ritualistic purposes—spaces for cult practices, initiation rites, or as liminal zones connecting the earthly realm with the underworld. A primary challenge in deciphering the function of most erdstalls lies in their usual lack of artifacts; they are typically found empty, offering few material clues to their historical use. This absence of material culture has often forced archaeologists to rely on architectural features, geographical distribution, and historical folklore for interpretation. This context makes the Dornberg erdstall exceptionally significant. Unlike its many barren counterparts, the tunnel system in Dornberg yielded a small but potent collection of artifacts, providing crucial insights into the activities that once took place within its hidden depths. Among the finds were a metal horseshoe, a relic often associated with good luck or protection in medieval superstition; a complete fox skeleton, which could suggest an animal sacrifice, a natural occurrence, or symbolic deposition; fragments of a globe-shaped ceramic pot, possibly used for storing or transporting liquids or other materials; and a distinct layer of charcoal found within one of the narrow, curving passages, indicating that a fire, likely short-lived, had been lit inside. Furthermore, the entrance to this subterranean labyrinth had been deliberately sealed with large stones, suggesting a conscious effort to conceal its existence and the activities within. These material clues, though modest, distinguish the Dornberg find, offering tangible evidence that points strongly towards intentional human activity, possibly ritualistic in nature, within this secret space. The combination of the sealed entrance and the presence of specific artifacts transforms the Dornberg erdstall from a mere structural curiosity into a potential window into the hidden spiritual landscape of medieval life.\r\n\r\nThe strategic placement of the Dornberg erdstall, directly intersecting a Neolithic burial ditch, is perhaps its most profound and evocative characteristic, offering a powerful lens through which to understand medieval perceptions of ancient landscapes. LDA researchers have posited that the Stone Age trapezoidal ditch, likely a prominent feature on the landscape for centuries after its initial construction, would have remained visible and perhaps regarded as a sacred or significant space by the medieval individuals who painstakingly carved out the tunnel beneath it. This deliberate choice of location suggests more than just convenience; it implies a conscious interaction with the ancient past, potentially imbuing the medieval tunnel with an added layer of spiritual significance. In a period when Christianity was firmly established but older pagan beliefs and folk traditions still held sway, prehistoric burial sites were often viewed with a mixture of reverence, awe, and sometimes fear. Such sites, associated with ancestral spirits or non-Christian practices, might have been considered \"pagan graves\" by medieval locals, leading them to avoid the area for everyday activities, thereby making it an ideal, secluded location for secretive gatherings or rituals. The presence of artifacts like the fox skeleton and charcoal further fuels the hypothesis of ritual activity, possibly involving offerings, purification ceremonies, or other practices outside the mainstream religious norms of the time. The horseshoe, too, could have been a protective charm or an offering. This discovery challenges conventional narratives by demonstrating a complex relationship between medieval communities and their ancient heritage, where the remnants of the distant past were not merely ignored or built over, but actively engaged with and integrated into contemporary spiritual or practical landscapes. The Dornberg erdstall thus becomes a critical piece in the puzzle of understanding medieval folk beliefs, the persistence of pre-Christian spiritualities, and the ways in which people found meaning and utility in the ancient world around them. Future research will undoubtedly focus on further analysis of the artifacts, the tunnel\'s construction techniques, and comparative studies with other erdstalls to refine these interpretations. The Dornberg find not only enriches our understanding of the mysterious earth tunnels but also deepens our appreciation for the intricate, often hidden, connections between different epochs of human history, revealing how the echoes of the Stone Age continued to resonate, inspiring and influencing the lives and secret practices of people in the Middle Ages.', 95, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eb432e7bc54.88987131.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:03:12', '2026-02-13 06:03:12', '2026-02-13 14:03:12', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(87, 11, NULL, 'NBA fines Jazz, Pacers amid ‘tanking’ turmoil', 'The NBA took aim at “tanking” on Thursday, fining the Utah Jazz and Indiana Pacers over “management of their rosters” amid intensifying scrutiny on struggling teams thought to be focused on draft position rather than winning.\r\n\r\nThe Jazz were fined $500,000 for conduct detrimental to the league in games against the Orlando Magic on February 7 and the Miami Heat on February 9.\r\n\r\nUtah Jazz forward Lauri Markkanen brings the ball up the court against the Orlando Magic during the first half of an NBA basketball game, Saturday, Feb. 7, 2026, in Orlando, Florida.\r\nUtah Jazz forward Lauri Markkanen brings the ball up the court against the Orlando Magic during the first half of an NBA basketball game, Saturday, Feb. 7, 2026, in Orlando, Florida. (AP Photo/Phelan M. Ebenhack)\r\n\r\nThe NBA took aim at “tanking” on Thursday, fining the Utah Jazz and Indiana Pacers over “management of their rosters” amid intensifying scrutiny on struggling teams thought to be focused on draft position rather than winning.\r\n\r\nThe Jazz were fined $500,000 for conduct detrimental to the league in games against the Orlando Magic on February 7 and the Miami Heat on February 9.\r\n\r\n“During those games, the Jazz removed two of the team’s top players, Lauri Markkanen and Jaren Jackson, Jr., before the beginning of the fourth quarter and did not return them to the game, even though these players were otherwise able to continue to play and the outcomes of the games were thereafter in doubt,” the league said in a statement announcing the fines.\r\n\r\nThe Pacers were fined $100,000 for violating the player participation policy in connection with a February 3 game against the Jazz.\r\n\r\n“Following an investigation, including review by an independent physician, the NBA determined that Pascal Siakam, a star player under the policy, and two other Pacers starters, neither of whom participated in the game, could have played under the medical standard in the policy, including by playing reduced minutes,” the league said.\r\n\r\n“Alternatively, the team could have held the players out of other games in a way that would have better promoted compliance with the policy.”\r\n\r\nThe draft system means the teams that finish lowest in the standings have the best chances of landing the top prospects.\r\n\r\nUtah Jazz forward Lauri Markkanen brings the ball up the court against the Orlando Magic during the first half of an NBA basketball game, Saturday, Feb. 7, 2026, in Orlando, Florida.\r\nUtah Jazz forward Lauri Markkanen brings the ball up the court against the Orlando Magic during the first half of an NBA basketball game, Saturday, Feb. 7, 2026, in Orlando, Florida. (AP Photo/Phelan M. Ebenhack)\r\n\r\nThe NBA took aim at “tanking” on Thursday, fining the Utah Jazz and Indiana Pacers over “management of their rosters” amid intensifying scrutiny on struggling teams thought to be focused on draft position rather than winning.\r\n\r\nThe Jazz were fined $500,000 for conduct detrimental to the league in games against the Orlando Magic on February 7 and the Miami Heat on February 9.\r\n\r\n“During those games, the Jazz removed two of the team’s top players, Lauri Markkanen and Jaren Jackson, Jr., before the beginning of the fourth quarter and did not return them to the game, even though these players were otherwise able to continue to play and the outcomes of the games were thereafter in doubt,” the league said in a statement announcing the fines.\r\n\r\nThe Pacers were fined $100,000 for violating the player participation policy in connection with a February 3 game against the Jazz.\r\n\r\n“Following an investigation, including review by an independent physician, the NBA determined that Pascal Siakam, a star player under the policy, and two other Pacers starters, neither of whom participated in the game, could have played under the medical standard in the policy, including by playing reduced minutes,” the league said.\r\n\r\n“Alternatively, the team could have held the players out of other games in a way that would have better promoted compliance with the policy.”\r\n\r\nThe draft system means the teams that finish lowest in the standings have the best chances of landing the top prospects.\r\n\r\nBut it has long contributed to “tanking” — lowly teams throwing in the towel long before the regular season ends in hopes of landing a franchise-altering player in the draft.\r\n\r\nThe Jazz, 13th in the Western Conference and eight games out of the play-in, were up by three points going into the fourth quarter of their February 9 game against Miami and were dominating in the paint.\r\n\r\nArticle continues after this advertisement\r\nBut Jazz coach Will Hardy benched his top players — a similar move he’d made in their game against Orlando two days earlier.\r\n\r\n“Overt behavior like this that prioritizes draft position over winning undermines the foundation of NBA competition and we will respond accordingly to any further actions that compromise the integrity of our games,” NBA commissioner Adam Silver said in Thursday’s statement.\r\n\r\nAgence France-Presse / 11:33 AM February 13, 2026', 56, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698eb2f2362c53.19506716.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:03:16', '2026-02-13 06:03:16', '2026-02-13 14:03:16', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(88, 10, 76, 'Diesel prices rise further by P1 per liter, gasoline by 60 centavos', 'MANILA, Philippines — Local petroleum products will be costlier by up to P1 per liter beginning Tuesday, with diesel prices now on a seventh-week streak of hikes. \r\n\r\nIn an advisory Monday, Seaoil said the per-liter price of diesel will increase by P1\r\n\r\nGasoline and kerosene prices will also climb by 60 centavos a liter, marking their fifth and seventh consecutive week of upward price adjustments, respectively. \r\n\r\nJetti Petroleum president Leo Bellas earlier said the fresh round of oil price hikes were due to supply risks and continued geopolitical conflict.\r\n\r\n“Diesel price has found support from weather-related supply and demand issues, as well as the continued geopolitical tension in the Middle East that directly affects supply dynamics, at a time when Europe is moving away from Russian-origin supplies,” Bellas said.\r\n\r\nThe Department of Energy previously assured consumers that it was closely monitoring the local market to ensure that price adjustments remain fair and just. \r\n\r\nBy: Lisbet K. Esmael - Reporter / @lisbetesmaelPhilippine Daily Inquirer / 10:44 AM February 09, 2026', 49, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698eb215b0cc85.09123400.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, '', 1, '2026-02-13 06:03:44', '2026-02-13 06:03:44', '2026-02-13 14:03:44', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(89, 7, NULL, 'Samsung\'s Galaxy AI Revolution: Transforming Mobile Experience at Upcoming Unpacked Event', 'Samsung Electronics is set to redefine smartphone technology at its Galaxy Unpacked event on February 25, 2026, in San Francisco. The upcoming Galaxy S series promises an innovative AI-driven mobile experience designed to simplify daily interactions and provide seamless technological integration.\r\n\r\nThe live-streamed event, available on Samsung.com, Samsung Newsroom, and YouTube, will showcase the company\'s latest Galaxy innovations, emphasizing a new era of personalized and adaptive artificial intelligence.\r\n\r\nAttendees and potential buyers can benefit from multiple incentives, including:\r\n- $30 pre-order credit\r\n- Chance to win a $5,000 Samsung gift card\r\n- Up to $900 in trade-in savings\r\n- $150 credit for non-trade-in pre-orders\r\n\r\nInterested consumers can register at samsung.com/unpacked for exclusive updates, teasers, and event information. Additional reservation options will also be available through AT&T and Best Buy.\r\n\r\nThe event highlights Samsung\'s commitment to making AI technology more intuitive, accessible, and integrated into everyday life.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_698ea002994296.02139574.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:03:46', '2026-02-13 06:03:46', '2026-02-13 14:03:46', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(90, NULL, NULL, 'LeBron James becomes oldest player to have a triple-double in NBA', 'LOS ANGELES — LeBron James became the oldest player in National Basketball Association history to record a triple-double, accomplishing the feat for the Los Angeles Lakers on Thursday night against the Dallas Mavericks.\r\n\r\nJames had 28 points and 12 assists when he grabbed his 10th rebound with 2:06 remaining in the Lakers’ 124-104 victory. He received a standing ovation when he checked out moments later, completing his 123rd career triple-double — the fifth-most in NBA history.\r\n\r\nAt 41 years and 44 days old, James broke the record previously held by Karl Malone, who recorded a triple-double for the Lakers at 40 years and 127 days old.\r\n\r\nThe league’s all-time leading scorer had not recorded a triple-double since Feb. 1, 2025, in New York. That date is also remembered in Lakers history for the late-night trade that brought Luka Dončić to Los Angeles in a blockbuster deal involving Anthony Davis.\r\n\r\nMalone had set the previous record on Nov. 28, 2003, during his final NBA season, posting 10 points, 11 rebounds, and 10 assists. Since then, James has recorded the next 15 triple-doubles on the list of oldest players to achieve the milestone. He had come close multiple times over the past year before finally surpassing the mark in the Lakers’ final game before the All-Star break.\r\n\r\nJames dominated early, tallying 14 points and six assists in the first quarter. By halftime, he had 18 points, eight assists, and four rebounds. He reached double figures in assists during the third quarter and played the entire fourth quarter before securing his 10th rebound.\r\n\r\nJames was also selected for his 22nd All-Star appearance this weekend at the Intuit Dome, despite missing 18 games this season due to injury. Because of league rules, he is ineligible for selection to a 22nd All-NBA team this season.\r\n\r\nEntering the game, James was averaging 21.8 points, 6.9 assists, and 5.7 rebounds per contest. The Lakers remain firmly in the Western Conference playoff race despite playing only 10 games this season with James, Dončić, and Austin Reaves all healthy at the same time. James also missed the first 14 games of the season while recovering from sciatica.', 56, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ec5733227b1.34001958.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-13 06:32:40', '2026-02-13 06:32:40', '2026-02-13 14:32:40', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(91, 45, NULL, '\"Alien-Like\" Sea Slugs Discovered in UK Rock Pools: A Glimpse into Changing Marine Ecosystems', 'Marine researchers in southwest England have made an exciting discovery of non-native sea hares, specifically the Aplysia depilans species, during a Rock Pool Project event at Mount Batten Beach. These unusual sea slugs, which can grow up to 40cm long and weigh 380g, were initially mistaken for seaweed by a young participant and his father. Zak Russell, the project\'s leader, described the creatures as \"alien-like\" and noted that two specimens were found during the same session, potentially indicating a broader environmental shift.\r\n\r\nExperts from the Marine Biological Association suggest that warming waters and increased storm activity might be facilitating the arrival of these rare sea slugs on British shores. While the sighting is preliminary, marine conservation researchers like Loretta Kwok view such discoveries as opportunities to inspire wonder and enhance understanding of coastal ecosystems. Russell advised careful observation, recommending that anyone encountering sea slugs should use gloves and a large bucket to minimize potential harm while appreciating these fascinating marine organisms.', 95, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ee6358da5f3.90375822.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:09:13', '2026-02-15 10:09:13', '2026-02-15 18:09:13', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(92, 44, NULL, 'Senate Bill Seeks to Broaden Voting Accessibility for Vulnerable Sectors', 'A new legislative initiative in the Senate aims to significantly enhance the accessibility of polling places for vulnerable sectors, including persons with disabilities (PWDs), pregnant women, senior citizens, and indigenous peoples (IPs). Senate Bill No. 1698, filed by Senator Mark Villar and titled “An Act Enhancing Accessibility in the Voting of Senior Citizens, Persons with Disabilities, Pregnant Women, and Indigenous Peoples, Amending for the Purpose Republic Act No. 10366,” seeks to build upon existing legislation. Republic Act No. 10366, enacted in 2013, empowered the Commission on Elections (COMELEC) to establish accessible precincts specifically for PWDs and senior citizens. However, Senator Villar highlighted that despite this progress, substantial gaps persist, particularly for pregnant women and indigenous communities. Many individuals from these groups continue to encounter considerable obstacles, such as physical barriers at voting sites, difficulties with transportation, and geographic challenges in remote areas, which collectively undermine their fundamental right to participate fully in democratic processes. Villar emphasized that true democracy necessitates the hearing of every voice, asserting that current hurdles faced by these citizens are \"unnecessary.\"\r\n\r\nIf enacted, Senate Bill No. 1698 would mandate a more robust set of requirements for accessible polling places. The proposed measure stipulates that voting venues must be situated in locations easily reachable by public transportation and must be entirely free from physical impediments. Furthermore, it requires the provision of essential infrastructure and services tailored for vulnerable voters, including transport wheelchairs, ramps, railings, well-maintained sidewalks, adequate lighting, and proper ventilation. The bill\'s core objective is to empower the COMELEC to proactively designate and prepare polling places that prioritize inclusivity, thereby alleviating the physical and logistical burdens currently faced by these sectors on election day. By ensuring that no Filipino is disenfranchised due to accessibility issues, the legislation aims to uphold the principle of equal opportunity in electoral participation. The proposed measure has since been referred to the Senate Committee on Electoral Reforms and People Participation for detailed review and public hearings.', 46, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ee3ec46c1a1.60184322.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:09:19', '2026-02-15 10:09:19', '2026-02-15 18:09:19', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(93, 43, NULL, 'Resurgence of Japanese Swordsmithing Attracts New Generation Amidst Declining Craft', 'MISATO, Saitama, Japan — In the soot-covered studio of swordsmith Akihira Kawasaki, the rhythmic clang of an apprentice hammering red-hot steel resonates, highlighting a traditional craft experiencing a revival. The katana, a hallmark of Japanese craftsmanship, is captivating a new audience, particularly younger women, despite the dwindling number of blademakers in the country. This renewed interest is largely fueled by pop culture phenomena, including the popular video game “Touken Ranbu,” which anthropomorphizes swords as attractive characters, alongside other media such as the U.S. series “Shogun” and the anime “Demon Slayer.”\r\n\r\nKawasaki, 57, expressed his optimism about the growing enthusiasm among young people for swords. He noted a significant shift from the past, when sword enthusiasts were predominantly male and often dismissive of newcomers. \"It was no fun community,\" he remarked, highlighting a cultural barrier that new fans like 25-year-old Minori Takumi are breaking down. After discovering “Touken Ranbu” as a teenager, Takumi’s fascination with the game led her to explore real swords at museums, eventually becoming a curator at the Bizen Osafune Sword Museum. She credits the game for deepening her appreciation of the craft and sparking her passion for the katana\'s intricate details.\r\n\r\nDespite this cultural renaissance, the swordsmithing profession faces significant challenges, with the number of blademakers in Japan halving over the past 40 years to approximately 160, many of whom are elderly. Tetsuya Tsubouchi, head of the All Japan Swordsmith Association\'s business unit, noted that the demanding apprenticeship, lasting at least five years without pay, deters potential young recruits. Furthermore, prevailing attitudes within the industry favor ancient swords over newly crafted ones, making it difficult for contemporary swordsmiths like Kawasaki to thrive financially. While his pieces command high prices due to their artistry and craftsmanship, the broader market remains difficult, necessitating a shift in perception for modern katana to be recognized as contemporary art rather than mere antiques.', 57, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ee0f5bab050.21494974.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:09:37', '2026-02-15 10:09:37', '2026-02-15 18:09:37', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(94, 42, NULL, 'Palace Press Officer Critiques Vice President Duterte as \"Emotional Vulture\" Amid National Concerns', 'MANILA, Philippines — Claire Castro, the Press Officer for the Palace, has sharply criticized Vice President Sara Duterte, labeling her an \"emotional vulture\" for allegedly feigning concern for the nation while lacking concrete solutions to its pressing issues. Castro\'s remarks came in response to Duterte\'s recent comments expressing uncertainty about the future of the Philippines, questioning whether the country would still exist by the time of the 2028 national elections. Castro suggested that the vice president is overlooking the ongoing efforts of the Marcos administration to tackle these challenges, stating, \"It is saddening because this is a Duterte move, showing the characteristic of an emotional vulture — pretending to be concerned for the state of the nation when in fact she admitted that she doesn’t want to help the President in his projects.\"\r\n\r\nIn her statements, Castro issued a stark warning about the potential consequences of electing a \"Manchurian candidate\" in the next election cycle, implying that such a leader could compromise the nation\'s resources. While she refrained from directly naming Duterte, Castro referenced the vice president\'s previous interactions with Chinese officials and her reluctance to address issues surrounding the West Philippine Sea. Additionally, Castro accused Duterte of spreading misinformation about both her and the Marcos administration and recalled a disturbing comment made by Duterte regarding a hitman who could target key political figures, including President Bongbong Marcos. Concluding her remarks, Castro urged Duterte to \"spread love, not fake news, not immorality,\" signaling the escalating tensions within the current administration as the country approaches a critical electoral period.', 48, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698edfa2d9d198.65769201.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:16:50', '2026-02-15 10:16:50', '2026-02-15 18:16:50', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(95, 41, NULL, 'Cardinal Tagle Assumes Titular Diocese of Albano in Historic Ceremony', 'Cardinal Luis Antonio Tagle has formally taken possession of the Titular Diocese of Albano in a significant ceremony held at the Albano Cathedral in Italy. The event was well-attended by Filipinos, Tagle\'s family, and members of the Pontificio Collegio Filipino (PCF). As one of the seven historic sees surrounding Rome, the suburbicarian Diocese of Albano is traditionally assigned to high-ranking cardinals. Pope Leo XIV\'s decree, issued on May 24, appointed Tagle to this ecclesiastical office, praising his \"extraordinary intellectual gifts, sensibility, competence, wisdom, fidelity, and zealous industriousness\" in his role as Pro-Prefect of the Dicastery for Evangelization.\r\n\r\nThe ceremony held special significance, coinciding with the 64th anniversary of the Pontificio Collegio Filipino\'s inauguration. Originally established by Giuseppe Cardinal Pizzardo, the college-seminary was dedicated to Our Lady of Peace and Good Voyage, with the purpose of supporting young Filipino priests undergoing formation in Rome. Notably, the title was previously briefly assigned to Cardinal Robert Francis Prevost, who was elected pope on May 8 before he could take possession. Tagle, who was elevated to the rank of Cardinal-Bishop by the late Pope Francis in 2020, continues the traditional practice where cardinal bishops hold a titular diocese while the administrative leadership remains with the local ecclesiastical authorities.', 97, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698edc594612b6.31317226.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:17:40', '2026-02-15 10:17:40', '2026-02-15 18:17:40', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(96, 38, NULL, 'Kris Aquino Celebrates Milestone Birthday with Resilience and Hope', 'As Kris Aquino approaches her 55th birthday on Valentine\'s Day, the beloved media personality is reflecting on her health journey with remarkable optimism. In a recent Instagram post, Aquino shared her simple yet profound birthday wish: to live long enough to reach 60 and qualify for both a senior citizen and person with disability (PWD) card. Despite battling autoimmune diseases and undergoing a six-week hospital stay, she expressed gratitude for her progress, noting that she can now walk unaided and is rarely using her wheelchair.\r\n\r\nLooking ahead, Aquino plans to co-produce an on-camera podcast and is hopeful about rebuilding her immunity, which is currently compromised. She also touched on her son Bimby\'s emerging career, emphasizing that she prefers being a supportive mother rather than a \"mamager\" and has entrusted his career planning to someone she trusts. By openly sharing her medical challenges and future aspirations, Aquino continues to demonstrate her trademark transparency and resilience, inspiring her followers with her positive outlook and determination to overcome obstacles.', 55, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ed76c31b5b9.39041023.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:17:56', '2026-02-15 10:17:56', '2026-02-15 18:17:56', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
