(97, 37, NULL, 'The Importance of Human-like Movement in Prosthetic Limbs', 'As artificial intelligence-powered prosthetic arms become more common, understanding how people respond to them is crucial. Acceptance of these devices depends not only on their functionality but also on how natural they feel. Researchers used virtual reality to create the illusion that a participant\'s arm had been replaced with a robotic prosthetic, and then tested how different movement speeds influenced embodiment, including body ownership, sense of agency, usability, and social impressions.\r\n\r\nThe findings revealed a clear pattern: when the prosthetic arm moved too quickly or too slowly, participants felt less connected to it and rated it as less usable. However, when the arm moved at a moderate pace similar to natural human reaching, taking about one second to complete the motion, participants reported the strongest sense that the arm felt like part of their own body. This suggests that future AI-enabled prostheses should prioritize human-compatible timing rather than speed alone, as designers may need to tune movement patterns to align with what the brain expects from a natural limb.\r\n\r\nThe implications of this research extend beyond prosthetic arms. Other technologies that function as extensions of the body, including supernumerary robotic limbs, exoskeletons, and wearable robots, could also benefit from movement that mirrors natural human rhythm. Researchers also plan to explore how long-term use changes perception, as even a fast and highly capable robotic limb may start to feel more normal and easier to operate with continued daily use. Virtual reality allows scientists to test emerging prosthetic technologies and control systems in a safe and controlled setting, making it possible to evaluate psychological responses, user acceptance, and design considerations early in development.', 54, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ed591a93ab5.09931171.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:00', '2026-02-15 10:18:00', '2026-02-15 18:18:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(98, 36, NULL, 'Robin Padilla: ‘Kids are weak’ remark based on suicide data', 'MANILA, Philippines—When he called today’s kids “weak,” it was not just an opinion but a reality supported by studies and records, according to Sen. Robin Padilla.\r\n\r\nPadilla took to Facebook to explain his remark during Wednesday’s hearing of the Senate committee on public information and mass media on various measures regarding children’s safety on social media.\r\n\r\n“As the chairman of the Committee on Public Information and Mass Media, it is my mandate to be truthful to the people and not be plastic or pretentious in what I say, because that is the truth,” he explained in Filipino.\r\n\r\n“It’s the suicide data we studied in our office that show today’s youth are weak; it is not merely the result of our suggestion or opinion,” he added.\r\n\r\nAnd this was supported by studies from other progressive countries and data from the World Health Organization, according to him\r\n\r\nPadilla also cited a 2021 survey, which showed that nearly one in five (about 20%) Filipino youth aged 15 to 24 have thought about ending their lives.\r\n\r\nSuicide attempts among young people, meanwhile,  increased to 7.5% in 2021, a 150 percent increase from the 3% recorded in 2013, while approximately 46% of all recorded suicide cases since 2010 involve young people aged 10–35, the senator added.\r\n\r\n“So if you want to help address this issue concerning the youth, do something about it and stop talking about me. Act on the data, not on my statement,” he said.\r\n\r\n“Focus on what is happening to our youth, not on me,” he added.', 48, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ed66e3fc1d9.39182596.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:03', '2026-02-15 10:18:03', '2026-02-15 18:18:03', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(99, 34, NULL, 'PNP: LRT-1 has no contributory negligence in fall incident', 'The Philippine National Police (PNP) sees no liability on the part of the management of the Light Rail Transit Line 1 (LRT-1) in the fatal fall of a student from FPJ Station in Quezon City. “Magkakaroon lang po ng pananagutan ang LRT na kung may nakita silang contributory negligence sa parte po ng LRT,” PNP spokesperson Police Brigadier General Randulf Tuaño said at a press briefing. (The LRT will only be held accountable if the police find contributory negligence on the part of the LRT.) “Pero sa ngayon po, wala po silang nakikita na contributory negligence sa part po ng LRT,” he added. (But for now, they do not find any contributory negligence on the part of the LRT.) The Quezon City Police District (QCPD) conducted an investigation into the incident involving a male student who reportedly fell from FPJ Station around 10:30 a.m. on Wednesday. According to the QCPD, a CCTV footage provided by the LRT-1 management showed the victim walking back and forth around the area. He was also looking at the road. After a few minutes, the incident happened. A vehicle on the road also hit him after the fall. The driver was placed under police custody in accordance with the PNP’s standard operating procedures (SOP) as the incident involved a fatality. The driver was released after the father of the victim executed a notarized letter stating that he is not pursuing a complaint against the driver. —AOL, GMA Integrated News\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: GMA News\r\nSource: GMA News\r\nPublished: February 13, 2026', 98, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ecf9331f806.00018761.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:06', '2026-02-15 10:18:06', '2026-02-15 18:18:06', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100, 33, NULL, 'ByteDance’s new AI video model goes viral as China looks for second DeepSeek moment', 'Already have Rappler+? Sign in to listen to groundbreaking journalism. This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article. BYTEDANCE. The Bytedance logo is seen in this illustration taken February 8, 2025. BEIJING, China – ByteDance’s new video-generating artificial intelligence model has already impressed the likes of Elon Musk and gone viral in China, where it has been compared to DeepSeek and won praise for its ability to produce cinematic storylines with just a few prompts. While text-centric AI models such as OpenAI’s ChatGPT and DeepSeek’s R1 have become widely adopted, models specialized in generating videos and pictures represent the next frontier in the technology’s potential for disruption. ByteDance, which officially unveiled Seedance 2.0 on Thursday, February 12, said in a statement that the system was designed for professional film, e-commerce, and advertising productions, because it was capable of processing text, images, audio, and video simultaneously, lowering the cost of creating content. The product launch comes as China and investors around the world are on the lookout for a successor to Chinese startup DeepSeek’s R1 and V3 models whose global debut early in 2025 triggered a systemic shock. On Chinese social media, Seedance 2.0 drew comparisons to DeepSeek’s meteoric rise to fame. “Early last year, the release of DeepSeek-R1 sparked heated debate in the US tech community over a ‘Sputnik moment’,” Chinese state-backed newspaper Global Times wrote in an editorial on Wednesday. “This year, the continued breakout success of Seedance 2.0 and similar innovations has gone even further, giving rise to a wave of admiration for China within Silicon Valley.” The buzz generated by Seedance 2.0 was underscored when the world’s richest man Elon Musk replied to a post praising the model on his social media platform X by commenting, “It’s happening fast.” Users on China’s Weibo microblogging platform shared videos generated by the AI model that showcased the complexity and image quality of its output, no matter how bizarre the prompt. One two-minute video, which had been viewed around a million times on Weibo, depicted rapper and record producer Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, and reality TV star Kim Kardashian, as characters in a palace drama set in Imperial China, speaking and singing in Mandarin. Hashtags related to Seedance 2.0 have racked up tens of millions of clicks on Weibo, including one from state-owned newspaper Beijing Daily that read “from DeepSeek to Seedance, China’s AI has succeeded.” – Rappler.com\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Rappler\r\nSource: Rappler\r\nPublished: February 13, 2026', 98, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ecfe8967e23.71136099.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:09', '2026-02-15 10:18:09', '2026-02-15 18:18:09', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(101, 32, NULL, 'Senate panel eyes passing anti-political dynasty bill before March ends', 'Senator Risa Hontiveros said Friday that the Senate Committee on Electoral Reforms is planning to pass the bill seeking to prohibit political dynasties before March ends.  “It will be passed. Intensyon namin maipasa ito this session so bago matapos ang buwan ng Marso,” Hontiveros said during a joint committee meeting. (It will be passed. It is our intention to pass it this session, so before March ends.) Hontiveros, who chairs the electoral reforms panel, said she wants the anti-political dynasty law to cover up to the 4th degree of consanguinity. “Para sa akin ‘yun ang dapat, ‘yun ang ideal. Bilang isa sa mga authors sa Senate, ‘yun ang ipu-push ko. At the same time… I\'m working with six bills na iba-iba ang prescription. Fourth degree, third degree, second degree,” she said. (For me, that is what should be done, that is the ideal. As one of the authors in the Senate, that is what I will push. At the same time… I’m working on six bills with different prescriptions: fourth degree, third degree, second degree.) She said they will undergo a consensus building to reach a compromise. “Ang sa akin lang, whatever will be our final form, ‘yung tingin kong dapat or ideal na 4th degree or maaring sa mas marami sa colleagues ko, mas practical or mas reasonable at this point in time, 3rd degree or 2nd degree, basta ang importante sa akin, magkaroon kami ng batas na impactful, may kwenta,” she said. (For me, whatever will be our final form, what I think should be the ideal—4th degree—or for many of my colleagues, maybe more practical or more reasonable at this point in time, 3rd degree or 2nd degree, what’s important to me is that we have a law that is impactful and meaningful.) Hontiveros also said that the damage brought by a dynasty is known to the public. “Kung saan nangingibabaw ang konsentrasyon ng kapangyarihan sa ilang pamilya, madalas matatagpuan rin ang korapsyon, kahirapan, at kakulangan ng pananagutan o accountability,” she said. (Where the concentration of power in a few families prevails, corruption, poverty, and a lack of accountability are often also found.) “Sa halip ng serbisyong publiko sa ordinaryong Pilipino, personal na interes at pakinabang ang madalas na nagiging sentro. Nandito tayo ngayon para baguhin ito,” she added. (Instead of public service for ordinary Filipinos, personal interest and gain often become the focus. We are here now to change this.) Meanwhile, Bacolod City Mayor Greg Gasataya said he is in favor of starting the discussion and coming up with a clear framework on the prohibition of dynasties. There are currently six bills on political dynasties filed in the Senate. — RSJ, GMA Integrated News\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: GMA News\r\nSource: GMA News\r\nPublished: February 13, 2026', 98, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ed0880aa398.19924945.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:13', '2026-02-15 10:18:13', '2026-02-15 18:18:13', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102, 31, NULL, 'SWS: Cheating is common in PH, but so is forgiveness', 'Cheating is a prevalent issue in the Philippines, as highlighted by a recent Social Weather Stations (SWS) survey. According to the survey conducted from November 24 to 30, 2025, 27% of adult Filipinos have either witnessed or experienced cheating in relationships. The forms of cheating reported include physical cheating (engaging in sexual or intimate activities with someone else), emotional cheating (developing romantic feelings for another person or confiding in someone else about personal issues instead of one\'s partner), and cyber cheating (maintaining secret social media accounts or engaging in clandestine online conversations).\r\n\r\nDespite the prevalence of cheating, the survey also revealed a positive trend towards forgiveness and the restoration of trust. Approximately 43% of respondents expressed belief in the possibility of rebuilding trust after an incident of cheating. This statistic indicates a strong inclination towards reconciliation and working through relationship challenges in the Filipino community.\r\n\r\nThe data underscores the need for open communication, trust-building exercises, and possibly professional counseling to address issues of infidelity in relationships. By acknowledging the various forms of cheating and understanding the emotional impact it can have on individuals and relationships, steps can be taken to promote healthier connections and foster a culture of forgiveness and resilience.\r\n\r\nMoving forward, it is essential for individuals and couples to engage in honest conversations about boundaries, expectations, and values within their relationships. By promoting transparency, mutual respect, and a commitment to addressing challenges constructively, the incidence of cheating can be minimized, and trust can be nurtured and strengthened over time.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, the SWS survey sheds light on the complex dynamics of trust, forgiveness, and infidelity in Filipino relationships. By acknowledging the realities of cheating and embracing the possibility of rebuilding trust, individuals and couples can navigate relationship challenges with resilience and empathy, ultimately fostering stronger and more enduring connections.', 57, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ec8d7a47345.36703281.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:20', '2026-02-15 10:18:20', '2026-02-15 18:18:20', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103, 30, NULL, 'Clock ticking on amnesty for fake birth records, says NACC', 'MANILA, Philippines — The National Authority for Child Care (NACC) has urged individuals who faked the birth records of children under their care to avail themselves of the rectification process allowed under the law, warning that the amnesty provision will only be available until March 28, 2029.\r\n\r\nSpeaking at a media forum, Assistant Secretary Rowena Macalintal cited Republic Act No. 11222, saying those who fail to file a petition within the 10-year period from the law’s effectivity in 2019 may no longer be covered by the amnesty and could face criminal, civil and administrative liabilities under existing laws.\r\n\r\n“Kung kayo po ay mayroong under custody na bata, iniwan sa inyo o inialok sa inyo, tapos iniregister mo ang sarili mo bilang nanay ng batang ito, ito po ay may criminal offense,” Macalintal said Thursday at the Department of Social Welfare and Development (DSWD) Central Office New Press Center.\r\n\r\n(If you have a child under your custody — one who was left with you or offered to you — and you register yourself as the child’s mother, that is a criminal offense.)\r\n\r\nShe said it constitutes illegal adoption and simulation of a birth certificate under the Revised Penal Code and Republic Act No. 1164.\r\n\r\nMacalintal said simulating or faking birth records carries serious penalties.\r\n\r\n“May kulong po ito na 8 to 10 years imprisonment. Mayroon din pong civil liability at administrative liability kung kayo po ay government employee,” she said.\r\n\r\n(This carries a penalty of eight to 10 years of imprisonment. There is also civil liability and administrative liability if you are a government employee.)\r\n\r\nThe NACC is a quasi-judicial agency attached to the DSWD. \r\n\r\nIf the simulation happened before 2019 and the child has been raised as the petitioner’s own, she said the petitioner may avail of the benefits under the Simulated Birth Rectification Act.\r\n\r\nUnder Republic Act No. 11222, simulation of birth record is defined as tampering with the civil registry to make it appear that a child was born to a person who is not the child’s biological mother, resulting in the loss of the child’s true identity and status.\r\n\r\nRectification of fake records\r\nThe law, signed on Feb. 21, 2019, and effective March 29, 2019, allows the rectification of simulated birth records through an administrative adoption process rather than court proceedings.\r\n\r\nBefore its enactment, families who faked birth records had to undergo judicial adoption under Republic Act No. 8552, or the Domestic Adoption Act of 1998. \r\n\r\nThe process was often costly and time-consuming and exposed petitioners to possible prosecution for falsification of public documents and simulation of births under the Revised Penal Code.\r\n\r\nRepublic Act No. 11222 provides amnesty to those who simulated birth records before its effectivity, provided the act was done in the best interest of the child and that a petition for adoption with application for rectification is filed within 10 years from effectivity.\r\n\r\nUnder Section 4 of the law, those who qualify “shall not be criminally, civilly, or administratively liable” for the act of simulation once the rectification process is successfully completed.\r\n\r\nThe law does not apply to cases involving child trafficking, abuse, exploitation or other illicit purposes, which remain prosecutable under existing laws.\r\n\r\nWho may qualify\r\nUnder the law, the child must have been living with and treated as the petitioners’ own son or daughter and must have been in their custody for at least three years before the law’s effectivity in 2019.\r\n\r\nThe implementing rules and regulations state that the petition must be filed with the Social Welfare and Development Office of the city or municipality where the child resides, regardless of where the simulated birth was registered.\r\n\r\nDSWD guidelines issued through Memorandum Circular No. 16, series of 2020, state that the child’s best interests remain the paramount consideration in all proceedings. \r\n\r\nSocial workers are required to conduct a comprehensive social case study report, including home visits, interviews and background checks, to determine whether the adoption and rectification will redound to the welfare of the child.\r\n\r\nIf the child is 10 years old or older, written consent is required. Consent of legitimate and adopted children of the adopter who are 10 years old or older may also be required under the law and its implementing rules.\r\n\r\nHow the rectification works\r\nMacalintal said the rectification process begins with filing a petition with the local Social Welfare and Development Office, which evaluates the application and endorses it to the DSWD field office.\r\n\r\nThe field office prepares a social case study report and submits a recommendation to the regional director, who forwards it to the DSWD secretary for final decision. The secretary must decide on the petition within 30 days from receipt of the recommendation.\r\n\r\nIf approved, an order of adoption is issued canceling the simulated birth record, directing the registration of the rectified birth record or foundling certificate, and ordering the issuance of a new birth certificate.\r\n\r\nThe administrative adoption order has the same legal effect as a decree of adoption issued under the Domestic Adoption Act of 1998.\r\n\r\n“I-file lang po ninyo ang inyong mga petition sa mga local government units, sa ating mga LSWDO para mapetition for the rectification ng simulated birth certificate. Kapag naissue na po yung adoption decree, pwede niyo na pong mapa-amend ang birth certificate na kayo po talaga ang lehitimong magulang ng bata na inampon ninyo at wala po kayong penalty,” she said.\r\n\r\n(Just file your petitions with your local government units, with our Local Social Welfare and Development Offices, so you can apply for the rectification of the simulated birth certificate. Once the adoption decree is issued, you can have the birth certificate amended to reflect that you are the child’s legitimate parent, and you will not incur any penalty.)\r\n\r\nShe added that the amnesty also covers those who cooperated in the simulation.\r\n\r\n“Pati na rin po yung mga kakuntsabang nurse, midwife, doctor na kasama pong naki-connive doon sa birth certificate, pati sila ay makaka-avail ng amnesty na pino-provide ng batas natin only until 2029,” Macalintal said.\r\n\r\n(This also includes the nurses, midwives or doctors who connived in the execution of the birth certificate — they, too, may avail themselves of the amnesty provided by the law, but only until 2029.)\r\n\r\nThe implementing rules also provide for the confidentiality of all records and proceedings. Unauthorized disclosure may be penalized under relevant laws, including the Data Privacy Act.\r\n\r\nIf a petition is denied, the petitioner may file a motion for reconsideration within 15 days, as provided in the rules. Appeals follow existing administrative procedures.\r\n\r\nDeadline: March 28, 2029\r\nThe law provides a 10-year window from March 29, 2019, to March 28, 2029, for qualified individuals to avail themselves of rectification and amnesty.\r\n\r\nAfter that date, applications will no longer be entertained under Republic Act No. 11222, and petitioners may have to pursue regular judicial adoption proceedings without the benefit of statutory amnesty.\r\n\r\nMacalintal urged families to coordinate with authorities while the amnesty remains in effect.\r\n\r\n“Kung mayroon po kayong kamag-anak o kakilala na nag-simulate ng birth certificate from 2019 backwards, makipag-coordinate po kayo sa NACC through our Regional Child Care Offices o kaya sa inyong Local Social Welfare Development Officers sa inyong mga LGUs para po ma-process na po natin ang rectification at adoption,” she said.\r\n\r\n(If you have a relative or know someone who simulated a birth certificate prior to 2019, coordinate with the NACC through our Regional Child Care Offices or with your Local Social Welfare and Development Officers in your local government units so the rectification and adoption can be processed.)\r\n\r\nAppeal to mothers in crisis\r\nMacalintal also appealed to mothers who may be struggling to care for their children not to abandon them in unsafe places.\r\n\r\n“Kung hindi niyo na po kayang alagaan pa ang inyong anak, hindi po kailangang itapon o iwan sa kung saan-saan kasi ilalagay lang po natin sila sa peligro at kapahamakan,” she said.\r\n\r\n(If you can no longer care for your child, there is no need to abandon them in unsafe places, as that would put them in danger. \r\n\r\n“Meron po tayong 148 prospective adoptive parents na nasa roster po ng NACC, waiting, praying na makapag-ampon at maka-match sila sa babies. Isuko po natin sa mga residential care facilities ng DSWD o kaya sa mga child caring agencies, o di kaya po sa ating mga social workers, sa ating mga safe havens, sa ospital, sa simbahan,” Macalintal said.\r\n\r\n(We have 148 prospective adoptive parents in the NACC roster who are waiting to adopt and be matched with babies. They may be surrendered to DSWD residential care facilities, child-caring agencies, social workers, safe havens, hospitals or churches.)\r\n\r\nShe said mothers who properly surrender their children will not face abandonment charges and will instead receive assistance.\r\n\r\n“Puwede po nating dalhin ang ating mga bata doon at hindi po kayo huhulihin. Hindi po kayo kakasuhan ng abandonment. Kayo po ay tutulungan. Ang unang protocol po ay mabigyan po ng counseling at intervention ang nanay para sana hindi niya kailangang i-let go yung kanyang anak,” Macalintal said.\r\n\r\n(You may bring your children there and you will not be arrested. You will not be charged with abandonment. You will be helped. The first protocol is to provide the mother with counseling and intervention so that she may not have to give up her child.)', 46, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ec8323d6ae7.39015214.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:24', '2026-02-15 10:18:24', '2026-02-15 18:18:24', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(104, 29, NULL, 'Screen Burn-In: Comprehensive Guide to Fixing Display Discoloration on Devices', 'Screen Burn-In: Comprehensive Guide to Fixing Display Discoloration on Devices\r\n\r\nScreen burn-in remains a persistent issue for electronic devices, despite significant advancements in display technology. This frustrating problem can affect smartphones, TVs, and computer monitors, leaving behind ghost images that mar your viewing experience.\r\n\r\nUnderstanding Screen Burn-In Fixes for Different Devices\r\n\r\nSmartphone Solutions:\r\n1. Basic Troubleshooting\r\n- Restart your device\r\n- Play dynamic, colorful videos to help pixel recovery\r\n- Download burn-in fixer apps from Apple App Store or Google Play Store\r\n- Consider professional screen replacement if issues persist\r\n\r\nTV Burn-In Remedies:\r\n1. Immediate Adjustments\r\n- Reduce brightness and contrast settings\r\n- Use built-in Pixel Shift functions\r\n- Activate TV\'s refresh mechanisms\r\n- Play colorful, fast-moving content\r\n\r\n2. Advanced Solutions\r\n- Utilize screen shift technology\r\n- Alternate between vibrant channel displays\r\n- Consider professional repair or replacement if burn-in is severe\r\n\r\nComputer Monitor Strategies:\r\n1. Recovery Techniques\r\n- Power down screen for 48 hours\r\n- Use white/black screensaver alternation\r\n- Utilize online pixel fixing tools like jscreenfix.com\r\n\r\nPrevention Tips:\r\n- Avoid displaying static images for extended periods\r\n- Use screen savers\r\n- Reduce screen brightness\r\n- Rotate content regularly\r\n- Enable auto-sleep functions\r\n\r\nWhen to Seek Professional Help:\r\nIf DIY methods fail, consult manufacturer support or authorized repair centers. Persistent burn-in might indicate underlying screen damage requiring professional intervention.\r\n\r\nUnderstanding Burn-In:\r\nScreen burn-in occurs when static images remain visible after being displayed for prolonged periods. OLED and LED screens are particularly susceptible, with pixels becoming \"stuck\" in a specific configuration.\r\n\r\nKeyword-rich conclusion: Addressing screen burn-in requires a combination of preventative measures and targeted recovery techniques tailored to your specific device type.\r\n\r\nDisclaimer: Results may vary depending on screen technology and damage extent.', 54, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ec6ec833061.11108708.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:27', '2026-02-15 10:18:27', '2026-02-15 18:18:27', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105, 28, NULL, 'Rafael Montero signing minor league contract with Yankees to add pitching depth', 'Pitcher Rafael Montero is headed to The Bronx. \r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Christian Arnold\r\nSource: Post\r\nPublished: February 13, 2026', 97, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_69919b2097aad9.26874745.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:30', '2026-02-15 10:18:30', '2026-02-15 18:18:30', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106, 27, NULL, 'LeBron James becomes oldest player to have a triple-double in NBA', 'LOS ANGELES— LeBron James became the oldest player in NBA history to have a triple-double, accomplishing the feat for the Los Angeles Lakers on Thursday night against the Dallas Mavericks. James had 28 points and 12 assists when he grabbed his 10th rebound with 2:06 to play in the Lakers’ 124-104 victory. \r\n\r\nJames got a standing ovation when he checked out moments after grabbing his final rebound to complete his 123rd career triple-double, fifth-most in NBA history. At 41 years and 44 days old, James broke the record held by Karl Malone, who recorded a triple-double for the Lakers when he was 40 years and 127 days old. But the top scorer in NBA history hadn’t had a triple-double since last Feb. 1, 2025, in New York. \r\n\r\nThat day is better remembered in Lakers history for the late-night breaking news of the trade that brought Luka Doncic to the Lakers in a seismic trade for Anthony Davis. Malone had held the record as the oldest player with a triple-double since he had 10 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists on Nov. 28, 2003, during his final NBA season. James recorded the next 15 triple-doubles on that list, and he repeatedly came close to setting the record repeatedly over the past year, but didn’t quite reach it until the Lakers’ final game before the All-Star break. James put up 14 points and six assists in the first quarter alone, and he had 18 points, eight assists and four rebounds by halftime. \r\n\r\nHe topped double digits in assists during the third quarter, and he played the entire fourth quarter before grabbing the 10th rebound. James was selected for his 22nd All-Star appearance this weekend at Intuit Dome even though he has missed 18 games this season due to injury. That means James is ineligible for inclusion on his 22nd All-NBA team. \r\n\r\nJames entered this game averaging 21.8 points, 6.9 assists and 5.7 rebounds per game for the Lakers, who are in the thick of the Western Conference playoff race despite playing only 10 games with James, Doncic and Austin Reaves simultaneously healthy. James missed the first 14 games of the season while dealing with sciatica.', 56, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ec5ea3e3a60.56267498.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:34', '2026-02-15 10:18:34', '2026-02-15 18:18:34', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107, 25, NULL, 'NATO Launches Arctic Sentry: Strengthening Defense in the High North', 'NATO has initiated Arctic Sentry, a military effort focused on enhancing security in Greenland and the Arctic region. The mission follows previous diplomatic tensions and aims to counter Russian and Chinese influence in the strategically important High North.\r\n\r\nCurrently, Arctic Sentry encompasses existing national military exercises like Denmark\'s Arctic Endurance and Norway\'s Cold Response, without establishing permanent NATO troop deployments. The United Kingdom has committed to doubling its troops in Norway, while France and Germany have also expressed participation.\r\n\r\nU.S. Air Force Gen. Alexus Grynkewich emphasized the mission\'s goal of maintaining stability in this challenging geographical area. With seven NATO allies in the Arctic region, the initiative seeks to strengthen alliance cooperation and preparedness.\r\n\r\nThe broader context includes navigating past diplomatic complications and refocusing NATO\'s strategic priorities, particularly in light of ongoing tensions with Russia. Greenland, a semiautonomous Danish territory, remains a key focal point in these geopolitical considerations.\r\n\r\nNATO\'s ultimate objective remains defending its 32 member states\' territories while adapting to evolving global security challenges.', 48, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ec49691a179.84601111.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:41', '2026-02-15 10:18:41', '2026-02-15 18:18:41', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108, 24, NULL, 'Ash Emissions and Lava Flow Recorded at Mayon Volcano, Alert Level 3 Maintained', 'MANILA, Philippines — On Friday morning, the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) reported two instances of ash emissions from the summit crater of Mayon Volcano. The emissions were documented at 8:21 a.m. and 8:27 a.m., producing a grayish plume that ascended 50 meters above the crater before drifting to the west-southwest.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the ash emissions, Phivolcs provided an update in its 24-hour observation summary indicating ongoing lava effusion, with lava flowing down three distinct gullies: Basud, Bonga, and Mi-isi. The agency measured sulfur dioxide emissions at 3,749 tons per day as of February 10.\r\n\r\nPhivolcs has emphasized that Alert Level 3 remains in effect for Mayon Volcano. This alert level signifies an increased risk, leading to a prohibition on entry into the 6-kilometer permanent danger zone surrounding the volcano to ensure public safety.', 51, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ec276c80360.67077180.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:45', '2026-02-15 10:18:45', '2026-02-15 18:18:45', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(109, 23, NULL, 'Ifugao opens first HIV treatment hub', 'Ifugao has launched its first HIV Treatment Hub, named \"Balen di Pamhod\" (\"house of love\"), at the Panopdoapan District Hospital in Lamut. Certified by national health authorities, the hub will provide comprehensive HIV treatment and related services locally, reducing the need for patients to seek care outside the province. The facility aims to offer a safe, compassionate environment for clients and improve access to timely, patient-centered HIV services.\r\n\r\nAccording to provincial data, the Cordillera region has recorded 1,355 HIV cases from 1984 to June 2025, with 57 cases in Ifugao. The majority of transmissions (99.9%) occurred through sexual contact, predominantly affecting males aged 25-34. The Provincial Implementation Team is committed to achieving the 95-95-95 HIV treatment targets by 2030, with this new treatment hub representing a significant step toward that goal.', 53, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ec074a089d3.94874604.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:48', '2026-02-15 10:18:48', '2026-02-15 18:18:48', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(110, 22, NULL, 'TESTESTETSETS', 'STSESETSETSETST\n\n---\nAuthor: mjuancho91\nSource: MBC Chat\nPublished: February 13, 2026\n', 96, 1, 7, 'uploads/chat_media/2026/02/thumb_698ebfc60e6b2.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:51', '2026-02-15 10:18:51', '2026-02-15 18:18:51', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(111, 21, NULL, 'Enhancing Sleep Quality: An Overview of the soundcore Sleep A30 Earbuds', 'In today\'s fast-paced world, achieving restorative sleep has become an increasingly difficult task for many individuals due to a myriad of distractions and disturbances. soundcore, a prestigious audio brand under Anker Innovations and a leading player in the global wireless headphone market, has recognized this pressing need and has launched the soundcore Sleep A30 earbuds—its most advanced sleep-focused technology to date. Engineered for a diverse range of users, from those grappling with insomnia to side-sleepers seeking comfort, the soundcore Sleep A30 combines the dual capabilities of Active Noise Cancellation (ANC) and Passive Noise Cancellation (PNC) with innovative AI-driven soundscapes. This multifaceted approach not only aims to provide a tranquil environment conducive to falling asleep more quickly and staying asleep longer but also strives to ensure users awaken genuinely refreshed.\r\n\r\nThe soundcore Sleep A30 is distinguished by its Smart ANC technology, which delivers an impressive 30dB reduction in ambient noise specifically tailored for sleep settings. By adapting to the unique contours of the user\'s ear canal, this technology effectively neutralizes common sleep disruptors, such as the hum of household appliances or the noise of outdoor traffic. Furthermore, the earbuds are designed with a snug fit to ensure robust passive noise isolation, creating a personal sanctuary of silence conducive to deep rest. Among its standout features is the Adaptive Snore Masking Technology, which monitors snoring patterns and generates tailored masking audio to blend with the snore frequencies, allowing users to remain undisturbed throughout the night. Complementing these features is the AI Brainwave Audio, which uses binaural beats and soundscapes to facilitate relaxation and guide the mind into a calmer state, ultimately promoting deeper sleep. With a focus on comfort, the A30 is designed to accommodate side-sleepers and features an extended battery life, ensuring that users can rely on them for uninterrupted sleep nights after night.', 54, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698ebf4cc25836.34355114.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:54', '2026-02-15 10:18:54', '2026-02-15 18:18:54', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(112, 39, 98, 'Robin Padilla inalmahan ng psychologist sa talak tungkol sa depression', 'HINDI napigilang mag-react ng psychologist na si Riyan Portuguez sa naging pahayag ni Sen. Robin Padilla patungkol sa depresyon.\r\n\r\nSa kanyang “Your Millenial Psychologist” Facebook page, ibinahagi niya ang mga dahilan kung bakit hindi uso ang salitang depresyon noong panahon ng senador.\r\n\r\n“Noong panahon po kasi ninyo [Robin Padilla] maraming mga tao partikular na ang kabataan ang natatakot na magsabi dahil sa katulad po ninyo na kaysa maunawaan eh hinuhusgahan kaagad na ‘weak’ o mahina kapag may pinagdadaanan,” sabi ng psychologist\r\n\r\nPagpapatuloy pa niya, “Maraming katulad po ninyo noon ang nagtatago sa dilim para sarilinin lang ang problema at magkunwaring ‘okay lang.’ Paano mo makikita eh nagtatago nga?\r\n\r\nKaya naman pakiusap ni Riyan na sana ay huwag danasin ng sinumang miyembro ng pamilya ni Robin ang depression para lang maintindihan niyo ang ibig sabihin ng pagkakaroon ng ganitong karamdamang mental.\r\n\r\nAng depresyon ay isang clinical diagnosis na kinakailangang gamutin sa pamamagitan ng therapy at mga gamot. Makakatulong rin para malabanan ito sa pamamagitan ng pag-e-exercise, meditation, pagkakaroon ng iba pang libangan, pagdarasal, at mga suporta mula sa pamilya at malalapit na kaibigan.\r\n\r\nMatatandaang noong Miyerkules, February 11, sinabi ni Robin sa Senate Committe on Public Information and Mass Media na hindi uso ang depression.\r\n\r\n“Ang mga bata po ngayon, sad to say, you are weak.\r\n\r\nHindi kayo katulad noong panahon namin na hindi kami iyakin. Natuto kami sa kalsada. Natuto kami na huwag umupo at umiyak,” sey ni Robin.', 48, 1, 3, 'uploads/thumb_698ed857340fd5.35733551.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, 'developing', 1, '2026-02-15 10:18:59', '2026-02-15 10:18:59', '2026-02-15 18:18:59', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(113, 40, 98, 'Generational Divide: Kuya Kim Responds to Senator Padilla\'s Critique of Modern Youth', 'In a recent Facebook post, GMA Network\'s Kuya Kim Atienza offered a thoughtful response to Senator Robin Padilla\'s controversial statement about today\'s youth being \"weak\" during a Senate committee hearing. Padilla had reminisced about the 1980s and 1990s, claiming that children from his generation were happier because they played outside, implying that current youth are somehow less resilient. The senator suggested that topics like depression were not discussed in his time, seemingly dismissing the mental health challenges faced by younger generations.\r\n\r\nAtienza approached the topic with compassion, emphasizing the importance of understanding and supporting individuals struggling with mental health challenges. He highlighted the existence of 24/7 crisis hotlines as evidence of the ongoing need for mental health support, regardless of generational perspectives. His response advocated for kindness and empathy, noting that while generational experiences may differ, the fundamental need for support remains constant. By addressing Padilla\'s comments with nuance and sensitivity, Atienza demonstrated a more inclusive approach to understanding the complex experiences of younger generations in an increasingly digital and challenging world.', 98, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_698eda3cdfed32.89317484.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, 'developing', 2, '2026-02-15 10:19:02', '2026-02-15 10:19:02', '2026-02-15 18:19:02', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114, 51, NULL, 'Mongolian National Arrested for Alleged Espionage Activities in Zambales', 'MANILA, Philippines — In a shocking turn of events, a Mongolian national has been apprehended in Zambales, Philippines, in connection with alleged espionage activities. The Bureau of Immigration (BI) confirmed the arrest, raising concerns over foreign individuals engaging in intelligence-gathering operations within the country.\r\n\r\nOn October 20, 2023, the BI reported the capture of a 33-year-old Mongolian man identified only by his surname, Baatar. The arrest took place in the coastal town of San Antonio, Zambales, during an operation led by the BI\'s intelligence division. Authorities acted on a tip-off regarding Baatar’s suspicious activities, which allegedly involved gathering sensitive information potentially harmful to national security.\r\n\r\nAccording to BI Commissioner Norman Tansingco, the operation was a collaborative effort with the Philippine National Police (PNP) and the military, highlighting the growing vigilance of local authorities against espionage. Tansingco emphasized that the Philippines will not tolerate any foreign nationals engaging in activities that threaten the sovereignty and safety of the nation.\r\n\r\nWhile details surrounding the specific nature of Baatar\'s espionage activities remain scarce, reports suggest that he was surveilling military installations and other strategic locations in the vicinity. This alarming revelation has prompted discussions about national security and the potential risks posed by foreign nationals who may be involved in intelligence work for their home countries.\r\n\r\nThe BI has not disclosed whether Baatar had any accomplices or if he was part of a larger network operating within the country. However, the incident has raised questions about how foreign nationals are monitored and regulated in the Philippines, especially given the country’s strategic geopolitical position in Southeast Asia.\r\n\r\nThe arrest of Baatar is a crucial reminder of the need for heightened awareness regarding foreign activities within the Philippines. National security experts have voiced their concerns about the increasing number of foreign nationals involved in espionage and surveillance operations, particularly in regions close to military bases and critical infrastructure.\r\n\r\nAs the Philippines continues to strengthen its international partnerships and alliances, especially in the face of rising tensions in the Asia-Pacific region, the government must remain vigilant in safeguarding its national interests. This includes implementing stricter regulations on foreign workers and tourists, particularly those from countries known for engaging in espionage.\r\n\r\nIn response to this incident, the Philippine government is likely to review its policies on immigration and the monitoring of foreign nationals. Increased cooperation with international intelligence agencies may also be considered to combat the threat of espionage more effectively.\r\n\r\nThe BI has indicated that Baatar will face charges related to his espionage activities, and the investigation is ongoing to determine the full extent of his operations. Authorities are urging the public to report any suspicious behavior by foreign nationals, highlighting the critical role that community vigilance plays in national security.\r\n\r\nThe arrest of the Mongolian national in Zambales serves as a stark reminder of the ever-present threats to national security posed by espionage. As the Philippines navigates complex international relationships, it is imperative for the government to bolster its defenses against foreign intelligence activities. Public awareness and cooperation will be essential in ensuring the safety and sovereignty of the nation in this increasingly interconnected world.', 46, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699289a286a076.36308613.gif', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-16 03:13:53', '2026-02-16 03:13:53', '2026-02-16 11:13:53', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(115, 50, NULL, '28 Lives Lost: Army Exposes Violent Tactics of Communist Rebels in Negros Island', 'The Philippine Army\'s 3rd Infantry Division (3ID) has reported a disturbing pattern of violence on Negros Island, revealing that at least 28 people have been killed since March 2025 by alleged communist terrorist group (CTG) remnants. In a recent statement, the division highlighted the brutal murder of 74-year-old Leonora Anguit, who was shot outside her home in Kabankalan City on February 3rd. The Armando Sumayang Jr. Command of the New People\'s Army claimed responsibility for her killing, alleging she was a military informant linked to a previous encounter where seven of their members were killed during a government operation.\r\n\r\nThe military emphasized that these victims are not combatants but ordinary citizens, including farmers and elderly residents, whose only \"crime\" was choosing peace over violence. According to 3ID, an average of two people have been killed monthly, with incidents designed to intimidate communities and disrupt local cooperation with authorities. The division has called on the Commission on Human Rights and other organizations to conduct independent investigations, stressing that these killings represent a systematic attack on civilian safety. While acknowledging the ongoing threat, military officials remain confident that local residents will continue supporting peace and security efforts in the region.', 47, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_6992882169c9f7.88221542.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-16 03:13:57', '2026-02-16 03:13:57', '2026-02-16 11:13:57', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(116, 49, NULL, 'Warming Oceans Spell Disaster for Vital Coral Reef Ecosystems', 'Coral reefs, often referred to as the bustling cities of the underwater world, are crucial ecosystems that occupy less than one percent of the ocean floor yet support an incredible 25 percent of all marine species. Unfortunately, these essential habitats are under threat from a worsening crisis characterized by widespread coral bleaching, primarily driven by rising ocean temperatures. A recent study published in *Nature Communications* reveals a bleak outlook, noting that the \"Third Global Bleaching Event\" has resulted in the most extensive damage on record, while a \"Fourth Global Bleaching Event\" is currently manifesting with alarming intensity.\r\n\r\nSean Connolly, a senior scientist with the Panama-based Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, emphasized the unprecedented scale of destruction from the Third Bleaching Event, marking it as the most severe and widespread incident documented to date. This alarming trend indicates a dire future for coral populations, which are now grappling with consecutive catastrophic events. The study, conducted by the U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration\'s (NOAA) Coral Reef Watch program, examined an extensive dataset of over 15,000 global reef surveys collected between June 2014 and May 2017. The findings were stark, revealing that approximately 80 percent of the surveyed reefs suffered moderate to severe loss of color and essential nutrients, with over 10 percent of individual corals directly impacted. Alarmingly, 35 percent of these corals were found to be either dying or already dead. By utilizing advanced satellite heat-stress data, researchers were able to project the global extent of this devastation, indicating that 51 percent of coral reefs worldwide are now at risk.', 59, 1, 5, 'uploads/thumb_699285af717ca0.02098744.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-16 03:14:00', '2026-02-16 03:14:00', '2026-02-16 11:14:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
