(176, 109, NULL, 'Zuckerberg Confronts Allegations of Youth Mental Health Harm in Landmark Trial', 'In a high-stakes trial addressing youth social media addiction, Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg defended his platforms against allegations of deliberately targeting young users. The lawsuit centers on a California woman who claims Instagram and YouTube negatively impacted her mental health during childhood, arguing that these platforms intentionally designed features to hook young users despite knowing potential psychological risks.\r\n\r\nZuckerberg faced intense questioning from lawyer Mark Lanier, who presented internal Meta documents suggesting strategic plans to attract younger users. When confronted with a 2018 Instagram presentation stating \"If we want to win big with teens, we must bring them in as tweens,\" Zuckerberg argued that the statement was being mischaracterized. He maintained that while Meta discussed creating child-friendly platform versions, they ultimately did not implement such services. Furthermore, Zuckerberg suggested that age verification is complex and suggested device manufacturers should bear more responsibility for protecting young users.\r\n\r\nThe trial represents a broader legal challenge against social media companies, with thousands of cases alleging these platforms contribute to a youth mental health crisis. Previous investigations have revealed internal research showing Meta\'s awareness of potential psychological harm, including findings that some teens reported Instagram negatively impacting their body image. While Meta and Google deny these allegations and point to user safety features, the lawsuit could potentially challenge Big Tech\'s legal protections against user harm claims. Notably, competitors Snap and TikTok have already settled with the plaintiff, adding weight to the ongoing scrutiny of social media\'s impact on young users.', 54, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_6996a4d28a7c41.29820976.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-20 07:19:41', '2026-02-20 07:19:41', '2026-02-20 15:19:41', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
