 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(178, 131, NULL, 'Engineered Algae: A Revolutionary Solution to Microplastics Pollution', 'University Researcher Pioneers Innovative Algae-Based Technology to Remove Microplastics from Water\r\n\r\nProfessor Susie Dai of the University of Missouri has developed a groundbreaking genetic engineering technique to create a new strain of algae that can effectively remove microplastics from wastewater. This innovative solution holds the potential to tackle the growing problem of microplastics pollution in the Philippines and beyond.\r\n\r\nMicroplastics, defined as plastic particles less than 5 millimeters in size, have become a pervasive environmental concern, with studies detecting their presence in air, water, and even the human food chain. These tiny plastic fragments can disrupt hormones, leading to potential reproductive issues, metabolic disorders, and respiratory problems.\r\n\r\nThe Philippines, as the world\'s top source of plastic waste in the oceans, faces a particularly severe microplastics pollution challenge. Studies on Laguna Lake have revealed widespread contamination, with particles from single-use plastics and disposable masks entering human bodies through ingestion and inhalation.\r\n\r\nProfessor Dai\'s research aims to address this problem head-on. By genetically engineering a new strain of algae, she has created a water-repellent organism that can effectively capture and remove microplastics from wastewater. The key lies in the algae\'s production of a natural oil called limonene, which attracts the water-repellent microplastics, causing them to clump together and sink to the bottom for easy collection and removal.\r\n\r\nThe specially engineered algae can thrive in wastewater, feeding on excess nutrients and cleaning the water as it grows. This innovative approach tackles multiple issues simultaneously: removing microplastics, cleaning wastewater, and potentially repurposing the collected microplastics into bioplastic products.\r\n\r\nDai envisions integrating this new algae-based process into existing wastewater treatment plants, enabling cities to clean their water more effectively and reduce pollution while creating useful products. The research, published in the journal Nature Communications, is still in the early stages, but Dai is working to scale up the technology and make it more widely applicable.\r\n\r\nBy harnessing the power of genetic engineering and the natural properties of algae, Professor Dai\'s groundbreaking work offers a promising solution to the growing microplastics crisis. As the Philippines and the world grapple with the environmental and health impacts of these pervasive pollutants, this innovative algae-based technology could pave the way for a cleaner and more sustainable future.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bcce77108a5.65004455.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 03:51:46', '2026-02-23 03:51:46', '2026-02-23 11:51:46', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(179, 129, NULL, 'Navigating the Evolving AI Startup Landscape: Challenges for Wrappers and Aggregators', 'The AI startup ecosystem is rapidly evolving, and according to a recent warning from a Google executive, two popular types of AI startups could be in trouble - wrappers and aggregators.\r\n\r\nDarren Mowry, who heads Google\'s global startup organization, told TechCrunch that companies built around large language model (LLM) wrappers and AI aggregators may be facing headwinds. Wrappers are startups that take existing LLMs like ChatGPT and build a product or consumer-facing layer on top, while aggregators pull multiple LLMs into a single interface or API.\r\n\r\nMowry\'s assessment is that the market is growing wary of these types of startups. For wrappers, he argues that simply \"white-labeling\" an underlying model without adding significant differentiation is no longer enough. \"If you\'re really just counting on the back-end model to do all the work and you\'re almost white-labeling that model, the industry doesn\'t have a lot of patience for that anymore,\" Mowry said. \r\n\r\nHe emphasizes that startups need to build \"deep, wide moats\" through either horizontal differentiation or vertical market specialization to stand out. Mere wrappers are unlikely to progress and grow in the current environment.\r\n\r\nAI aggregators face their own challenges. While many have found success in giving users access to multiple models through a unified interface, Mowry believes they too need to add more \"intellectual property\" to steer users to the right model at the right time. Users, he says, want to see AI startups build something proprietary into the experience.\r\n\r\nThese warnings come as the broader AI landscape continues to evolve rapidly. A recent PYMNTS report examines how agentic AI is reconfiguring the B2B product experience. In this new paradigm, the digital shelf is no longer just about merchandising - it\'s a complex data engineering challenge, especially for online marketplaces.\r\n\r\nAgentic commerce, where AI drives procurement decisions, collapses the traditional separation between sourcing, contracting, and settlement. Factors like payment terms, credit availability, and settlement speed now become critical inputs to purchasing algorithms. \r\n\r\nAs a result, PYMNTS argues that \"if aggregation defined the first generation of B2B marketplaces and workflow defined the second, payments and data structure are emerging as the connective tissue of the landscape\'s agentic-driven third act.\"\r\n\r\nThe clear message is that the AI startup world is evolving rapidly, and simple wrappers or aggregators may no longer be enough. Startups need to build deep, differentiated intellectual property and integrate seamlessly with the new agentic commerce landscape. Those that can\'t may find themselves facing an ominous \"check engine\" light, as Mowry warned.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bc2adb60af1.48443736.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 03:51:50', '2026-02-23 03:51:50', '2026-02-23 11:51:50', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(180, 127, NULL, 'Meta Shifts Focus to Mobile-First Metaverse Strategy', 'When Facebook rebranded to Meta in 2021, it signaled the company\'s strong belief in the future of virtual reality (VR) technology. A key part of this vision was Horizon Worlds, which Meta envisioned as the primary way people would communicate in the metaverse.\r\n\r\nHowever, it appears that the VR fad may be fading, and Meta is now pivoting to a mobile-first approach for its metaverse ambitions. In a recent interview, Samantha Ryan, Meta\'s VP of Content at Reality Labs, revealed that Horizon Worlds is shifting gears to become \"almost exclusively mobile.\"\r\n\r\nAs part of this change, Meta is splitting Horizon Worlds and the Quest VR platform into two separate products. On the Quest or VR side, the focus will be on supporting third-party developers and content, rather than first-party worlds. In fact, individual Horizon Worlds destinations are being pulled from the VR store, and the Worlds section is disappearing from the Quest home screen.\r\n\r\nOn the Horizon side, the focus is almost entirely shifting to mobile. According to Meta, in 2025, the number of mobile-only Horizon Worlds grew from zero to 2,000, and the number of monthly users increased more than four times. To support this mobile-first strategy, Meta is introducing and expanding the availability of new tools, such as the Meta Horizon Studio and the Meta Horizon Engine, to help create more engaging mobile worlds. Additionally, Meta is introducing new monetization tools, like featured bundles and season passes.\r\n\r\nThis shift in strategy raises questions about Meta\'s ability to compete with established players in the mobile gaming and virtual world space, such as Roblox and Fortnite. While Meta\'s mobile-first approach may be a sensible move, the restructuring has not been without its challenges. Recently, the company\'s Reality Labs division, which is responsible for the development of VR and metaverse technologies, laid off around 10% of its workforce.\r\n\r\nThe metaverse is a rapidly evolving and highly competitive landscape, and Meta\'s decision to pivot to a mobile-first strategy reflects the changing priorities and realities of the industry. As the company continues to navigate this transition, it will be crucial for them to maintain a strong focus on user engagement, content creation, and monetization to stay relevant and competitive in the rapidly evolving world of virtual experiences.', 92, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bbec81dace8.18502949.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 03:51:53', '2026-02-23 03:51:53', '2026-02-23 11:51:53', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(181, 126, NULL, 'Empowering Filipinos through Food Label Literacy: Insights from the Philippine Association of Nutrition', 'In today\'s increasingly complex food landscape, understanding food labels has become a critical skill for Filipino consumers. As emphasized by the Philippine Association of Nutrition (PAN), food labels are more than just regulatory compliance – they are powerful tools that empower individuals to align their food choices with their personal health goals and lifestyle needs.\r\n\r\nThe importance of clear and transparent labeling is highlighted, as it builds consumer trust and facilitates understanding. When food labels provide clear and accurate information, consumers can make informed decisions that support their well-being. This is particularly important in a country like the Philippines, where the prevalence of non-communicable diseases, such as diabetes and cardiovascular disease, continues to rise.\r\n\r\nHowever, the responsibility does not lie solely with the food industry. The article stresses the importance of consumers cultivating nutrition literacy, which allows them to critically evaluate claims, compare nutritional values, and make healthier decisions, especially for their families. By understanding the information on food labels, Filipinos can make informed choices that prioritize their health and well-being.\r\n\r\nWhile understanding labels is crucial, the enduring principles of balance and moderation in achieving a healthy diet are also reiterated. Filipinos are encouraged to start with simple habits, such as consistently checking the serving size and nutrition facts panel, to kickstart their journey towards better-informed and healthier food choices. These small steps can have a significant impact on an individual\'s overall health and can contribute to the broader societal goal of improving the nation\'s health outcomes.\r\n\r\nThe message is clear: food label literacy empowers Filipinos to take control of their health and well-being, one informed choice at a time. By equipping consumers with the knowledge and skills to interpret food labels, the Philippine Association of Nutrition is empowering Filipinos to make more mindful and nutritious choices, ultimately contributing to a healthier and more sustainable future for the nation.', 53, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_69981ea391c0d4.45280130.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 03:51:56', '2026-02-23 03:51:56', '2026-02-23 11:51:56', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(182, 124, NULL, 'Refurbished vs. New Phones in 2026: Finding the Perfect Balance Between Cost and Features', 'As smartphone prices continue to soar, the decision between purchasing a new or refurbished phone has become increasingly crucial in 2026. While new phones boast the latest features and full battery life, refurbished models present a compelling value proposition, delivering similar performance at a significantly lower cost.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to hardware performance, advancements in technology have made even older flagship devices still feel powerful and modern. Processors, RAM, and storage capacities have improved to the point where a refurbished two-year-old high-end phone can often outperform the current mid-range offerings. This means that for many users, the performance gap between new and refurbished phones has narrowed considerably, reducing the need to pay premium prices for the newest releases.\r\n\r\nCamera quality is another area where refurbished phones have become increasingly competitive. Smartphone cameras have advanced rapidly in recent years, and even the cameras on older flagship devices can capture stunning photos and videos. While the latest computational photography features may be missing, the core imaging hardware on many refurbished phones is still more than capable of meeting the needs of most users.\r\n\r\nSoftware updates are often a concern when considering a refurbished phone, as older devices may not receive the same level of long-term support as their newer counterparts. However, the software landscape has also evolved, with many Android manufacturers and even Apple providing extended update periods for their devices. Additionally, the rise of custom ROM communities and third-party software support has made it possible to keep even older phones feeling fresh and secure.\r\n\r\nSustainability is an increasingly important factor in consumer decisions, and refurbished phones offer a more eco-friendly alternative to purchasing brand-new devices. By giving new life to existing hardware, refurbished phones reduce electronic waste and minimize the environmental impact of smartphone production and disposal.\r\n\r\nUltimately, for the majority of buyers in 2026, refurbished phones make the most sense, offering an excellent balance of cost and features. However, new phones still have their place for those who prioritize the latest hardware, maximum battery life, and long-term ownership. The decision ultimately comes down to individual needs, usage patterns, and budget, with both new and refurbished options providing viable choices in the evolving smartphone market.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699817a30dbf70.98396309.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 03:51:58', '2026-02-23 03:51:58', '2026-02-23 11:51:58', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(183, 122, 167, 'Remulla: Illegal cigarettes smugglers have ‘backers’ in government', 'MANILA, Philippines — The Department of Interior and Local Government (DILG) is preparing charges against an alleged smuggler of illicit cigarettes, but agency secretary Jonvic Remulla says that these illegal operations are likely backed by government officials.  \r\n\r\nThe DILG has raided an illegal warehouse owned by a certain Jimmy Reyes Cua in Tanza, Cavite.\r\n\r\nDespite being declared as a canned goods storage site, citizens in the area reported a tobacco odor from the warehouse. \r\n\r\nAuthorities raised the warehouse, finding cigarette manufacturing machinery, industrial generators, and other equipment.\r\n\r\nThis is the fifth warehouse in a series of government raids against tobacco smugglers, with Remulla eyeing 10 major raids in total. \r\n\r\nThe DILG is preparing raps against the suspects for allegedly violating the Customs Modernization and Tariff Act, as well as the Anti-Agricultural Economic Sabotage Act.\r\n\r\n“Imposible na mangyari ito na walang protector. Sigurado ako na merong tao sa gobyerno na nasa taas lahat ito, at hindi kami titigil hanggang makuha namin at matigil namin lahat operasyon nila,” Remulla said in a press briefing on Friday, February 20. \r\n\r\n(It is impossible for this to happen without a protector. I am sure that there are people in the government high up there, and we will not stop until we get them and stop all of their operations.)   \r\n\r\nRemulla said that once these smugglers are charged, they will coordinate with the Anti-Money Laundering Council to trace the finances and see if they are tied to more powerful people. \r\n\r\nAside from being backed by officials, Remulla said that many of the warehouses and illegal factories that police have raided are owned by Chinese nationals. All of their machines are also from Mainland China.', 50, 1, 12, 'uploads/thumb_69980afcc97e0.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, 'developing', 1, '2026-02-23 03:52:01', '2026-02-23 03:52:01', '2026-02-23 11:52:01', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(184, 137, NULL, 'NASA to Roll Back Artemis II Rocket Following Helium Supply Issue', 'NASA is set to roll back the Artemis II rocket from its launch pad on February 24 due to a significant helium supply issue that has arisen during preparations for the much-anticipated mission. This decision comes as part of the agency\'s commitment to ensuring the safety and integrity of the spacecraft before it embarks on its historic journey to the Moon. The Artemis II mission aims to carry astronauts around the lunar orbit, marking a pivotal step in NASA’s broader Artemis program, which seeks to establish a sustainable human presence on the Moon and eventually pave the way for human exploration of Mars.\r\n\r\nThe helium issue was identified during recent checks, raising concerns about the rocket\'s readiness for launch. Helium is a critical component used in various systems of the Space Launch System (SLS), particularly for pressurizing fuel tanks and ensuring the stability of the spacecraft during its ascent. NASA engineers are working diligently to address the situation, but the agency has opted for a cautious approach by returning the rocket to the Vehicle Assembly Building (VAB) for further inspection and necessary repairs. This decision reflects NASA’s stringent safety protocols, ensuring that all systems are functioning optimally before the rocket is cleared for launch.\r\n\r\nThe Artemis II mission is particularly significant as it will be the first crewed flight in the Artemis program, intended to demonstrate critical technologies and operations needed for future lunar exploration. Originally scheduled for launch in late 2024, delays caused by the helium issue may push timelines further, emphasizing the complexities of space exploration. As NASA navigates these challenges, they remain committed to transparency, providing regular updates to the public and stakeholders. The agency aims to inspire confidence in the Artemis program, showcasing its dedication not only to innovation but also to safety and thoroughness in its pursuit of new frontiers in space.', 54, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699bf624b749c2.96330971.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 06:41:51', '2026-02-23 06:41:51', '2026-02-23 14:41:51', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(185, 136, NULL, 'Headline: Manila Police Under Investigation for Allegedly Blocking Driver at Traffic Light', 'The National Police Commission (Napolcom) is investigating some Manila Police District (MPD) officers after a video emerged showing an MPD vehicle allegedly blocking a driver at a traffic light while it was on a go signal.\r\n\r\nThe incident, which occurred along Taft Avenue near the Philippine General Hospital in Ermita, was captured in a video shared by vlogger James Deakin on social media. The video, which was provided to Deakin by the wife of the driver involved, shows the MPD vehicle suddenly cutting off the driver\'s vehicle, causing the driver to honk their horn to alert the officers.\r\n\r\nNapolcom Executive Officer Rafael Calinisan expressed his disappointment in the officers\' actions, stating, \"I am not exactly thrilled with what I saw.\" He immediately contacted the district director of the Manila Police District and instructed him to have the officers involved report to the Napolcom office for an investigation.\r\n\r\nCalinisan noted that he has yet to determine the exact number of police officers in the vehicle, but he described the incident as \"very petty\" and emphasized that such actions should not occur within the police force. He added, \"That kind of action should not happen in our police force... Hotter heads prevailed.\"\r\n\r\nThe driver\'s wife, who shared the video with Deakin, questioned whether citizens can no longer honk their horns at police vehicles on the road, and whether it is appropriate for a police car to retaliate in such a manner. She argued that the police should be role models on the roads, not those who set a bad example.\r\n\r\nThe Napolcom\'s motu proprio investigation is aimed at addressing this incident and ensuring that the police officers involved are held accountable for their actions, which appear to have violated the standards of professional conduct expected from law enforcement personnel.', 50, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bf201232c04.03512494.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 06:41:55', '2026-02-23 06:41:55', '2026-02-23 14:41:55', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(186, 135, NULL, 'When Cultures Connect: Pinoy Customs Drive Sari-Sari Store Sales for Chinese New Year', 'The vibrant spirit of Filipino communal celebration, often seen during traditional holidays, is now extending its reach to an unlikely calendar event: Chinese New Year. Despite being designated a special non-working holiday rather than a regular one, the festive atmosphere surrounding the Lunar New Year has proven to be a significant boon for the Philippines\' ubiquitous sari-sari stores. Data from Packworks, a leading retail-tech startup, reveals a compelling trend: a surge in sales driven by distinctly Pinoy traditions of gathering, feasting, and last-minute preparations.\r\n\r\nAccording to Packworks\' comprehensive analysis, sari-sari stores across the archipelago experienced an average sales increase of 15% during the Chinese New Year week compared to the preceding week. This impressive growth underscores the deep-rooted Filipino inclination to celebrate, regardless of a holiday\'s official status. The impact was particularly pronounced in key provinces, with Laguna, Pampanga, Cavite, Batangas, and Bulacan reporting even higher jumps, ranging from 18% to 20%. Other regions, including Bicol, Western Visayas, and Zamboanga Peninsula, also witnessed double-digit sales growth, painting a picture of nationwide participation in the festivities. The types of products flying off the shelves further solidify the narrative of communal celebration: carbonated drinks, instant noodles, beer, chips, and a variety of snacks topped the sales charts – all essential ingredients for impromptu gatherings and family meals.\r\n\r\nThis phenomenon highlights the crucial role sari-sari stores play within Filipino communities. Often the most accessible retail points, especially in remote areas, these micro-enterprises become indispensable hubs for last-minute purchases and daily necessities. The sales surge during Chinese New Year is', 49, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699bf1f8ce5ab8.23011968.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 06:41:58', '2026-02-23 06:41:58', '2026-02-23 14:41:58', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187, 134, NULL, 'Philippines Faces Challenges in Achieving Digital Payments Targets, Warns BSP', 'The Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP) has raised concerns regarding the Philippines\' potential to meet its ambitious digital payments targets. The central bank had previously set a goal to transition 50% of all retail transactions to digital formats by 2023 as part of its broader strategy to enhance financial inclusion across the nation. However, recent evaluations suggest that the country may fall short of this target, highlighting several underlying issues that need to be addressed.\r\n\r\nOne of the primary challenges hindering the growth of digital payments in the Philippines is the lack of infrastructure, particularly in rural areas. While urban centers have seen a surge in digital payment adoption, many remote locations still rely heavily on cash transactions due to limited internet access and inadequate financial services. The BSP has emphasized the need for improved connectivity and infrastructure investments to bridge this digital divide. Additionally, the disparity in financial literacy among the population poses another significant barrier, as many individuals remain unaware of the advantages and operations of digital payment systems.\r\n\r\nTo overcome these obstacles, the BSP is actively working to promote financial education and encourage the adoption of digital platforms among both businesses and consumers. Initiatives such as partnerships with private sector stakeholders and public awareness campaigns aim to foster a culture of digital payments, emphasizing not only convenience but also security and efficiency. The BSP\'s commitment to supporting a more inclusive financial ecosystem is crucial, especially in light of the ongoing push for economic recovery post-pandemic. As the country navigates these challenges, collaborative efforts will be essential in realizing the full potential of digital payments and achieving the targeted transformation in the financial landscape of the Philippines.', 54, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699bf07538f736.89496404.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 06:42:02', '2026-02-23 06:42:02', '2026-02-23 14:42:02', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188, 133, NULL, 'AFP Enhances Interagency Collaboration with Training in Tarlac', 'In a significant effort to enhance operational efficiency and interagency collaboration, the Armed Forces of the Philippines (AFP) conducted an interagency coordination training in Tarlac. This initiative, aimed at improving the capacity of various government agencies to respond effectively to national security challenges, was held at the AFP Command and General Staff College. The training brought together representatives from multiple sectors, including law enforcement, disaster response, and local government units, highlighting the importance of a unified approach in addressing complex situations.\r\n\r\nThe training program included a series of workshops and simulations designed to foster communication and coordination among participating agencies. Facilitators emphasized the critical need for a cohesive response framework, particularly in crisis situations where timely and effective action is paramount. Participants engaged in practical exercises that tested their abilities to work collaboratively, share resources, and leverage each other\'s strengths. This focused approach not only aimed to improve individual agency capabilities but also sought to establish a network of cooperation that can be activated during emergencies.\r\n\r\nOfficials from the AFP underscored the importance of such training in building resilience within communities and enhancing national security protocols. By fostering strong interagency relationships, the AFP aims to create a more robust response system capable of addressing a wide range of threats, from natural disasters to security concerns. As the complexities of modern challenges evolve, the need for integrated strategies becomes increasingly vital, making initiatives like the Tarlac training a crucial component of the AFP\'s ongoing commitment to national safety and security.', 46, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699bef120bd703.63944006.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 06:42:05', '2026-02-23 06:42:05', '2026-02-23 14:42:05', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(189, 144, NULL, 'Ryan Garcia Outclasses Mario Barrios to Win WBC Welterweight Title in Las Vegas', 'LAS VEGAS — Ryan Garcia showcased his boxing prowess on Saturday night, decisively defeating Mario Barrios to win the WBC welterweight championship by unanimous decision. The judges scored the bout 119-108, 120-107, and 118-109 in favor of Garcia, who improved his record to 25 wins, 2 losses, and 20 knockouts. In contrast, Barrios, who fell to 29-3-2 with 18 knockouts, struggled to make an impact in what was his second consecutive disappointing performance, having previously managed only a majority draw against Manny Pacquiao last July.\r\n\r\nIn the co-main event, Gary Antuanne Russell retained his WBA super lightweight title with a unanimous decision over Japan’s Andy Hiraoka, with the judges scoring the fight 117-110, 116-111, and 116-111. Hiraoka received a point deduction in the 10th round for a low blow that interrupted the action. Meanwhile, Richardson Hitchins was scheduled to defend his IBF super lightweight title against Oscar Duarte but withdrew due to illness, leaving uncertainty regarding the status of his title. Garcia, favored at -250 by BetMGM Sportsbook, effectively began the fight by knocking down Barrios within the first half-minute and maintained control throughout, displaying a tactical approach as he looked to redeem himself after a challenging three years marked by a suspension and personal issues.', 56, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699c04b04b1157.61064392.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:30', '2026-02-23 07:42:30', '2026-02-23 15:42:30', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(190, 143, NULL, 'This is how Whirlpool washers make laundry easier in homes of every size', 'Laundry is part of every Filipino household story, whether it’s tackling a week’s worth of shirts and uniforms from a busy family or doing quick daily washes in a compact condo. Every home has its own pace, and Whirlpool designs washers that fit seamlessly into those real, everyday moments.\r\n\r\nFrom high-capacity units built for big families to compact models perfect for modern living, Whirlpool’s top load washing machine lineup brings the right balance of convenience, performance, and reliability. Whatever your space or routine looks like, there is a Whirlpool washer made to keep your laundry days simpler, smoother, and stress-free.\r\n\r\nFor large households or heavy-laundry days, keeping up with piles of clothes, towels, and linens can quickly consume time. The 4GWTW3000FW 15 kg IEC Top Load U.S. Washer delivers true heavy-duty performance with a galvanized outer body that resists rust and a white porcelain inner tub that protects fabrics while standing up to frequent use. Its Dual Action Agitator tackles large loads such as blankets, towels, and everyday clothing efficiently while still providing gentle care.\r\n\r\nWhen paired with the 4KWED4815FW U.S. Electric Dryer or the 4GWGD4815FW U.S. Gas Dryer, both 15 kg IEC rated, families get a heavy-duty dryer designed to handle large loads efficiently. Its AccuDry Sensing System detects moisture levels and adjusts the drying cycle automatically to ensure clothes reach the ideal dryness. This prevents over-drying, saves energy, and keeps fabrics in excellent condition.\r\n\r\nWith this heavy-duty U.S. washer and dryer pair, families can tackle laundry faster and with greater efficiency, leaving more time for meals, schoolwork, or simply relaxing together', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699c026794f248.66424069.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:35', '2026-02-23 07:42:35', '2026-02-23 15:42:35', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(191, 142, NULL, 'Expert Insights on Love Handles: Causes, Risks, and Effective Solutions', 'In Manila, the term \"love handles\" may evoke a sense of affection, but the health implications of excess fat around the waist are far from benign. Love handles refer to the surplus fat that accumulates above the waistline, often where a partner’s hands would rest during an embrace. Dr. Juancho Alfredo D. Las from Makati Medical Center explains that this fat accumulation occurs when caloric intake exceeds expenditure. Factors such as age, genetics, body composition, and hormonal fluctuations influence where fat is deposited, with common areas including the upper back, arms, abdomen, and thighs. Excess fat, particularly visceral fat surrounding vital organs like the heart and liver, poses significant health risks, including heart disease, stroke, type II diabetes, hypertension, and certain cancers. To mitigate these risks, Dr. Las recommends dietary changes, such as reducing ultra-processed foods that contribute to weight gain and increasing the intake of natural, minimally processed items like lean proteins, high-fiber vegetables, fruits, oats, and beans. Incorporating healthy fats from avocados and nuts, while favoring whole grains like brown rice over white rice, is also advised. Exercise plays a crucial role, even for those with sedentary jobs; simple changes like taking the stairs, walking short distances, and engaging in physical activities with colleagues can promote fitness. While cardiovascular workouts are effective for fat loss, strength training also has long-term benefits by continuing to burn calories post-exercise. Additionally, managing stress is essential as elevated cortisol levels can lead to increased belly fat. Dr. Las emphasizes the importance of adequate sleep to regulate appetite hormones and advises against smoking, which disrupts hormone balance. Moreover, alcohol consumption should be moderated, as excessive intake can lead to weight gain in the midsection. Understanding these aspects of love handles is vital for improving overall health and well-being.', 53, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699bffe4c2c7b5.51005548.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:38', '2026-02-23 07:42:38', '2026-02-23 15:42:38', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(192, 141, NULL, 'Nintendo Switch Gets Classic Pokémon Titles, But Will They Connect to Pokémon HOME?', 'Nintendo is set to release classic titles *Pokémon FireRed Version* and *Pokémon LeafGreen Version* on the Nintendo Switch next week, coinciding with the franchise\'s 30th anniversary. This re-release offers a nostalgic return to the Kanto region for both new and veteran trainers, featuring updated graphics and refined gameplay based on the original *Pokémon Red* and *Green* games. However, a significant concern looms over this launch: whether these new versions will be compatible with *Pokémon HOME*, the cloud-based service that allows players to store and transfer their Pokémon across various games. Despite some details about the upcoming releases being revealed, Nintendo and The Pokémon Company have not clarified this crucial aspect, leaving dedicated fans, particularly collectors and completionists, anxious about the potential impact on their gameplay experience.\r\n\r\n*Pokémon HOME* has become an essential tool for many players, enabling them to manage extensive Pokémon collections from multiple titles, including the latest mainline games and the mobile game *Pokémon GO*. Its integration with older systems through *Pokémon Bank* allows trainers to transfer Pokémon from classic titles into the modern gaming landscape, although the process can be complex and tedious. Currently, the original *FireRed* and *LeafGreen* games support *Pokémon HOME*, but the transfer method is intricate, requiring multiple systems and steps to migrate Pokémon from the Game Boy Advance titles to the cloud service. The possibility of direct compatibility with the new Switch versions could significantly streamline this process, eliminating the need for outdated hardware.\r\n\r\nThe absence of direct *Pokémon HOME* integration for the upcoming Switch versions poses a critical challenge for players aiming to achieve 100% completion of the games. While the Kanto Pokédex can be filled through regular gameplay and local trades, completing the National Dex—which includes Pokémon from later generations—requires trading with other titles that are not currently available on the Switch. This limitation raises concerns, particularly for completionists who strive to \"catch \'em all.\" Despite the excitement surrounding the launch of *FireRed* and *LeafGreen*, the lack of clarity from Nintendo and The Pokémon Company about *Pokémon HOME* compatibility has left many with unresolved questions. With the official release just around the corner, fans eagerly await further announcements to determine how these classic titles will fit into the modern Pokémon ecosystem.', 92, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699bfebe7b9433.10845465.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:42', '2026-02-23 07:42:42', '2026-02-23 15:42:42', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(193, 140, NULL, 'Samsung Expands Galaxy AI Ecosystem with Perplexity Integration for Enhanced User Experience', 'Samsung Electronics has announced the expansion of its Galaxy AI ecosystem, introducing a new AI agent called Perplexity to provide users with greater choice, flexibility, and control in their daily interactions. This move reflects the growing trend of users relying on multiple AI agents for different tasks, as AI becomes more integrated into daily routines.\r\n\r\nGalaxy AI is designed to work at the system level, understanding the user\'s context to support more natural and efficient interactions, reducing the need to switch between apps or repeat commands. The addition of Perplexity as an integrated AI agent on upcoming flagship Galaxy devices will allow users to access it through voice commands or quick-access controls, enabling smoother, multi-step workflows across a range of Samsung and third-party apps.\r\n\r\nSamsung\'s vision for the Galaxy AI ecosystem is to create an open and inclusive platform that offers users a richer and more flexible AI experience. By collaborating with trusted partners like Perplexity, the company aims to continue expanding its AI capabilities and provide seamless, user-centric experiences that are easy to use and accessible to all.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bfc9bb55d55.89826218.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:45', '2026-02-23 07:42:45', '2026-02-23 15:42:45', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(194, 139, NULL, 'Mayweather\'s Return Sparks Pacquiao Rematch Talk', 'Filipino boxing icon Manny Pacquiao has recently teased the possibility of a rematch with Floyd Mayweather Jr., sparked by Mayweather’s announcement of his return to the boxing ring. At a press event for the partnership between Sportsplus and the Maharlika Pilipinas Basketball League (MPBL), Pacquiao was asked about Mayweather\'s decision to come out of retirement. He cryptically replied, \"Abangan niyo na lang announcement\" (Just wait for the announcement), leaving fans speculating on what could unfold. Mayweather, who retired in 2017 with an impressive record of 50 wins and no losses, has remained active through various exhibition bouts. His next challenge is set against former heavyweight champion Mike Tyson on April 25, paving the way for a potential return to professional boxing. Meanwhile, Pacquiao is also preparing for his own exhibition match against former world champion Ruslan Provodnikov on April 18 in Las Vegas.\r\n\r\nThe first encounter between these two boxing titans, known as the \"Fight of the Century,\" took place in 2015, where Mayweather claimed victory by unanimous decision. Since then, the idea of a rematch has captivated fans and analysts alike. Pacquiao’s return to the ring occurred approximately seven months ago, when he fought Mario Barrios Jr. to a draw. Following Mayweather\'s recent statements, Pacquiao has expressed that a rematch is among the options he is considering for his next bout. In addition to his boxing endeavors, he is committed to maintaining the integrity of the MPBL, especially in light of ongoing game-fixing allegations. \"As the founder of the Maharlika Pilipinas Basketball League, I am always watching to protect the integrity and the name of the MPBL,\" Pacquiao declared, urging players to stay clear of any misconduct that could threaten their careers. \"We can play the game fairly and show it to the public. Getting involved in that will only destroy your integrity as players,\" he asserted. With both fighters gearing up for their upcoming events, the boxing world eagerly anticipates further updates on a potential rematch that could once again captivate audiences globally.', 56, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699bfc73e6a184.25002727.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:48', '2026-02-23 07:42:48', '2026-02-23 15:42:48', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(195, 138, NULL, 'PayPal Customers Impacted by Data Breach, Passwords Reset', 'PayPal has confirmed a data breach that exposed personal information of some of its users for around six months. The breach impacted the company\'s PayPal Working Capital (PPWC) loan application process, allowing a hacker to gain unauthorized access to PayPal\'s systems from July to December 2025.\r\n\r\nThe exposed information includes names, email addresses, phone numbers, business addresses, Social Security numbers, and dates of birth. A small number of customers, around 100 according to PayPal, also experienced unauthorized transactions on their accounts, which have been refunded.\r\n\r\nPayPal has terminated the attacker\'s access to its systems and reset the passwords of affected accounts. The company is offering two years of complimentary credit monitoring and identity restoration services to those impacted.\r\n\r\nTo protect themselves, PayPal is advising all users to use unique username and password combinations, change passwords and security questions if they detect suspicious activity, be wary of phishing attempts, and never provide login credentials over a call, text, or email. The article also recommends using passkeys whenever available for added security.\r\n\r\nWhile the breach appears to have been limited in scope, it serves as a reminder for all PayPal customers to remain vigilant and take proactive steps to safeguard their accounts and personal information.', 50, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699bf80f3dd984.64774320.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 07:42:52', '2026-02-23 07:42:52', '2026-02-23 15:42:52', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(196, 148, NULL, 'Hello Kitty’s Creator Yuko Yamaguchi Steps Down After 43 Years', 'TOKYO, Japan — Yuko Yamaguchi, the iconic designer who has shaped the beloved character Hello Kitty for over four decades, is stepping down from her role. Since 1980, Yamaguchi has been the creative force behind Hello Kitty, who is officially recognized as a little girl from London rather than a cat, epitomizing Japan\'s \"kawaii\" or cute culture. Sanrio, the company that manages the character, announced on its website that Yamaguchi has \"passed the baton to the next generation,\" with a new designer, known by the pseudonym \"Aya,\" set to take over by the end of 2026. Yamaguchi, often seen in Hello Kitty-inspired outfits, has been praised for her ability to connect with fans and collaborate with various artists, helping to elevate Hello Kitty into a global phenomenon. From her humble beginnings on a vinyl coin purse, Hello Kitty has expanded into a vast array of products, collaborating with high-profile brands like Adidas and Balenciaga. The character\'s popularity continues to grow, with a Warner Bros movie in development and a new theme park scheduled to open next year in Hainan, China. Despite her many adventures, Hello Kitty remains largely narrative-free, with her full name being Kitty White and a few key companions, including her twin sister Mimmy and her boyfriend Dear Daniel.', 57, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699c1123c41e85.75054696.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 10:37:26', '2026-02-23 10:37:26', '2026-02-23 18:37:26', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
