(197, 147, NULL, 'Marcos and Robredo Advocate Collaboration Over Political Rivalry', 'MANILA, Philippines — President Ferdinand R. Marcos Jr. reiterated his commitment to addressing the nation\'s challenges, downplaying discussions about potential alliances with opposition figures as the country approaches the 2028 presidential elections. In a recent Facebook post, he stressed the need for political collaboration, stating, “Differences in politics should never prevent us from working together for our people.” Marcos emphasized that national interests must take precedence over personal political ambitions, declaring, “Nation first. Personal agendas later.”\r\n\r\nIn a video shared on social media, Marcos and former Vice President Leni Robredo discussed the possibility of collaboration between their political parties, especially in light of Vice President Sara Duterte’s announcement of her presidential candidacy for 2028. However, Malacañang Palace has labeled any election-related discussions as premature, with Marcos describing Duterte’s early declaration as “irrelevant.” Robredo, who met with Marcos in Naga City last week for a separate project, denied that their discussions focused on the upcoming elections, asserting that such a focus would be a “disservice” to her constituents. Both leaders appear to be prioritizing public service over electoral strategies for the time being, even as the political landscape remains fluid.', 48, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699c0904ef7ce3.63700377.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 10:37:34', '2026-02-23 10:37:34', '2026-02-23 18:37:34', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(198, 145, NULL, 'In a Single Shot: Alessandra de Rossi\'s Bold Directorial Vision', 'In the wake of Juaning Sevilla\'s death, her youngest daughter Miraquel, played by Alessandra de Rossi, has stepped into the role of caretaker for the family home, alongside her husband Alfred, portrayed by JM de Guzman. To manage the household, they enlisted the help of an eccentric maid named Anna (Angeli Bayani) and a gardener named Jacob (Kevin Miranda), who had a special bond with Juaning. As the first anniversary of Juaning\'s passing approaches, coinciding with the local town fiesta, Miraquel\'s five older siblings gather for a reunion lunch, showcasing the complex dynamics within the family. The siblings include Tupe (Edu Manzano), a renowned plastic surgeon with a teenage wife and an iguana; Josie (Ruby Ruiz), a housewife entangled in a same-sex affair; Rosalinda (Gina Alajar), a political aspirant; Ramil (Ronnie Lazaro), a devout cult member; and Roel (Joel Torre), the family\'s estranged musician.\r\n\r\nThe film, which marks Alessandra de Rossi\'s second directorial effort after \"My Amanda\" (2021), delves into the familiar narrative of estranged families reconvening after the loss of a parent, yet it does so with a distinctive flair. Utilizing a continuous shot technique that keeps the camera in constant motion, De Rossi adds a unique dimension to the storytelling while posing significant challenges for the cast, who must maintain precision and collaboration throughout. Featuring an ensemble of award-winning actors, the film\'s ambitious format intensifies the pressure on performers, as any mistakes would necessitate a complete reshoot. While the execution may have its flaws—such as shaky camera work and inconsistent lighting—the film manages to engage its audience with the actors\' lively interactions and the script\'s blend of humor and emotional depth. Ultimately, the film captures the essence of familial bonds, navigating themes of love, conflict, and the complexities of relationships, all while delivering an entertaining experience that resonates with viewers.', 55, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699c05a6dd8106.06937414.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-23 10:37:37', '2026-02-23 10:37:37', '2026-02-23 18:37:37', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(199, 146, NULL, 'Rare Metal Alloy May Unlock the Potential of Quantum Computing', 'The Norwegian University of Science and Technology (NTNU) researchers believe they have found signs of a rare triplet superconductor, a material that could revolutionize quantum computing. Triplet superconductors have the ability to transmit both electricity and electron spin with zero resistance, which could dramatically stabilize quantum computers while significantly reducing their energy consumption.\r\n\r\nThe researchers have been studying the niobium-rhenium (NbRe) alloy, a rare metal combination, and their findings suggest that it behaves differently from conventional superconductors. This could make NbRe a potential cornerstone for next-generation quantum and spintronic technology.\r\n\r\nConventional superconductors, known as \"singlet superconductors,\" do not carry spin, while triplet superconductors can transport both electrical currents and spin currents with zero resistance. This unique property could enable the development of ultra-fast quantum computers that operate using almost no electricity.\r\n\r\nProfessor Jacob Linder, a physicist at NTNU\'s Department of Physics and a researcher at the QuSpin research center, explained that the stability of quantum technology has been a major challenge, and triplet superconductors could be the solution. The ability to transmit spin currents without any energy loss could significantly improve the accuracy of quantum computer operations.\r\n\r\nThe researchers have published their findings in Physical Review Letters, where the paper was selected as one of the journal\'s editor\'s recommendations. While further verification is still needed, the initial results are promising, as the NbRe alloy superconducts at a relatively high temperature of 7 Kelvin, which is more practical and attainable compared to other potential triplet superconductors that require temperatures close to 1 Kelvin.\r\n\r\nIf the existence of a triplet superconductor is confirmed, it could pave the way for the development of the most energy-efficient technologies ever created, including ultra-fast quantum computers that operate with virtually no power consumption.', 54, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699c0862c5de25.26161095.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-24 02:29:12', '2026-02-24 02:29:12', '2026-02-24 10:29:12', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(200, 170, NULL, 'Taste and Art Unite: Hong Kong Launches Inaugural Central Yards Edible Art Fair', 'Art and gastronomy converge in Hong Kong with the inaugural Central Yards Edible Art Fair, taking place from March 26 to April 4 at the Central Harbourfront Event Space. This unique cultural event, envisioned by Arbiona Cadman, the founder and creative director of Feste Group, and curated by Art-Partners, serves as an introduction to Central Yards—a significant mixed-use development by Henderson Land Group, set to begin in phases in 2027. The project, which will cover more than 1.6 million square feet, aims to transform Hong Kong\'s Central district by integrating commerce, culture, and lifestyle.\r\n\r\nSet within a specially constructed tent of nearly 20,000 square feet adjacent to the forthcoming development, the fair offers a 10-gallery, multi-sensory experience. Each installation draws inspiration from a prominent art movement and is complemented by an edible creation. Visitors can immerse themselves in interactive environments that showcase styles ranging from Impressionism and Surrealism to Modernism, Neo-Pop, and Optical Illusion Art. Two galleries highlight Hong Kong\'s Contemporary and New Ink Art movements through partnerships with local artists. Open daily from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m., the event features timed entries every 30 minutes. Tickets grant access to all installations and curated edible delights, with optional workshops allowing attendees to craft their own edible art.', 58, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d4bf7b9eb62.16886367.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:23', '2026-02-25 03:22:23', '2026-02-25 11:22:23', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(201, 169, NULL, 'Philippines Sees Decline in External Debt Service Burden as Payments Drop', 'The Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP) reported a significant reduction in the Philippines’ external debt service burden during the first 11 months of 2025, highlighting a decline in both principal and interest payments. Combined payments to foreign creditors from January to November totaled approximately $12 billion, marking a nearly 23 percent decrease from the same period in the previous year. This reduction brings the debt service burden down to 2.9 percent of the country’s gross domestic product (GDP), a notable improvement from the previous year’s figure of 3.9 percent. Additionally, the share of external debt payments relative to total export receipts also fell from 30.6 percent to 20.7 percent, indicating that the Philippines is using a smaller portion of its export revenues to meet foreign obligations.\r\n\r\nDespite the decrease in debt servicing costs, the total external obligations of both the public and private sectors reached $149 billion, reflecting a year-on-year increase of 6.8 percent and representing 30.9 percent of GDP. Government offshore liabilities rose nearly 11 percent to $96.3 billion, while private sector obligations remained stable at $52.8 billion. Economists attribute the decline in debt service payments to fewer external debts maturing this year and decreasing global interest rates. Michael Ricafort, chief economist at Rizal Commercial Banking Corp., suggested that continued lower foreign borrowings and potential rate cuts by the U.S. Federal Reserve may contribute to ongoing reductions in foreign debt servicing costs. The BSP, which is responsible for compiling and publishing external debt statistics, aims to enhance transparency and support informed decision-making among borrowers, lenders, and policymakers.', 49, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d49886458a7.00884789.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:26', '2026-02-25 03:22:26', '2026-02-25 11:22:26', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(202, 168, NULL, 'Revolutionizing Color Perception: Los Alamos Researchers Fill Gaps in Schrödinger\'s Theory', 'A century after Erwin Schrödinger first outlined a geometric theory of color perception, researchers at Los Alamos National Laboratory have completed the picture. Led by Roxana Bujack, the team mathematically demonstrated that hue, saturation, and lightness are not shaped by culture or experience but are embedded in the internal structure of the color system itself. By defining a long-missing element known as the “neutral axis” — the continuum of grays from black to white — they resolved a foundational gap in Schrödinger’s framework. Their model also corrects perceptual anomalies such as the Bezold-Brücke effect, where increasing brightness subtly alters perceived hue, by calculating color relationships using shortest paths within a refined geometric space.\r\n\r\nPresented at the Eurographics Conference on Visualization, the research strengthens the mathematical foundations of color theory and advances visualization science. Building on earlier work published in the Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences in 2022, the findings improve how color differences are measured and interpreted in curved, non-Riemannian perceptual spaces. More precise color modeling has wide-ranging applications, from photography and video technology to complex data analysis and national security simulations, offering a more reliable framework for how humans truly perceive color.', 95, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d418c42e3c5.70973650.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:33', '2026-02-25 03:22:33', '2026-02-25 11:22:33', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(203, 167, NULL, 'Kris Lawrence recalls meeting Alvin Aragon, apology over stolen phone', 'Kris Lawrence recounted the 2006 incident involving his stolen phone and Alvin Aragon, saying the latter had apologized for it.\r\n\r\nAragon has been making headlines due to his criticisms toward his wife Izzy Trazona’s former girl group SexBomb Girls as well as her transgender child Sofia Trazona. He further became a trending topic on social media after his video admitting that he used to steal from others — with his victims including Lawrence — resurfaced.\r\n\r\nThrough his Facebook page on Monday, Feb. 23, Lawrence spoke about the matter and narrated how he was with fellow singer Jay R at a bar when they met a group of people that included Aragon. As the bar was closing at the time, Lawrence said he invited the group to his house to have a few more drinks.\r\n\r\n“They came to the house and we started drinking in the studio. [Nung] sumisikat na ‘yung araw, pack up na, umalis na sila. When I was going back to my room, I noticed that nawawala ang cellphone ko,” Lawrence recalled. (The morning came so they left. When I was going back to my room, I noticed that my phone was missing.)\r\n\r\nLawrence then said that one of Aragon’s friends called the former apparently out of guilt, and admitted that the then-“Starstruck” contestant took the singer’s cellphone.\r\n\r\n“I was like, ‘Dude, why would you do that? Why would you steal from me in my own house? That’s so disrespectful,\'” Lawrence continued.\r\n\r\n“Nag-sorry siya and honestly, my fists were balled up. Gusto ko siyang suntukin pero I know that violence is never the answer, so I said it’s okay,” he stated, “Medyo binibinigyan ko pa rin siya ng attitude na understandable naman kasi ninakaw niya ‘yung cellphone ko.”\r\n\r\nLawrence even quipped that he had already forgotten about the incident, but was reminded of it after Aragon’s video admitting to it recently resurfaced.\r\n\r\n“I know he’s in a better place now. I know he’s a Christian and alam ko naman na mabait si Alvin (I know that Alvin is kind),” the singer said.\r\n\r\nHe, however, expressed confusion toward the end of the video as he addressed Aragon, “Naibalik mo ba [‘yung phone]?” (Were you able to return the phone?)', 55, 1, 13, 'uploads/thumb_699d4061e9d194.93390894.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:36', '2026-02-25 03:22:36', '2026-02-25 11:22:36', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(204, 166, 160, 'Alexandra Eala Builds Momentum Following Career-Defining Year', 'Filipina tennis standout Alexandra Eala continued her meteoric rise in the professional ranks, climbing 16 spots to world No. 31 in the latest WTA Rankings released on February 23, 2026. With the jump, she further cemented her place in history as the only player from the Philippines to break into the WTA Top 100 since the rankings began in 1975. Her surge followed an impressive campaign at the Dubai Duty Free Tennis Championships, where she defeated Hailey Baptiste, sixth seed Jasmine Paolini, and Sorana Cîrstea before bowing out to Coco Gauff in the quarterfinals. Beyond her on-court success, Eala’s rapidly growing global fanbase has drawn attention across the tour, with fellow stars Jessica Pegula and Gauff noting the strong support she receives at tournaments.\r\n\r\nThe 20-year-old holds a 10–6 singles record this season and has already competed in six events, showcasing one of the busiest schedules on tour. She now heads into the prestigious Sunshine Swing in the United States, set to compete at the BNP Paribas Open in Indian Wells and the Miami Open—both WTA Masters 1000 events that offer major ranking opportunities. It was in Miami last year where Eala enjoyed her breakthrough, stunning Iga Swiatek en route to a semifinal finish. Reflecting on her journey, Eala shared that the past year of consistently playing full WTA tournaments has brought growth, maturity, and perspective, as she continues embracing both the sacrifices and rewards of living out her lifelong dream.', 56, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d3f7f89e358.54208718.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, '', 4, '2026-02-25 03:22:39', '2026-02-25 03:22:39', '2026-02-25 11:22:39', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(205, 165, NULL, 'Vlogger Francis Leo Marcos Arrested for Alleged Usurpation of Authority', 'Norman Mangusin, popularly known as Francis Leo Marcos, was apprehended by the Philippine National Police (PNP) at a hotel in Pasay City, with the confirmation coming from the National Police Commission (NAPOLCOM) on Tuesday. NAPOLCOM Vice Chairperson and Executive Officer Rafael Vicente Calinisan informed the media that the Criminal Investigation and Detection Group - National Capital Region (CIDG-NCR) carried out the arrest under a warrant issued by the Regional Trial Court Branch 294 of Parañaque. Calinisan stated, “I confirm that the PNP-CIDG-NCR just arrested Mangusin in (a hotel) by virtue of a warrant of arrest issued by the Regional Trial Court Branch 294 of Parañaque,” adding that the Pasay City Police and operatives from the NAPOLCOM Inspection, Monitoring, and Investigation Service were also involved, declaring this event a triumph for justice in the Philippines and emphasizing that crime does not pay. He also mentioned plans to visit Mangusin upon his arrival at the CIDG. This development follows an investigation initiated by the CIDG on February 17 due to a viral image of Mangusin donning a police uniform. The PNP had previously criticized Mangusin, hinting at potential charges for “usurpation of authority and illegal use of uniforms or insignia.” NAPOLCOM has shown its support for the PNP\'s inquiry into Mangusin. The investigation stemmed from a photo showing Mangusin in a “ceremonial blue” police uniform, to which Mangusin responded by claiming that the image was digitally altered and maliciously leaked by individuals opposed to him.', NULL, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d3cf24d1b91.09651358.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:41', '2026-02-25 03:22:41', '2026-02-25 11:22:41', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(206, 164, NULL, 'Anne Curtis, Jericho Rosales’ reunion movie ‘The Loved One’ earns P160 million', 'Anne Curtis and Jericho Rosales’ heartbreaking portrayal of the end of a long-term relationship brought audiences to the cinemas, as “The Loved One” earned P160-million at the box office.\r\n\r\nAs of Sunday, Feb. 22, the Irene Villamor-helmed film crossed the P160-million mark in global box office sales, as announced by Viva Films on Facebook. \r\n\r\n“We feel your yearning hanggang abroad! Maraming salamat ‘coz ‘THE LOVED ONE’ just reached P160 MILLION global gross! Iba mag-yearn ang mga Pinoy!” the production company said. \r\n\r\n(We feel your yearning even from abroad. Thank you very much because ‘The Loved One’ just reached P160 million in global gross. Filipinos yearn very differently.)\r\n\r\nThe film tells the story of Ellie (Curtis) and Eric (Rosales), whose attraction, which, according to Ellie, came from them being a Gemini and a Leo, respectively, blossomed into a long-term relationship. \r\n\r\nAs they passed the honeymoon stage, Ellie and Eric found themselves constantly fighting over what they truly wanted in their relationship, which eventually led to their breakup. They meet again several years later, with Ellie saying that they had “just been too much for each other,” which was why they didn’t work out.\r\n\r\n“The Loved One” also made headlines for the use of Cup of Joe’s “Multo” as its theme song, which was arguably one of the biggest OPM songs in the past year.\r\n\r\nViva Films CEO Vincent del Rosario told Deadline that, aside from the relatable storyline and star power of its leads, it’s the lower ticket prices that led to its strong box-office performance.\r\n\r\n“The narrative is tailored to resonate with a Filipino audience, capturing the essence of a generation seeking a poignant romantic drama with characters that reflect their own experiences,” he was quoted as saying. “The reduced cinema ticket prices also helped make the film more accessible to a wider audience.”\r\n\r\nThe film also stars Catriona Gray, Jackie Lou Blanco, Luis Alandy, and Max Eigenmann.\r\n\r\nAside from the Philippines, “The Loved One” is also showing in the US and the UAE. It will also hit cinemas in Canada, Taiwan, New Zealand, and Australia soon.', 55, 1, 13, 'uploads/thumb_699d3b69d4ce45.13458478.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:44', '2026-02-25 03:22:44', '2026-02-25 11:22:44', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(207, 163, NULL, 'Breakthrough in Space Weather Forecasting: AI-Enabled Tool Paves the Way for Advance Warnings', 'Researchers at the U.S. National Science Foundation National Center for Atmospheric Research (NSF NCAR) and Southwest Research Institute (SwRI) have developed a new tool called PINNBARDS (PINN-Based Active Regions Distribution Simulator) that provides a first step toward the ability to forecast space weather weeks in advance, instead of just hours. \r\n\r\nThe PINNBARDS framework integrates global solar active region observations with a physics-based model and artificial intelligence (AI) to better understand and anticipate extreme space weather. This advance warning could allow agencies and industries to mitigate impacts to GPS, power grids, astronaut safety and more.\r\n\r\nThe simulations for the research utilized the Derecho supercomputer at the NSF NCAR-Wyoming Supercomputer Center. The research was funded by NASA\'s Heliophysics Guest Investigator Open (HGIO) program and Consequences of Fields and Flows in the Interior and Exterior of the Sun (COFFIES) DRIVE Center.\r\n\r\nThe reconstructed subsurface states from PINNBARDS provide initial conditions for forward simulations of solar magnetic evolution, opening the door to predicting where and when large, flare-producing active regions are likely to emerge weeks in advance. This breakthrough represents a significant step forward in space weather forecasting capabilities, which are critical for safeguarding our technological infrastructure and enabling future human space exploration.', NULL, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699d1e31497567.85011670.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:47', '2026-02-25 03:22:47', '2026-02-25 11:22:47', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(208, 162, NULL, 'Six Planets to Align in Rare Celestial Spectacle This Weekend', 'This weekend, stargazers will have the opportunity to witness a rare planetary parade, as six planets will align in the night sky. According to the article, the lineup includes Mercury, Venus, Jupiter, and Saturn, all of which will be visible to the naked eye. Additionally, Uranus and Neptune can be spotted with the help of binoculars or telescopes.\r\n\r\nThe optimal time to view the celestial event is about an hour after sunset, when the planets will be visible in the western sky. Viewers should look for objects that are not twinkling, as those are the planets, rather than stars.\r\n\r\nThis planetary parade is a relatively uncommon occurrence, with lineups of four or five planets being less frequent and happening every few years. Last year, both a six-planet and a seven-planet alignment were observed.\r\n\r\nAstronomers and planetary scientists are excited about this event, as it allows people to connect with the centuries-old practice of making sense of the universe by simply looking up at the night sky. This is a testament to the enduring fascination with the celestial bodies and the continued wonder that they inspire in both professional and amateur stargazers alike.', NULL, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699d1c235d1a75.30932881.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:49', '2026-02-25 03:22:49', '2026-02-25 11:22:49', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(209, 161, NULL, 'Sibol Announces Team Representatives for Upcoming Asian Games Events', 'As the excitement builds for the upcoming Asian Games, Sibol, the Philippines\' national esports team, has officially named its representatives for three key events. This announcement comes as a significant step forward for Filipino esports, highlighting the nation\'s commitment to competing on the international stage. The Asian Games, set to take place in Hangzhou, China, in September 2023, will feature a diverse range of esports disciplines, and Sibol is ready to showcase its talent and determination.\r\n\r\nSibol\'s roster includes a mix of seasoned veterans and promising newcomers, reflecting the country\'s dynamic gaming culture. The selected athletes will represent the Philippines in popular titles such as League of Legends, Dota 2, and Mobile Legends: Bang Bang. Each representative has undergone rigorous training and selection processes to ensure that they possess not only exceptional gaming skills but also the ability to perform under pressure in a highly competitive environment. As the team prepares for the games, they are focused on strategy, teamwork, and mental resilience, essential elements for success in the fast-paced world of esports.\r\n\r\nThe significance of this announcement extends beyond just the athletes; it represents a growing recognition of esports as a legitimate sport in the Philippines. With the government and private sectors increasingly supporting esports initiatives, the nation is poised to cultivate a thriving esports ecosystem. The upcoming Asian Games will serve as a pivotal moment for Filipino gamers, potentially paving the way for future international competitions and collaborations. As fans eagerly await the events, the pressure is on Sibol to not only perform well but to inspire a new generation of gamers in the Philippines.', 56, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699d1bee9fe5b3.12555179.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:52', '2026-02-25 03:22:52', '2026-02-25 11:22:52', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(210, 160, NULL, 'Cyberzone’s E-Waste Initiative: A Milestone in Sustainable Disposal', 'In an era where technology is rapidly evolving, the challenge of managing electronic waste (e-waste) is becoming increasingly significant. Recognizing this pressing issue, Cyberzone has taken a commendable step towards promoting responsible e-waste disposal by establishing strategic drop-off points across communities. Recently, the initiative successfully collected an impressive 14,000 kilograms of e-waste, demonstrating a commitment to sustainability and environmental stewardship. This initiative not only provides a convenient solution for residents but also raises awareness about the importance of proper e-waste disposal.\r\n\r\nThe collection effort by Cyberzone underscores the growing need for accessible e-waste disposal options. With millions of electronic devices being discarded annually, the potential for harmful environmental impact is substantial. By setting up multiple drop-off points, Cyberzone has made it easier for individuals and businesses to recycle their old gadgets responsibly. This accessibility is crucial in encouraging more people to participate in e-waste recycling, as it removes barriers such as distance and inconvenience. Furthermore, the initiative emphasizes the importance of community involvement in environmental efforts, fostering a collective responsibility towards sustainable practices.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the tangible benefits of e-waste collection, Cyberzone’s initiative serves as a catalyst for broader discussions about sustainability in the tech industry. As consumers become more aware of the environmental implications of their electronic purchases and disposal habits, companies like Cyberzone can lead the way in promoting eco-friendly practices. Through educational campaigns and partnerships with local governments, the initiative aims to inform the public about the dangers of e-waste and the importance of recycling. As more organizations join the movement towards responsible e-waste management, it paves the way for a greener future, where technology and sustainability go hand in hand. The success of this initiative marks a significant step forward, encouraging other companies to adopt similar practices and contribute to a healthier planet.', 49, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699d1b240b99a2.15384058.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:54', '2026-02-25 03:22:54', '2026-02-25 11:22:54', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(211, 159, NULL, 'Panawagang BBM Resign sa 40th Anniversary ng EDSA People Power Papayagan ng PNP', 'MANILA, Philippines — Aprub sa Philippine National Police (PNP) ang panawagang “BBM Resign” ng mga magpopro­testang sa 3rd Trillion Peso March at   ika-40 taong ­anibersaryo ng EDSA People Power bukas.\r\n\r\nIto sinabi ni PNP- National Capital Region Police Office (NCRPO) Spokesperson PMaj. Hazel Asilo sa ginanap na press briefing sa Camp Crame.\r\n\r\n\r\nAyon kay Asilo, bilang bahagi ng freedom of expression, hindi naman maikokosidera na paghihimagsik ang panawagang “BBM Resign”.\r\n\r\nAniya, ang hindi nila papayagan ay panghihikayat ng mga magprotesta na pagbagsakin ang pamahalaan, manggulo, manira, at magsunog ng mga government pro­perties.\r\n\r\nTiniyak naman ni PNP chief PGen. Jose Melencio Nartatez, Jr. na all systems go na ang latag ng seguridad para sa ­akitibidad bukas.\r\n\r\nNasa 13,448 pulis ang ipakakalat ng National Capital Region Police Office (NCRPO), kabilang ang augmentation personnel mula sa Police Regional Office 3 (Central Luzon) at Police Regional Office 4A (CALABARZON).\r\n\r\nHandang ring umalalay ang Armed Forces of the Philippines (AFP) partikular na ang National Capital Region Command (NCRCOM).', 48, 1, 13, 'uploads/thumb_699d19c57e4937.52118438.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:22:58', '2026-02-25 03:22:58', '2026-02-25 11:22:58', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(212, 158, NULL, 'Looking Back on Four Years of Strength: Ukraine Marks the Anniversary of Russia’s Invasion', 'As Ukraine marks the four-year anniversary of the Russian invasion, the nation reflects on a journey characterized by resilience, sacrifice, and unwavering determination. The conflict, which began on February 24, 2022, has profoundly shaped the socio-political landscape of Ukraine and the broader global community. Over the past four years, Ukrainians have come together in the face of adversity, showcasing an extraordinary spirit of unity and defiance against aggression that has garnered international support and solidarity.\r\n\r\nThe impact of the invasion has been felt on multiple fronts—military, economic, and humanitarian. Thousands of Ukrainian lives have been lost, and countless families have been displaced as they sought refuge from the ongoing conflict. Despite these challenges, the Ukrainian government and its citizens have worked tirelessly to rebuild and adapt, implementing reforms that aim to strengthen their democratic institutions and economy. The resolve of the Ukrainian people is evident in their commitment to safeguarding their sovereignty, as they continue to push back against external threats and advocate for their rights on the global stage.\r\n\r\nInternationally, the anniversary of the invasion serves as a poignant reminder of the importance of collective action against aggression and the need for continued support for Ukraine. As countries around the world reflect on the lessons learned from this conflict, the solidarity shown to Ukraine has underscored the significance of alliances and cooperation in addressing global security challenges. As Ukraine honors the memory of those who have fought bravely and sacrifices made over the past four years, it also looks toward the future, determined to emerge stronger and more united than ever in its quest for peace and stability.', 48, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699d197a8e9eb5.08205512.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:00', '2026-02-25 03:23:00', '2026-02-25 11:23:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(213, 157, NULL, 'Abi Marquez, the \"Lumpia Queen,\" Featured in Netflix\'s \"Being Gordon Ramsay\" Docuseries', 'Filipino food creator Abi Marquez, known as the \"Lumpia Queen,\" was recently featured in the Netflix documentary series \"Being Gordon Ramsay.\" The series follows the world-renowned chef during a pivotal period of expansion in his career, including the opening of five new restaurant concepts inside 22 Bishopsgate in London.\r\n\r\nMarquez\'s inclusion in the series reflects the evolving nature of today\'s culinary landscape, which is shaped not only by chefs and restaurants but also by digital creators who serve as cultural bridges. With over 10 million followers across social media, Marquez has emerged as one of Southeast Asia\'s most recognizable food creators, championing Filipino cuisine through accessible storytelling.\r\n\r\nBuilding on this global exposure, Marquez is set to take part in the upcoming Melbourne Food & Wine Festival, where she will collaborate with Melbourne-based Filipino-Italian chef Morris Danzen Catanghal at Nine Yards. Marquez has also shared a single behind-the-scenes, documentary-style video on her YouTube channel, offering a personal look at the experience from her perspective and underscoring the significance of the collaboration.', NULL, 1, 4, 'uploads/thumb_699d19665f5ea0.36430456.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:03', '2026-02-25 03:23:03', '2026-02-25 11:23:03', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(214, 155, NULL, 'E-bike charging explosion damages sedan, nearly burns down Pattaya home', 'PATTAYA, Thailand – A fire sparked by an electric bicycle left charging nearly engulfed a residential property in Pattaya on Monday morning, authorities said, as emergency crews moved quickly to prevent the blaze from spreading. The incident was reported at about 10:30 a.m. on February 23 at a home in Nongprue. Pol. Capt. Janda Dermpan, […]\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Pattaya Mail\r\nSource: pattayamail\r\nPublished: February 24, 2026', 97, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d16c141d030.77850615.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:05', '2026-02-25 03:23:05', '2026-02-25 11:23:05', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(215, 154, NULL, 'GoTyme Bank becomes top Visa debit card in the Philippines', 'GoTyme Bank is now the most-used Visa debit card in the Philippines. This milestone was announced on February 19 by...\r\nThe post GoTyme Bank becomes top Visa debit card in the Philippines appeared first on YugaTech | Philippines Tech News & Reviews.\r\n\r\n---\r\nAuthor: Bryan Aliwalas\r\nSource: Yugatech.com\r\nPublished: February 23, 2026', 97, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d1610914d42.48232189.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:08', '2026-02-25 03:23:08', '2026-02-25 11:23:08', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(216, 153, NULL, 'Brazilian Sauropod Fossil Points to Prehistoric Intercontinental Migration', 'Paleontologists in Brazil have identified a new species of somphospondylan sauropod that provides fresh insight into dinosaur migration between ancient landmasses. The species, named Dasosaurus tocantinensis, lived around 120 million years ago during the Early Cretaceous period, when the southern supercontinent Gondwana had not yet fully broken apart. Measuring about 20 meters (66 feet) long, the massive plant-eater belonged to Somphospondyli, a group of titanosauriform sauropods that thrived from the Late Jurassic until the end of the Cretaceous.\r\n\r\nFossil remains, including a partial skeleton, were unearthed from the Itapecuru Formation in northeastern Brazil. Researchers identified distinctive features in the dinosaur’s tail vertebrae, which display three elongated ridges and grooves, as well as a pronounced lateral bulge on the thigh bone — a combination not previously recorded in other species. These anatomical traits indicate that Dasosaurus tocantinensis falls outside the titanosaur lineage that later dominated the southern continents and is instead closely related to Garumbatitan morellensis, a sauropod discovered in Spain and dated to about 122 million years ago.\r\n\r\nScientists say the find supports the idea that South America was connected to other regions during the Early Cretaceous, allowing dinosaur lineages to disperse across continents before the Atlantic Ocean fully formed. According to lead author Dr. Max Langer of the Universidade de São Paulo, biogeographical analyses suggest the lineage shared by the Brazilian and Spanish species likely originated in Europe before spreading to South America via northern Africa between 137 and 113 million years ago. The discovery was detailed in a study published on Feb. 12 in the Journal of Systematic Palaeontology.', 95, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d154d754fc8.18507153.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:11', '2026-02-25 03:23:11', '2026-02-25 11:23:11', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(217, 152, 194, 'Pacquiao, Mayweather Set for Long-Awaited September Rematch in Las Vegas', 'Boxing legends Manny Pacquiao and Floyd Mayweather are set to meet again in a professional rematch on Sept. 19 at the Sphere in Las Vegas, with the event to be streamed live on Netflix. Mayweather, 48, confirmed he is coming out of retirement for another professional bout, his first since stopping Conor McGregor in 2017. Pacquiao, 47, who stepped away from boxing in 2021 to focus on politics, returned to the ring last year and fought WBC welterweight champion Mario Barrios to a draw.\r\n\r\nTheir initial encounter in 2015, dubbed the “Fight of the Century,” became the richest fight in boxing history. Mayweather secured a unanimous decision victory in a match that drew a record 4.6 million pay-per-view buys and generated a $72-million live gate at the MGM Grand Garden Arena. The upcoming rematch revives one of boxing’s most talked-about rivalries, though details such as the weight class and number of rounds have yet to be finalized.\r\n\r\nMayweather heads into the bout with an unblemished 50-0 professional record, including 27 knockouts, while Pacquiao boasts 62 wins in 73 fights and holds the distinction of winning 12 world titles across eight divisions. Both fighters have expressed confidence ahead of their second showdown, which is expected to draw global attention as more information on ticket sales and the undercard is announced in the coming weeks.', 56, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d13ce1336f.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, '', 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:15', '2026-02-25 03:23:15', '2026-02-25 11:23:15', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(218, 151, 197, 'Moreno Reunites with 2022 Rivals at Malacañang Event', 'Manila Mayor Francisco “Isko Moreno” Domagoso joined President Ferdinand R. Marcos Jr. and Naga City Mayor Leni Robredo at Malacañang on Monday during the launch of the “Sa Bagong Pilipinas, Bawat Bayan Makikinabang” initiative, a program aimed at strengthening national government support for local government units through the Local Government Support Fund. The three leaders, who faced off in the 2022 presidential race, were seen together with other LGU officials in a gathering that underscored cooperation between national and local governments.\r\n\r\nMoreno expressed appreciation for the administration’s assistance to LGUs, saying he was pleased that support continues despite past political differences. The event also marked another public encounter between Marcos and Robredo, following the President’s recent visit to Naga City to inspect flood control efforts and turn over P500 million for the rehabilitation of the Jesse M. Robredo Coliseum. While speculation about future political alignments persists, all parties emphasized governance and public service over politics.', 48, 1, 8, 'uploads/thumb_699d12fa61a6f.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 1, '', 1, '2026-02-25 03:23:18', '2026-02-25 03:23:18', '2026-02-25 11:23:18', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(219, 181, NULL, 'SCHEDULE: Gilas Pilipinas at Fiba World Cup Asian Qualifiers Window 2', 'MANILA, Philippines–Gilas Pilipinas sees action in the second window of the Fiba Basketball World Cup 2027 Asian Qualifiers in Manila.\r\n\r\nThe Philippines hosts New Zealand and Australia in a pair of home games at Mall of Asia Arena on February 26 and March 1.\r\n\r\nGilas Pilipinas during the Fiba Basketball World Cup 2027 Asian Qualifiers. \r\n\r\nGilas, slotted in Group A, opened the qualifiers with a 2-0 record after sweeping Guam last December.\r\n\r\nSCHEDULE: Fiba World Cup Asian Qualifiers (second window)\r\nFebruary 26,  Thursday – Mall of Asia Arena\r\n\r\n7:30pm – Gilas Pilipinas vs New Zealand\r\nMarch 1, Sunday – Mall of Asia Arena\r\n\r\n7:30pm – Gilas Pilipinas vs Australia', 56, 1, 13, 'uploads/thumb_699ea805b6c653.04588660.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-26 02:30:24', '2026-02-26 02:30:24', '2026-02-26 10:30:24', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(220, 180, NULL, 'The Impact of AI on Philippine Employment and Consumer Spending: Insights from Visa', 'As artificial intelligence (AI) continues to advance and integrate into various sectors, its implications for employment and consumer spending in the Philippines are becoming increasingly significant. A recent report from Visa highlights the potential challenges the country may face as automation and AI technologies reshape the job market and consumer behavior. With a workforce that is largely engaged in tasks that can be automated, it is essential to examine how these changes could affect not only individual livelihoods but also the broader economic landscape.\r\n\r\nThe Philippines has long been known for its robust service and customer support sectors, which employ millions of workers. However, as AI systems become more sophisticated and capable of handling tasks traditionally performed by humans, there is a growing concern about job displacement. Visa\'s report suggests that up to 30% of jobs in the country could be at risk as businesses increasingly adopt AI solutions to enhance efficiency and reduce costs. This shift could lead to heightened unemployment rates and exacerbate existing economic inequalities, particularly among low-skilled workers who may find it challenging to transition into new roles in an evolving job market.\r\n\r\nIn addition to its impact on employment, the rise of AI is also poised to influence consumer spending patterns. With automation driving down operational costs, businesses may lower prices or improve service quality, potentially altering consumer behavior. However, if significant job losses occur, disposable income will likely decrease, leading to reduced consumer spending overall. This creates a paradox where, even though some may benefit from lower prices and improved services, the wider economic repercussions of job losses could stifle growth and limit purchasing power across the board. \r\n\r\nAs the Philippines navigates this transformative technological landscape, it is crucial for stakeholders, including the government, businesses, and educational institutions, to collaborate on strategies that will mitigate the adverse effects of AI on employment and consumer spending. Investing in reskilling and upskilling programs will be key to empowering workers to adapt to the changing job market while also fostering a culture of innovation and entrepreneurship. By embracing the opportunities that AI presents and addressing the challenges head-on, the Philippines can position itself to thrive in an increasingly automated future.', 49, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699ea75c23b4e3.24516432.webp', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-26 02:30:26', '2026-02-26 02:30:26', '2026-02-26 10:30:26', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(221, 179, NULL, 'Min Hee-jin offers to give up $17.9 million payout if HYBE ends legal fight', 'Min Hee-jin, the former head of ADOR who created the girl group NewJeans, has proposed that HYBE drop all ongoing civil and criminal litigation and bring their dispute to a close.\r\n\r\nIn return, she offered to forgo the 25.6 billion won (or $17.9 million) put option payment she is set to receive following her recent court victory against HYBE, framing the offer as an effort to resolve the protracted conflict.\r\n\r\nAt a press conference, Min said she is willing to give up the payout the court awarded her if HYBE agrees to terminate all related lawsuits including those involving NewJeans members and other parties connected to the conflict.\r\n\r\nShe also stated that ending the prolonged legal battle would “help prevent further harm to artists and the industry.”\r\n\r\nMin also urged HYBE and its chairman Bang Si-hyuk to shift their focus “from the courtroom to the stage of creation,” adding that she intends to relinquish her title as the former CEO of ADOR and move forward in her role as the CEO of Ooak Records.', 55, 1, 13, 'uploads/thumb_699ea744ed1ee2.83006529.png', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-26 02:30:29', '2026-02-26 02:30:29', '2026-02-26 10:30:29', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(222, 178, NULL, 'Iloilo Takes Center Stage: Hosting ASEAN Economic Talks to Foster Regional Collaboration', 'Iloilo City has recently emerged as a significant player in Southeast Asia\'s economic landscape by hosting the ASEAN Economic Talks. This event marks a crucial turning point for the city, underscoring its growing influence and commitment to enhancing collaboration among the ASEAN member states. With its strategic location, rich agricultural resources, and evolving infrastructure, Iloilo is poised to serve as a vital hub for trade and investment, facilitating economic growth within the region. The talks not only spotlighted Iloilo\'s potential but also offered a platform for dialogue on pressing economic issues facing the ASEAN community.\r\n\r\nThe ASEAN Economic Talks convened a diverse array of participants, including government officials, business leaders, and economic experts from various Southeast Asian nations. During the discussions, attendees explored essential topics such as trade facilitation, investment opportunities, and sustainable development strategies. The local government of Iloilo showcased its commitment to creating an inviting business environment, highlighting ongoing projects aimed at improving transportation, logistics, and overall infrastructure. By focusing on these areas, Iloilo is positioning itself as an attractive destination for both local and foreign investments, paving the way for enhanced economic activity and collaboration.\r\n\r\nBeyond economic discussions, Iloilo City is dedicated to fostering cultural exchange among ASEAN nations. The talks provided a unique opportunity for participants to engage in meaningful relationships that extend beyond business, encouraging collaboration on various levels. By hosting such influential gatherings, Iloilo aims to strengthen its ties within the ASEAN framework while promoting sustainable growth and development. As the city evolves into a regional trade center, the outlook for increased economic collaboration and prosperity with its ASEAN neighbors is brighter than ever, positioning Iloilo as a promising beacon of opportunity in Southeast Asia.', 49, 1, 10, 'uploads/thumb_699ea6b3d566c5.41293165.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'manual', 1, 0, NULL, 1, '2026-02-26 02:30:32', '2026-02-26 02:30:32', '2026-02-26 10:30:32', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'normal', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
